125 template <typename T, typename Allocator>
126 static StringRef bytes(const std::vector<T, Allocator> &v) {
127  if (v.empty()) return StringRef();
128  return StringRef(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(&v[0]),
129  sizeof(T) * v.size());
130 }
131 
132 template <typename T>
133 static StringRef bytes(const SmallVectorImpl<T> &v) {
134  return StringRef(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(v.data()),
135  sizeof(T) * v.size());
136 }
137 
138 static std::string bytes(const std::vector<bool> &V) {
139  std::string Str;
140  Str.reserve(V.size() / 8);
141  for (unsigned I = 0, E = V.size(); I < E;) {
142  char Byte = 0;
143  for (unsigned Bit = 0; Bit < 8 && I < E; ++Bit, ++I)
144  Byte |= V[I] << Bit;
145  Str += Byte;
146  }
147  return Str;
148 }

154 static TypeCode getTypeCodeForTypeClass(Type::TypeClass id) {
155  switch (id) {
156 #define TYPE_BIT_CODE(CLASS_ID, CODE_ID, CODE_VALUE) \
157  case Type::CLASS_ID: return TYPE_##CODE_ID;
158 #include "clang/Serialization/TypeBitCodes.def"
159  case Type::Builtin:
160  llvm_unreachable("shouldn't be serializing a builtin type this way");
161  }
162  llvm_unreachable("bad type kind");
163 }

165 namespace {
166 
167 std::optional<std::set<const FileEntry *>>
168 GetAffectingModuleMaps(const Preprocessor &PP, Module *RootModule) {
169  if (!PP.getHeaderSearchInfo()
170  .getHeaderSearchOpts()
171  .ModulesPruneNonAffectingModuleMaps)
172  return std::nullopt;
173 
174  SmallVector<const Module *> ModulesToProcess{RootModule};
175 
176  const HeaderSearch &HS = PP.getHeaderSearchInfo();
177 
178  SmallVector<OptionalFileEntryRef, 16> FilesByUID;
179  HS.getFileMgr().GetUniqueIDMapping(FilesByUID);
180 
181  if (FilesByUID.size() > HS.header_file_size())
182  FilesByUID.resize(HS.header_file_size());
183 
184  for (unsigned UID = 0, LastUID = FilesByUID.size(); UID != LastUID; ++UID) {
185  OptionalFileEntryRef File = FilesByUID[UID];
186  if (!File)
187  continue;
188 
189  const HeaderFileInfo *HFI = HS.getExistingLocalFileInfo(*File);
190  if (!HFI || (HFI->isModuleHeader && !HFI->isCompilingModuleHeader))
191  continue;
192 
193  for (const auto &KH : HS.findResolvedModulesForHeader(*File)) {
194  if (!KH.getModule())
195  continue;
196  ModulesToProcess.push_back(KH.getModule());
197  }
198  }
199 
200  const ModuleMap &MM = HS.getModuleMap();
201  SourceManager &SourceMgr = PP.getSourceManager();
202 
203  std::set<const FileEntry *> ModuleMaps;
204  auto CollectIncludingModuleMaps = [&](FileID FID, FileEntryRef F) {
205  if (!ModuleMaps.insert(F).second)
206  return;
207  SourceLocation Loc = SourceMgr.getIncludeLoc(FID);
208  // The include location of inferred module maps can point into the header
209  // file that triggered the inferring. Cut off the walk if that's the case.
210  while (Loc.isValid() && isModuleMap(SourceMgr.getFileCharacteristic(Loc))) {
211  FID = SourceMgr.getFileID(Loc);
212  F = *SourceMgr.getFileEntryRefForID(FID);
213  if (!ModuleMaps.insert(F).second)
214  break;
215  Loc = SourceMgr.getIncludeLoc(FID);
216  }
217  };
218 
219  std::set<const Module *> ProcessedModules;
220  auto CollectIncludingMapsFromAncestors = [&](const Module *M) {
221  for (const Module *Mod = M; Mod; Mod = Mod->Parent) {
222  if (!ProcessedModules.insert(Mod).second)
223  break;
224  // The containing module map is affecting, because it's being pointed
225  // into by Module::DefinitionLoc.
226  if (FileID FID = MM.getContainingModuleMapFileID(Mod); FID.isValid())
227  CollectIncludingModuleMaps(FID, *SourceMgr.getFileEntryRefForID(FID));
228  // For inferred modules, the module map that allowed inferring is not in
229  // the include chain of the virtual containing module map file. It did
230  // affect the compilation, though.
231  if (FileID FID = MM.getModuleMapFileIDForUniquing(Mod); FID.isValid())
232  CollectIncludingModuleMaps(FID, *SourceMgr.getFileEntryRefForID(FID));
233  }
234  };
235 
236  for (const Module *CurrentModule : ModulesToProcess) {
237  CollectIncludingMapsFromAncestors(CurrentModule);
238  for (const Module *ImportedModule : CurrentModule->Imports)
239  CollectIncludingMapsFromAncestors(ImportedModule);
240  for (const Module *UndeclaredModule : CurrentModule->UndeclaredUses)
241  CollectIncludingMapsFromAncestors(UndeclaredModule);
242  }
243 
244  return ModuleMaps;
245 }
246 
247 class ASTTypeWriter {
248  ASTWriter &Writer;
249  ASTWriter::RecordData Record;
250  ASTRecordWriter BasicWriter;
251 
252 public:
253  ASTTypeWriter(ASTWriter &Writer)
254  : Writer(Writer), BasicWriter(Writer, Record) {}
255 
256  uint64_t write(QualType T) {
257  if (T.hasLocalNonFastQualifiers()) {
258  Qualifiers Qs = T.getLocalQualifiers();
259  BasicWriter.writeQualType(T.getLocalUnqualifiedType());
260  BasicWriter.writeQualifiers(Qs);
261  return BasicWriter.Emit(TYPE_EXT_QUAL, Writer.getTypeExtQualAbbrev());
262  }
263 
264  const Type *typePtr = T.getTypePtr();
265  serialization::AbstractTypeWriter<ASTRecordWriter> atw(BasicWriter);
266  atw.write(typePtr);
267  return BasicWriter.Emit(getTypeCodeForTypeClass(typePtr->getTypeClass()),
268  /*abbrev*/ 0);
269  }
270 };

272 class TypeLocWriter : public TypeLocVisitor<TypeLocWriter> {
273  using LocSeq = SourceLocationSequence;
274 
275  ASTRecordWriter &Record;
276  LocSeq *Seq;
277 
278  void addSourceLocation(SourceLocation Loc) {
279  Record.AddSourceLocation(Loc, Seq);
280  }
281  void addSourceRange(SourceRange Range) { Record.AddSourceRange(Range, Seq); }
282 
283 public:
284  TypeLocWriter(ASTRecordWriter &Record, LocSeq *Seq)
285  : Record(Record), Seq(Seq) {}
286 
287 #define ABSTRACT_TYPELOC(CLASS, PARENT)
288 #define TYPELOC(CLASS, PARENT) \
289  void Visit##CLASS##TypeLoc(CLASS##TypeLoc TyLoc);
290 #include "clang/AST/TypeLocNodes.def"
291 
292  void VisitArrayTypeLoc(ArrayTypeLoc TyLoc);
293  void VisitFunctionTypeLoc(FunctionTypeLoc TyLoc);
294 };
295

299  // nothing to do
300 }

302 void TypeLocWriter::VisitBuiltinTypeLoc(BuiltinTypeLoc TL) {
303  addSourceLocation(TL.getBuiltinLoc());
304  if (TL.needsExtraLocalData()) {
305  Record.push_back(TL.getWrittenTypeSpec());
306  Record.push_back(static_cast<uint64_t>(TL.getWrittenSignSpec()));
307  Record.push_back(static_cast<uint64_t>(TL.getWrittenWidthSpec()));
308  Record.push_back(TL.hasModeAttr());
309  }
310 }

349 void TypeLocWriter::VisitArrayTypeLoc(ArrayTypeLoc TL) {
350  addSourceLocation(TL.getLBracketLoc());
351  addSourceLocation(TL.getRBracketLoc());
352  Record.push_back(TL.getSizeExpr() ? 1 : 0);
353  if (TL.getSizeExpr())
354  Record.AddStmt(TL.getSizeExpr());
355 }

420 void TypeLocWriter::VisitFunctionTypeLoc(FunctionTypeLoc TL) {
421  addSourceLocation(TL.getLocalRangeBegin());
422  addSourceLocation(TL.getLParenLoc());
423  addSourceLocation(TL.getRParenLoc());
424  addSourceRange(TL.getExceptionSpecRange());
425  addSourceLocation(TL.getLocalRangeEnd());
426  for (unsigned i = 0, e = TL.getNumParams(); i != e; ++i)
427  Record.AddDeclRef(TL.getParam(i));
428 }

484 void ASTRecordWriter::AddConceptReference(const ConceptReference *CR) {
485  assert(CR);
486  AddNestedNameSpecifierLoc(CR->getNestedNameSpecifierLoc());
487  AddSourceLocation(CR->getTemplateKWLoc());
488  AddDeclarationNameInfo(CR->getConceptNameInfo());
489  AddDeclRef(CR->getFoundDecl());
490  AddDeclRef(CR->getNamedConcept());
491  push_back(CR->getTemplateArgsAsWritten() != nullptr);
492  if (CR->getTemplateArgsAsWritten())
493  AddASTTemplateArgumentListInfo(CR->getTemplateArgsAsWritten());
494 }

500 void TypeLocWriter::VisitAutoTypeLoc(AutoTypeLoc TL) {
501  addSourceLocation(TL.getNameLoc());
502  auto *CR = TL.getConceptReference();
503  Record.push_back(TL.isConstrained() && CR);
504  if (TL.isConstrained() && CR)
505  Record.AddConceptReference(CR);
506  Record.push_back(TL.isDecltypeAuto());
507  if (TL.isDecltypeAuto())
508  addSourceLocation(TL.getRParenLoc());
509 }

550 void TypeLocWriter::VisitTemplateSpecializationTypeLoc(
551  TemplateSpecializationTypeLoc TL) {

557  Record.AddTemplateArgumentLocInfo(TL.getArgLoc(i).getArgument().getKind(),
558  TL.getArgLoc(i).getLocInfo());
559 }

585 void TypeLocWriter::VisitDependentTemplateSpecializationTypeLoc(
586  DependentTemplateSpecializationTypeLoc TL) {
587  addSourceLocation(TL.getElaboratedKeywordLoc());
588  Record.AddNestedNameSpecifierLoc(TL.getQualifierLoc());
589  addSourceLocation(TL.getTemplateKeywordLoc());
590  addSourceLocation(TL.getTemplateNameLoc());
591  addSourceLocation(TL.getLAngleLoc());
592  addSourceLocation(TL.getRAngleLoc());
593  for (unsigned I = 0, E = TL.getNumArgs(); I != E; ++I)
594  Record.AddTemplateArgumentLocInfo(TL.getArgLoc(I).getArgument().getKind(),
595  TL.getArgLoc(I).getLocInfo());
596 }

607 void TypeLocWriter::VisitObjCObjectTypeLoc(ObjCObjectTypeLoc TL) {
608  Record.push_back(TL.hasBaseTypeAsWritten());
609  addSourceLocation(TL.getTypeArgsLAngleLoc());
610  addSourceLocation(TL.getTypeArgsRAngleLoc());
611  for (unsigned i = 0, e = TL.getNumTypeArgs(); i != e; ++i)
612  Record.AddTypeSourceInfo(TL.getTypeArgTInfo(i));
613  addSourceLocation(TL.getProtocolLAngleLoc());
614  addSourceLocation(TL.getProtocolRAngleLoc());
615  for (unsigned i = 0, e = TL.getNumProtocols(); i != e; ++i)
616  addSourceLocation(TL.getProtocolLoc(i));
617 }
618 
619 void TypeLocWriter::VisitObjCObjectPointerTypeLoc(ObjCObjectPointerTypeLoc TL) {
620  addSourceLocation(TL.getStarLoc());
621 }
622 
623 void TypeLocWriter::VisitAtomicTypeLoc(AtomicTypeLoc TL) {
624  addSourceLocation(TL.getKWLoc());
625  addSourceLocation(TL.getLParenLoc());
626  addSourceLocation(TL.getRParenLoc());
627 }

629 void TypeLocWriter::VisitPipeTypeLoc(PipeTypeLoc TL) {
630  addSourceLocation(TL.getKWLoc());
631 }

633 void TypeLocWriter::VisitBitIntTypeLoc(clang::BitIntTypeLoc TL) {
634  addSourceLocation(TL.getNameLoc());
635 }
636 void TypeLocWriter::VisitDependentBitIntTypeLoc(
637  clang::DependentBitIntTypeLoc TL) {
638  addSourceLocation(TL.getNameLoc());
639 }

641 void ASTWriter::WriteTypeAbbrevs() {
642  using namespace llvm;
643 
644  std::shared_ptr<BitCodeAbbrev> Abv;
645 
646  // Abbreviation for TYPE_EXT_QUAL
647  Abv = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
648  Abv->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(serialization::TYPE_EXT_QUAL));
649  Abv->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 6)); // Type
650  Abv->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 3)); // Quals
651  TypeExtQualAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abv));
652 }

654 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
655 // ASTWriter Implementation
656 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
657 
658 static void EmitBlockID(unsigned ID, const char *Name,
659  llvm::BitstreamWriter &Stream,
660  ASTWriter::RecordDataImpl &Record) {
661  Record.clear();
662  Record.push_back(ID);
663  Stream.EmitRecord(llvm::bitc::BLOCKINFO_CODE_SETBID, Record);
664 
665  // Emit the block name if present.
666  if (!Name || Name[0] == 0)
667  return;
668  Record.clear();
669  while (*Name)
670  Record.push_back(*Name++);
671  Stream.EmitRecord(llvm::bitc::BLOCKINFO_CODE_BLOCKNAME, Record);
672 }
673 
674 static void EmitRecordID(unsigned ID, const char *Name,
675  llvm::BitstreamWriter &Stream,
676  ASTWriter::RecordDataImpl &Record) {
677  Record.clear();
678  Record.push_back(ID);
679  while (*Name)
680  Record.push_back(*Name++);
681  Stream.EmitRecord(llvm::bitc::BLOCKINFO_CODE_SETRECORDNAME, Record);
682 }

1087 
1088 /// Prepares a path for being written to an AST file by converting it
1089 /// to an absolute path and removing nested './'s.
1090 ///
1091 /// \return \c true if the path was changed.
1092 static bool cleanPathForOutput(FileManager &FileMgr,
1093  SmallVectorImpl<char> &Path) {
1094  bool Changed = FileMgr.makeAbsolutePath(Path);
1095  return Changed | llvm::sys::path::remove_dots(Path);
1096 }
1097 
1098 /// Adjusts the given filename to only write out the portion of the
1099 /// filename that is not part of the system root directory.
1100 ///
1101 /// \param Filename the file name to adjust.
1102 ///
1103 /// \param BaseDir When non-NULL, the PCH file is a relocatable AST file and
1104 /// the returned filename will be adjusted by this root directory.
1105 ///
1106 /// \returns either the original filename (if it needs no adjustment) or the
1107 /// adjusted filename (which points into the @p Filename parameter).
1108 static const char *
1109 adjustFilenameForRelocatableAST(const char *Filename, StringRef BaseDir) {
1110  assert(Filename && "No file name to adjust?");
1111 
1112  if (BaseDir.empty())
1113  return Filename;
1114 
1115  // Verify that the filename and the system root have the same prefix.
1116  unsigned Pos = 0;
1117  for (; Filename[Pos] && Pos < BaseDir.size(); ++Pos)
1118  if (Filename[Pos] != BaseDir[Pos])
1119  return Filename; // Prefixes don't match.
1120 
1121  // We hit the end of the filename before we hit the end of the system root.
1122  if (!Filename[Pos])
1123  return Filename;
1124 
1125  // If there's not a path separator at the end of the base directory nor
1126  // immediately after it, then this isn't within the base directory.
1127  if (!llvm::sys::path::is_separator(Filename[Pos])) {
1128  if (!llvm::sys::path::is_separator(BaseDir.back()))
1129  return Filename;
1130  } else {
1131  // If the file name has a '/' at the current position, skip over the '/'.
1132  // We distinguish relative paths from absolute paths by the
1133  // absence of '/' at the beginning of relative paths.
1134  //
1135  // FIXME: This is wrong. We distinguish them by asking if the path is
1136  // absolute, which isn't the same thing. And there might be multiple '/'s
1137  // in a row. Use a better mechanism to indicate whether we have emitted an
1138  // absolute or relative path.
1139  ++Pos;
1140  }
1141 
1142  return Filename + Pos;
1143 }
1144 
1145 std::pair<ASTFileSignature, ASTFileSignature>
1146 ASTWriter::createSignature() const {
1147  StringRef AllBytes(Buffer.data(), Buffer.size());
1148 
1149  llvm::SHA1 Hasher;
1150  Hasher.update(AllBytes.slice(ASTBlockRange.first, ASTBlockRange.second));
1151  ASTFileSignature ASTBlockHash = ASTFileSignature::create(Hasher.result());
1152 
1153  // Add the remaining bytes:
1154  // 1. Before the unhashed control block.
1155  Hasher.update(AllBytes.slice(0, UnhashedControlBlockRange.first));
1156  // 2. Between the unhashed control block and the AST block.
1157  Hasher.update(
1158  AllBytes.slice(UnhashedControlBlockRange.second, ASTBlockRange.first));
1159  // 3. After the AST block.
1160  Hasher.update(AllBytes.slice(ASTBlockRange.second, StringRef::npos));
1161  ASTFileSignature Signature = ASTFileSignature::create(Hasher.result());
1162 
1163  return std::make_pair(ASTBlockHash, Signature);
1164 }
1165 
1166 ASTFileSignature ASTWriter::backpatchSignature() {
1167  if (!WritingModule ||
1168  !PP->getHeaderSearchInfo().getHeaderSearchOpts().ModulesHashContent)
1169  return {};
1170 
1171  // For implicit modules, write the hash of the PCM as its signature.
1172 
1173  auto BackpatchSignatureAt = [&](const ASTFileSignature &S, uint64_t BitNo) {
1174  for (uint8_t Byte : S) {
1175  Stream.BackpatchByte(BitNo, Byte);
1176  BitNo += 8;
1177  }
1178  };
1179 
1180  ASTFileSignature ASTBlockHash;
1181  ASTFileSignature Signature;
1182  std::tie(ASTBlockHash, Signature) = createSignature();
1183 
1184  BackpatchSignatureAt(ASTBlockHash, ASTBlockHashOffset);
1185  BackpatchSignatureAt(Signature, SignatureOffset);
1186 
1187  return Signature;
1188 }
1189 
1190 void ASTWriter::writeUnhashedControlBlock(Preprocessor &PP,
1191  ASTContext &Context) {
1192  using namespace llvm;
1193 
1194  // Flush first to prepare the PCM hash (signature).
1195  Stream.FlushToWord();
1196  UnhashedControlBlockRange.first = Stream.GetCurrentBitNo() >> 3;
1197 
1198  // Enter the block and prepare to write records.
1199  RecordData Record;
1200  Stream.EnterSubblock(UNHASHED_CONTROL_BLOCK_ID, 5);
1201 
1202  // For implicit modules, write the hash of the PCM as its signature.
1203  if (WritingModule &&
1204  PP.getHeaderSearchInfo().getHeaderSearchOpts().ModulesHashContent) {
1205  // At this point, we don't know the actual signature of the file or the AST
1206  // block - we're only able to compute those at the end of the serialization
1207  // process. Let's store dummy signatures for now, and replace them with the
1208  // real ones later on.
1209  // The bitstream VBR-encodes record elements, which makes backpatching them
1210  // really difficult. Let's store the signatures as blobs instead - they are
1211  // guaranteed to be word-aligned, and we control their format/encoding.
1212  auto Dummy = ASTFileSignature::createDummy();
1213  SmallString<128> Blob{Dummy.begin(), Dummy.end()};
1214 
1215  auto Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
1216  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(AST_BLOCK_HASH));
1217  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob));
1218  unsigned ASTBlockHashAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
1219 
1220  Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
1221  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(SIGNATURE));
1222  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob));
1223  unsigned SignatureAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
1224 
1225  Record.push_back(AST_BLOCK_HASH);
1226  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(ASTBlockHashAbbrev, Record, Blob);
1227  ASTBlockHashOffset = Stream.GetCurrentBitNo() - Blob.size() * 8;
1228  Record.clear();
1229 
1230  Record.push_back(SIGNATURE);
1231  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(SignatureAbbrev, Record, Blob);
1232  SignatureOffset = Stream.GetCurrentBitNo() - Blob.size() * 8;
1233  Record.clear();
1234  }
1235 
1236  const auto &HSOpts = PP.getHeaderSearchInfo().getHeaderSearchOpts();
1237 
1238  // Diagnostic options.
1239  const auto &Diags = Context.getDiagnostics();
1240  const DiagnosticOptions &DiagOpts = Diags.getDiagnosticOptions();
1241  if (!HSOpts.ModulesSkipDiagnosticOptions) {
1242 #define DIAGOPT(Name, Bits, Default) Record.push_back(DiagOpts.Name);
1243 #define ENUM_DIAGOPT(Name, Type, Bits, Default) \
1244  Record.push_back(static_cast<unsigned>(DiagOpts.get##Name()));
1245 #include "clang/Basic/DiagnosticOptions.def"
1246  Record.push_back(DiagOpts.Warnings.size());
1247  for (unsigned I = 0, N = DiagOpts.Warnings.size(); I != N; ++I)
1248  AddString(DiagOpts.Warnings[I], Record);
1249  Record.push_back(DiagOpts.Remarks.size());
1250  for (unsigned I = 0, N = DiagOpts.Remarks.size(); I != N; ++I)
1251  AddString(DiagOpts.Remarks[I], Record);
1252  // Note: we don't serialize the log or serialization file names, because
1253  // they are generally transient files and will almost always be overridden.
1254  Stream.EmitRecord(DIAGNOSTIC_OPTIONS, Record);
1255  Record.clear();
1256  }
1257 
1258  // Header search paths.
1259  if (!HSOpts.ModulesSkipHeaderSearchPaths) {
1260  // Include entries.
1261  Record.push_back(HSOpts.UserEntries.size());
1262  for (unsigned I = 0, N = HSOpts.UserEntries.size(); I != N; ++I) {
1263  const HeaderSearchOptions::Entry &Entry = HSOpts.UserEntries[I];
1264  AddString(Entry.Path, Record);
1265  Record.push_back(static_cast<unsigned>(Entry.Group));
1266  Record.push_back(Entry.IsFramework);
1267  Record.push_back(Entry.IgnoreSysRoot);
1268  }
1269 
1270  // System header prefixes.
1271  Record.push_back(HSOpts.SystemHeaderPrefixes.size());
1272  for (unsigned I = 0, N = HSOpts.SystemHeaderPrefixes.size(); I != N; ++I) {
1273  AddString(HSOpts.SystemHeaderPrefixes[I].Prefix, Record);
1274  Record.push_back(HSOpts.SystemHeaderPrefixes[I].IsSystemHeader);
1275  }
1276 
1277  // VFS overlay files.
1278  Record.push_back(HSOpts.VFSOverlayFiles.size());
1279  for (StringRef VFSOverlayFile : HSOpts.VFSOverlayFiles)
1280  AddString(VFSOverlayFile, Record);
1281 
1282  Stream.EmitRecord(HEADER_SEARCH_PATHS, Record);
1283  }
1284 
1285  if (!HSOpts.ModulesSkipPragmaDiagnosticMappings)
1286  WritePragmaDiagnosticMappings(Diags, /* isModule = */ WritingModule);
1287 
1288  // Header search entry usage.
1289  {
1290  auto HSEntryUsage = PP.getHeaderSearchInfo().computeUserEntryUsage();
1291  auto Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
1292  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(HEADER_SEARCH_ENTRY_USAGE));
1293  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 32)); // Number of bits.
1294  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob)); // Bit vector.
1295  unsigned HSUsageAbbrevCode = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
1296  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {HEADER_SEARCH_ENTRY_USAGE,
1297  HSEntryUsage.size()};
1298  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(HSUsageAbbrevCode, Record, bytes(HSEntryUsage));
1299  }
1300 
1301  // VFS usage.
1302  {
1303  auto VFSUsage = PP.getHeaderSearchInfo().collectVFSUsageAndClear();
1304  auto Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
1305  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(VFS_USAGE));
1306  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 32)); // Number of bits.
1307  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob)); // Bit vector.
1308  unsigned VFSUsageAbbrevCode = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
1309  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {VFS_USAGE, VFSUsage.size()};
1310  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(VFSUsageAbbrevCode, Record, bytes(VFSUsage));
1311  }
1312 
1313  // Leave the options block.
1314  Stream.ExitBlock();
1315  UnhashedControlBlockRange.second = Stream.GetCurrentBitNo() >> 3;
1316 }
1317 
1318 /// Write the control block.
1319 void ASTWriter::WriteControlBlock(Preprocessor &PP, ASTContext &Context,
1320  StringRef isysroot) {
1321  using namespace llvm;
1322 
1323  Stream.EnterSubblock(CONTROL_BLOCK_ID, 5);
1324  RecordData Record;
1325 
1326  // Metadata
1327  auto MetadataAbbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
1328  MetadataAbbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(METADATA));
1329  MetadataAbbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 16)); // Major
1330  MetadataAbbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 16)); // Minor
1331  MetadataAbbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 16)); // Clang maj.
1332  MetadataAbbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 16)); // Clang min.
1333  MetadataAbbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 1)); // Relocatable
1334  // Standard C++ module
1335  MetadataAbbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 1));
1336  MetadataAbbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 1)); // Timestamps
1337  MetadataAbbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 1)); // Errors
1338  MetadataAbbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob)); // SVN branch/tag
1339  unsigned MetadataAbbrevCode = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(MetadataAbbrev));
1340  assert((!WritingModule || isysroot.empty()) &&
1341  "writing module as a relocatable PCH?");
1342  {
1343  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {METADATA,
1344  VERSION_MAJOR,
1345  VERSION_MINOR,
1346  CLANG_VERSION_MAJOR,
1347  CLANG_VERSION_MINOR,
1348  !isysroot.empty(),
1349  isWritingStdCXXNamedModules(),
1350  IncludeTimestamps,
1351  ASTHasCompilerErrors};
1352  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(MetadataAbbrevCode, Record,
1353  getClangFullRepositoryVersion());
1354  }
1355 
1356  if (WritingModule) {
1357  // Module name
1358  auto Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
1359  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(MODULE_NAME));
1360  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob)); // Name
1361  unsigned AbbrevCode = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
1362  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {MODULE_NAME};
1363  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(AbbrevCode, Record, WritingModule->Name);
1364  }
1365 
1366  if (WritingModule && WritingModule->Directory) {
1367  SmallString<128> BaseDir;
1368  if (PP.getHeaderSearchInfo().getHeaderSearchOpts().ModuleFileHomeIsCwd) {
1369  // Use the current working directory as the base path for all inputs.
1370  auto CWD =
1371  Context.getSourceManager().getFileManager().getOptionalDirectoryRef(
1372  ".");
1373  BaseDir.assign(CWD->getName());
1374  } else {
1375  BaseDir.assign(WritingModule->Directory->getName());
1376  }
1377  cleanPathForOutput(Context.getSourceManager().getFileManager(), BaseDir);
1378 
1379  // If the home of the module is the current working directory, then we
1380  // want to pick up the cwd of the build process loading the module, not
1381  // our cwd, when we load this module.
1382  if (!PP.getHeaderSearchInfo().getHeaderSearchOpts().ModuleFileHomeIsCwd &&
1383  (!PP.getHeaderSearchInfo()
1384  .getHeaderSearchOpts()
1385  .ModuleMapFileHomeIsCwd ||
1386  WritingModule->Directory->getName() != StringRef("."))) {
1387  // Module directory.
1388  auto Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
1389  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(MODULE_DIRECTORY));
1390  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob)); // Directory
1391  unsigned AbbrevCode = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
1392 
1393  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {MODULE_DIRECTORY};
1394  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(AbbrevCode, Record, BaseDir);
1395  }
1396 
1397  // Write out all other paths relative to the base directory if possible.
1398  BaseDirectory.assign(BaseDir.begin(), BaseDir.end());
1399  } else if (!isysroot.empty()) {
1400  // Write out paths relative to the sysroot if possible.
1401  BaseDirectory = std::string(isysroot);
1402  }
1403 
1404  // Module map file
1405  if (WritingModule && WritingModule->Kind == Module::ModuleMapModule) {
1406  Record.clear();
1407 
1408  auto &Map = PP.getHeaderSearchInfo().getModuleMap();
1409  AddPath(WritingModule->PresumedModuleMapFile.empty()
1410  ? Map.getModuleMapFileForUniquing(WritingModule)
1411  ->getNameAsRequested()
1412  : StringRef(WritingModule->PresumedModuleMapFile),
1413  Record);
1414 
1415  // Additional module map files.
1416  if (auto *AdditionalModMaps =
1417  Map.getAdditionalModuleMapFiles(WritingModule)) {
1418  Record.push_back(AdditionalModMaps->size());
1419  SmallVector<FileEntryRef, 1> ModMaps(AdditionalModMaps->begin(),
1420  AdditionalModMaps->end());
1421  llvm::sort(ModMaps, [](FileEntryRef A, FileEntryRef B) {
1422  return A.getName() < B.getName();
1423  });
1424  for (FileEntryRef F : ModMaps)
1425  AddPath(F.getName(), Record);
1426  } else {
1427  Record.push_back(0);
1428  }
1429 
1430  Stream.EmitRecord(MODULE_MAP_FILE, Record);
1431  }
1432 
1433  // Imports
1434  if (Chain) {
1435  serialization::ModuleManager &Mgr = Chain->getModuleManager();
1436  Record.clear();
1437 
1438  for (ModuleFile &M : Mgr) {
1439  // Skip modules that weren't directly imported.
1440  if (!M.isDirectlyImported())
1441  continue;
1442 
1443  Record.push_back((unsigned)M.Kind); // FIXME: Stable encoding
1444  Record.push_back(M.StandardCXXModule);
1445  AddSourceLocation(M.ImportLoc, Record);
1446 
1447  // We don't want to hard code the information about imported modules
1448  // in the C++20 named modules.
1449  if (!M.StandardCXXModule) {
1450  // If we have calculated signature, there is no need to store
1451  // the size or timestamp.
1452  Record.push_back(M.Signature ? 0 : M.File.getSize());
1453  Record.push_back(M.Signature ? 0 : getTimestampForOutput(M.File));
1454  llvm::append_range(Record, M.Signature);
1455  }
1456 
1457  AddString(M.ModuleName, Record);
1458 
1459  if (!M.StandardCXXModule)
1460  AddPath(M.FileName, Record);
1461  }
1462  Stream.EmitRecord(IMPORTS, Record);
1463  }
1464 
1465  // Write the options block.
1466  Stream.EnterSubblock(OPTIONS_BLOCK_ID, 4);
1467 
1468  // Language options.
1469  Record.clear();
1470  const LangOptions &LangOpts = Context.getLangOpts();
1471 #define LANGOPT(Name, Bits, Default, Description) \
1472  Record.push_back(LangOpts.Name);
1473 #define ENUM_LANGOPT(Name, Type, Bits, Default, Description) \
1474  Record.push_back(static_cast<unsigned>(LangOpts.get##Name()));
1475 #include "clang/Basic/LangOptions.def"
1476 #define SANITIZER(NAME, ID) \
1477  Record.push_back(LangOpts.Sanitize.has(SanitizerKind::ID));
1478 #include "clang/Basic/Sanitizers.def"
1479 
1480  Record.push_back(LangOpts.ModuleFeatures.size());
1481  for (StringRef Feature : LangOpts.ModuleFeatures)
1482  AddString(Feature, Record);
1483 
1484  Record.push_back((unsigned) LangOpts.ObjCRuntime.getKind());
1485  AddVersionTuple(LangOpts.ObjCRuntime.getVersion(), Record);
1486 
1487  AddString(LangOpts.CurrentModule, Record);
1488 
1489  // Comment options.
1490  Record.push_back(LangOpts.CommentOpts.BlockCommandNames.size());
1491  for (const auto &I : LangOpts.CommentOpts.BlockCommandNames) {
1492  AddString(I, Record);
1493  }
1494  Record.push_back(LangOpts.CommentOpts.ParseAllComments);
1495 
1496  // OpenMP offloading options.
1497  Record.push_back(LangOpts.OMPTargetTriples.size());
1498  for (auto &T : LangOpts.OMPTargetTriples)
1499  AddString(T.getTriple(), Record);
1500 
1501  AddString(LangOpts.OMPHostIRFile, Record);
1502 
1503  Stream.EmitRecord(LANGUAGE_OPTIONS, Record);
1504 
1505  // Target options.
1506  Record.clear();
1507  const TargetInfo &Target = Context.getTargetInfo();
1508  const TargetOptions &TargetOpts = Target.getTargetOpts();
1509  AddString(TargetOpts.Triple, Record);
1510  AddString(TargetOpts.CPU, Record);
1511  AddString(TargetOpts.TuneCPU, Record);
1512  AddString(TargetOpts.ABI, Record);
1513  Record.push_back(TargetOpts.FeaturesAsWritten.size());
1514  for (unsigned I = 0, N = TargetOpts.FeaturesAsWritten.size(); I != N; ++I) {
1515  AddString(TargetOpts.FeaturesAsWritten[I], Record);
1516  }
1517  Record.push_back(TargetOpts.Features.size());
1518  for (unsigned I = 0, N = TargetOpts.Features.size(); I != N; ++I) {
1519  AddString(TargetOpts.Features[I], Record);
1520  }
1521  Stream.EmitRecord(TARGET_OPTIONS, Record);
1522 
1523  // File system options.
1524  Record.clear();
1525  const FileSystemOptions &FSOpts =
1526  Context.getSourceManager().getFileManager().getFileSystemOpts();
1527  AddString(FSOpts.WorkingDir, Record);
1528  Stream.EmitRecord(FILE_SYSTEM_OPTIONS, Record);
1529 
1530  // Header search options.
1531  Record.clear();
1532  const HeaderSearchOptions &HSOpts =
1533  PP.getHeaderSearchInfo().getHeaderSearchOpts();
1534 
1535  AddString(HSOpts.Sysroot, Record);
1536  AddString(HSOpts.ResourceDir, Record);
1537  AddString(HSOpts.ModuleCachePath, Record);
1538  AddString(HSOpts.ModuleUserBuildPath, Record);
1539  Record.push_back(HSOpts.DisableModuleHash);
1540  Record.push_back(HSOpts.ImplicitModuleMaps);
1541  Record.push_back(HSOpts.ModuleMapFileHomeIsCwd);
1542  Record.push_back(HSOpts.EnablePrebuiltImplicitModules);
1543  Record.push_back(HSOpts.UseBuiltinIncludes);
1544  Record.push_back(HSOpts.UseStandardSystemIncludes);
1545  Record.push_back(HSOpts.UseStandardCXXIncludes);
1546  Record.push_back(HSOpts.UseLibcxx);
1547  // Write out the specific module cache path that contains the module files.
1548  AddString(PP.getHeaderSearchInfo().getModuleCachePath(), Record);
1549  Stream.EmitRecord(HEADER_SEARCH_OPTIONS, Record);
1550 
1551  // Preprocessor options.
1552  Record.clear();
1553  const PreprocessorOptions &PPOpts = PP.getPreprocessorOpts();
1554 
1555  // If we're building an implicit module with a context hash, the importer is
1556  // guaranteed to have the same macros defined on the command line. Skip
1557  // writing them.
1558  bool SkipMacros = BuildingImplicitModule && !HSOpts.DisableModuleHash;
1559  bool WriteMacros = !SkipMacros;
1560  Record.push_back(WriteMacros);
1561  if (WriteMacros) {
1562  // Macro definitions.
1563  Record.push_back(PPOpts.Macros.size());
1564  for (unsigned I = 0, N = PPOpts.Macros.size(); I != N; ++I) {
1565  AddString(PPOpts.Macros[I].first, Record);
1566  Record.push_back(PPOpts.Macros[I].second);
1567  }
1568  }
1569 
1570  // Includes
1571  Record.push_back(PPOpts.Includes.size());
1572  for (unsigned I = 0, N = PPOpts.Includes.size(); I != N; ++I)
1573  AddString(PPOpts.Includes[I], Record);
1574 
1575  // Macro includes
1576  Record.push_back(PPOpts.MacroIncludes.size());
1577  for (unsigned I = 0, N = PPOpts.MacroIncludes.size(); I != N; ++I)
1578  AddString(PPOpts.MacroIncludes[I], Record);
1579 
1580  Record.push_back(PPOpts.UsePredefines);
1581  // Detailed record is important since it is used for the module cache hash.
1582  Record.push_back(PPOpts.DetailedRecord);
1583  AddString(PPOpts.ImplicitPCHInclude, Record);
1584  Record.push_back(static_cast<unsigned>(PPOpts.ObjCXXARCStandardLibrary));
1585  Stream.EmitRecord(PREPROCESSOR_OPTIONS, Record);
1586 
1587  // Leave the options block.
1588  Stream.ExitBlock();
1589 
1590  // Original file name and file ID
1591  SourceManager &SM = Context.getSourceManager();
1592  if (auto MainFile = SM.getFileEntryRefForID(SM.getMainFileID())) {
1593  auto FileAbbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
1594  FileAbbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(ORIGINAL_FILE));
1595  FileAbbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 6)); // File ID
1596  FileAbbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob)); // File name
1597  unsigned FileAbbrevCode = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(FileAbbrev));
1598 
1599  Record.clear();
1600  Record.push_back(ORIGINAL_FILE);
1601  AddFileID(SM.getMainFileID(), Record);
1602  EmitRecordWithPath(FileAbbrevCode, Record, MainFile->getName());
1603  }
1604 
1605  Record.clear();
1606  AddFileID(SM.getMainFileID(), Record);
1607  Stream.EmitRecord(ORIGINAL_FILE_ID, Record);
1608 
1609  WriteInputFiles(Context.SourceMgr,
1610  PP.getHeaderSearchInfo().getHeaderSearchOpts());
1611  Stream.ExitBlock();
1612 }
1613 
1614 namespace {
1615 
1616 /// An input file.
1617 struct InputFileEntry {
1618  FileEntryRef File;
1619  bool IsSystemFile;
1620  bool IsTransient;
1621  bool BufferOverridden;
1622  bool IsTopLevel;
1623  bool IsModuleMap;
1624  uint32_t ContentHash[2];
1625 
1626  InputFileEntry(FileEntryRef File) : File(File) {}
1627 };
1628 
1629 } // namespace
1630 
1631 void ASTWriter::WriteInputFiles(SourceManager &SourceMgr,
1632  HeaderSearchOptions &HSOpts) {
1633  using namespace llvm;
1634 
1635  Stream.EnterSubblock(INPUT_FILES_BLOCK_ID, 4);
1636 
1637  // Create input-file abbreviation.
1638  auto IFAbbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
1639  IFAbbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(INPUT_FILE));
1640  IFAbbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 6)); // ID
1641  IFAbbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 12)); // Size
1642  IFAbbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 32)); // Modification time
1643  IFAbbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 1)); // Overridden
1644  IFAbbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 1)); // Transient
1645  IFAbbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 1)); // Top-level
1646  IFAbbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 1)); // Module map
1647  IFAbbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 16)); // Name as req. len
1648  IFAbbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob)); // Name as req. + name
1649  unsigned IFAbbrevCode = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(IFAbbrev));
1650 
1651  // Create input file hash abbreviation.
1652  auto IFHAbbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
1653  IFHAbbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(INPUT_FILE_HASH));
1654  IFHAbbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 32));
1655  IFHAbbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 32));
1656  unsigned IFHAbbrevCode = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(IFHAbbrev));
1657 
1658  uint64_t InputFilesOffsetBase = Stream.GetCurrentBitNo();
1659 
1660  // Get all ContentCache objects for files.
1661  std::vector<InputFileEntry> UserFiles;
1662  std::vector<InputFileEntry> SystemFiles;
1663  for (unsigned I = 1, N = SourceMgr.local_sloc_entry_size(); I != N; ++I) {
1664  // Get this source location entry.
1665  const SrcMgr::SLocEntry *SLoc = &SourceMgr.getLocalSLocEntry(I);
1666  assert(&SourceMgr.getSLocEntry(FileID::get(I)) == SLoc);
1667 
1668  // We only care about file entries that were not overridden.
1669  if (!SLoc->isFile())
1670  continue;
1671  const SrcMgr::FileInfo &File = SLoc->getFile();
1672  const SrcMgr::ContentCache *Cache = &File.getContentCache();
1673  if (!Cache->OrigEntry)
1674  continue;
1675 
1676  // Do not emit input files that do not affect current module.
1677  if (!IsSLocAffecting[I])
1678  continue;
1679 
1680  InputFileEntry Entry(*Cache->OrigEntry);
1681  Entry.IsSystemFile = isSystem(File.getFileCharacteristic());
1682  Entry.IsTransient = Cache->IsTransient;
1683  Entry.BufferOverridden = Cache->BufferOverridden;
1684  Entry.IsTopLevel = File.getIncludeLoc().isInvalid();
1685  Entry.IsModuleMap = isModuleMap(File.getFileCharacteristic());
1686 
1687  auto ContentHash = hash_code(-1);
1688  if (PP->getHeaderSearchInfo()
1689  .getHeaderSearchOpts()
1690  .ValidateASTInputFilesContent) {
1691  auto MemBuff = Cache->getBufferIfLoaded();
1692  if (MemBuff)
1693  ContentHash = hash_value(MemBuff->getBuffer());
1694  else
1695  PP->Diag(SourceLocation(), diag::err_module_unable_to_hash_content)
1696  << Entry.File.getName();
1697  }
1698  auto CH = llvm::APInt(64, ContentHash);
1699  Entry.ContentHash[0] =
1700  static_cast<uint32_t>(CH.getLoBits(32).getZExtValue());
1701  Entry.ContentHash[1] =
1702  static_cast<uint32_t>(CH.getHiBits(32).getZExtValue());
1703 
1704  if (Entry.IsSystemFile)
1705  SystemFiles.push_back(Entry);
1706  else
1707  UserFiles.push_back(Entry);
1708  }
1709 
1710  // User files go at the front, system files at the back.
1711  auto SortedFiles = llvm::concat<InputFileEntry>(std::move(UserFiles),
1712  std::move(SystemFiles));
1713 
1714  unsigned UserFilesNum = 0;
1715  // Write out all of the input files.
1716  std::vector<uint64_t> InputFileOffsets;
1717  for (const auto &Entry : SortedFiles) {
1718  uint32_t &InputFileID = InputFileIDs[Entry.File];
1719  if (InputFileID != 0)
1720  continue; // already recorded this file.
1721 
1722  // Record this entry's offset.
1723  InputFileOffsets.push_back(Stream.GetCurrentBitNo() - InputFilesOffsetBase);
1724 
1725  InputFileID = InputFileOffsets.size();
1726 
1727  if (!Entry.IsSystemFile)
1728  ++UserFilesNum;
1729 
1730  // Emit size/modification time for this file.
1731  // And whether this file was overridden.
1732  {
1733  SmallString<128> NameAsRequested = Entry.File.getNameAsRequested();
1734  SmallString<128> Name = Entry.File.getName();
1735 
1736  PreparePathForOutput(NameAsRequested);
1737  PreparePathForOutput(Name);
1738 
1739  if (Name == NameAsRequested)
1740  Name.clear();
1741 
1742  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {
1743  INPUT_FILE,
1744  InputFileOffsets.size(),
1745  (uint64_t)Entry.File.getSize(),
1746  (uint64_t)getTimestampForOutput(Entry.File),
1747  Entry.BufferOverridden,
1748  Entry.IsTransient,
1749  Entry.IsTopLevel,
1750  Entry.IsModuleMap,
1751  NameAsRequested.size()};
1752 
1753  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(IFAbbrevCode, Record,
1754  (NameAsRequested + Name).str());
1755  }
1756 
1757  // Emit content hash for this file.
1758  {
1759  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {INPUT_FILE_HASH, Entry.ContentHash[0],
1760  Entry.ContentHash[1]};
1761  Stream.EmitRecordWithAbbrev(IFHAbbrevCode, Record);
1762  }
1763  }
1764 
1765  Stream.ExitBlock();
1766 
1767  // Create input file offsets abbreviation.
1768  auto OffsetsAbbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
1769  OffsetsAbbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(INPUT_FILE_OFFSETS));
1770  OffsetsAbbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 6)); // # input files
1771  OffsetsAbbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 6)); // # non-system
1772  // input files
1773  OffsetsAbbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob)); // Array
1774  unsigned OffsetsAbbrevCode = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(OffsetsAbbrev));
1775 
1776  // Write input file offsets.
1777  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {INPUT_FILE_OFFSETS,
1778  InputFileOffsets.size(), UserFilesNum};
1779  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(OffsetsAbbrevCode, Record, bytes(InputFileOffsets));
1780 }
1781 
1782 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
1783 // Source Manager Serialization
1784 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
1785 
1786 /// Create an abbreviation for the SLocEntry that refers to a
1787 /// file.
1788 static unsigned CreateSLocFileAbbrev(llvm::BitstreamWriter &Stream) {
1789  using namespace llvm;
1790 
1791  auto Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
1792  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(SM_SLOC_FILE_ENTRY));
1793  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 8)); // Offset
1794  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 8)); // Include location
1795  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 3)); // Characteristic
1796  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 1)); // Line directives
1797  // FileEntry fields.
1798  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 6)); // Input File ID
1799  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 8)); // NumCreatedFIDs
1800  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 24)); // FirstDeclIndex
1801  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 8)); // NumDecls
1802  return Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
1803 }
1804 
1805 /// Create an abbreviation for the SLocEntry that refers to a
1806 /// buffer.
1807 static unsigned CreateSLocBufferAbbrev(llvm::BitstreamWriter &Stream) {
1808  using namespace llvm;
1809 
1810  auto Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
1811  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(SM_SLOC_BUFFER_ENTRY));
1812  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 8)); // Offset
1813  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 8)); // Include location
1814  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 3)); // Characteristic
1815  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 1)); // Line directives
1816  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob)); // Buffer name blob
1817  return Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
1818 }
1819 
1820 /// Create an abbreviation for the SLocEntry that refers to a
1821 /// buffer's blob.
1822 static unsigned CreateSLocBufferBlobAbbrev(llvm::BitstreamWriter &Stream,
1823  bool Compressed) {
1824  using namespace llvm;
1825 
1826  auto Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
1827  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(Compressed ? SM_SLOC_BUFFER_BLOB_COMPRESSED
1828  : SM_SLOC_BUFFER_BLOB));
1829  if (Compressed)
1830  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 8)); // Uncompressed size
1831  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob)); // Blob
1832  return Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
1833 }
1834 
1835 /// Create an abbreviation for the SLocEntry that refers to a macro
1836 /// expansion.
1837 static unsigned CreateSLocExpansionAbbrev(llvm::BitstreamWriter &Stream) {
1838  using namespace llvm;
1839 
1840  auto Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
1841  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(SM_SLOC_EXPANSION_ENTRY));
1842  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 8)); // Offset
1843  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 8)); // Spelling location
1844  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 6)); // Start location
1845  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 6)); // End location
1846  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 1)); // Is token range
1847  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 6)); // Token length
1848  return Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
1849 }
1850 
1851 /// Emit key length and data length as ULEB-encoded data, and return them as a
1852 /// pair.
1853 static std::pair<unsigned, unsigned>
1854 emitULEBKeyDataLength(unsigned KeyLen, unsigned DataLen, raw_ostream &Out) {
1855  llvm::encodeULEB128(KeyLen, Out);
1856  llvm::encodeULEB128(DataLen, Out);
1857  return std::make_pair(KeyLen, DataLen);
1858 }
1859 
1860 namespace {
1861 
1862  // Trait used for the on-disk hash table of header search information.
1863  class HeaderFileInfoTrait {
1864  ASTWriter &Writer;
1865 
1866  // Keep track of the framework names we've used during serialization.
1867  SmallString<128> FrameworkStringData;
1868  llvm::StringMap<unsigned> FrameworkNameOffset;
1869 
1870  public:
1871  HeaderFileInfoTrait(ASTWriter &Writer) : Writer(Writer) {}
1872 
1873  struct key_type {
1874  StringRef Filename;
1875  off_t Size;
1876  time_t ModTime;
1877  };
1878  using key_type_ref = const key_type &;
1879 
1880  using UnresolvedModule =
1881  llvm::PointerIntPair<Module *, 2, ModuleMap::ModuleHeaderRole>;
1882 
1883  struct data_type {
1884  const HeaderFileInfo &HFI;
1885  bool AlreadyIncluded;
1886  ArrayRef<ModuleMap::KnownHeader> KnownHeaders;
1887  UnresolvedModule Unresolved;
1888  };
1889  using data_type_ref = const data_type &;
1890 
1891  using hash_value_type = unsigned;
1892  using offset_type = unsigned;
1893 
1894  hash_value_type ComputeHash(key_type_ref key) {
1895  // The hash is based only on size/time of the file, so that the reader can
1896  // match even when symlinking or excess path elements ("foo/../", "../")
1897  // change the form of the name. However, complete path is still the key.
1898  return llvm::hash_combine(key.Size, key.ModTime);
1899  }
1900 
1901  std::pair<unsigned, unsigned>
1902  EmitKeyDataLength(raw_ostream& Out, key_type_ref key, data_type_ref Data) {
1903  unsigned KeyLen = key.Filename.size() + 1 + 8 + 8;
1904  unsigned DataLen = 1 + 4 + 4;
1905  for (auto ModInfo : Data.KnownHeaders)
1906  if (Writer.getLocalOrImportedSubmoduleID(ModInfo.getModule()))
1907  DataLen += 4;
1908  if (Data.Unresolved.getPointer())
1909  DataLen += 4;
1910  return emitULEBKeyDataLength(KeyLen, DataLen, Out);
1911  }
1912 
1913  void EmitKey(raw_ostream& Out, key_type_ref key, unsigned KeyLen) {
1914  using namespace llvm::support;
1915 
1916  endian::Writer LE(Out, llvm::endianness::little);
1917  LE.write<uint64_t>(key.Size);
1918  KeyLen -= 8;
1919  LE.write<uint64_t>(key.ModTime);
1920  KeyLen -= 8;
1921  Out.write(key.Filename.data(), KeyLen);
1922  }
1923 
1924  void EmitData(raw_ostream &Out, key_type_ref key,
1925  data_type_ref Data, unsigned DataLen) {
1926  using namespace llvm::support;
1927 
1928  endian::Writer LE(Out, llvm::endianness::little);
1929  uint64_t Start = Out.tell(); (void)Start;
1930 
1931  unsigned char Flags = (Data.AlreadyIncluded << 6)
1932  | (Data.HFI.isImport << 5)
1933  | (Writer.isWritingStdCXXNamedModules() ? 0 :
1934  Data.HFI.isPragmaOnce << 4)
1935  | (Data.HFI.DirInfo << 1)
1936  | Data.HFI.IndexHeaderMapHeader;
1937  LE.write<uint8_t>(Flags);
1938 
1939  if (!Data.HFI.ControllingMacro)
1940  LE.write<uint32_t>(Data.HFI.ControllingMacroID);
1941  else
1942  LE.write<uint32_t>(Writer.getIdentifierRef(Data.HFI.ControllingMacro));
1943 
1944  unsigned Offset = 0;
1945  if (!Data.HFI.Framework.empty()) {
1946  // If this header refers into a framework, save the framework name.
1947  llvm::StringMap<unsigned>::iterator Pos
1948  = FrameworkNameOffset.find(Data.HFI.Framework);
1949  if (Pos == FrameworkNameOffset.end()) {
1950  Offset = FrameworkStringData.size() + 1;
1951  FrameworkStringData.append(Data.HFI.Framework);
1952  FrameworkStringData.push_back(0);
1953 
1954  FrameworkNameOffset[Data.HFI.Framework] = Offset;
1955  } else
1956  Offset = Pos->second;
1957  }
1958  LE.write<uint32_t>(Offset);
1959 
1960  auto EmitModule = [&](Module *M, ModuleMap::ModuleHeaderRole Role) {
1961  if (uint32_t ModID = Writer.getLocalOrImportedSubmoduleID(M)) {
1962  uint32_t Value = (ModID << 3) | (unsigned)Role;
1963  assert((Value >> 3) == ModID && "overflow in header module info");
1964  LE.write<uint32_t>(Value);
1965  }
1966  };
1967 
1968  for (auto ModInfo : Data.KnownHeaders)
1969  EmitModule(ModInfo.getModule(), ModInfo.getRole());
1970  if (Data.Unresolved.getPointer())
1971  EmitModule(Data.Unresolved.getPointer(), Data.Unresolved.getInt());
1972 
1973  assert(Out.tell() - Start == DataLen && "Wrong data length");
1974  }
1975 
1976  const char *strings_begin() const { return FrameworkStringData.begin(); }
1977  const char *strings_end() const { return FrameworkStringData.end(); }
1978  };
1979 
1980 } // namespace
1981 
1982 /// Write the header search block for the list of files that
1983 ///
1984 /// \param HS The header search structure to save.
1985 void ASTWriter::WriteHeaderSearch(const HeaderSearch &HS) {
1986  HeaderFileInfoTrait GeneratorTrait(*this);
1987  llvm::OnDiskChainedHashTableGenerator<HeaderFileInfoTrait> Generator;
1988  SmallVector<const char *, 4> SavedStrings;
1989  unsigned NumHeaderSearchEntries = 0;
1990 
1991  // Find all unresolved headers for the current module. We generally will
1992  // have resolved them before we get here, but not necessarily: we might be
1993  // compiling a preprocessed module, where there is no requirement for the
1994  // original files to exist any more.
1995  const HeaderFileInfo Empty; // So we can take a reference.
1996  if (WritingModule) {
1997  llvm::SmallVector<Module *, 16> Worklist(1, WritingModule);
1998  while (!Worklist.empty()) {
1999  Module *M = Worklist.pop_back_val();
2000  // We don't care about headers in unimportable submodules.
2001  if (M->isUnimportable())
2002  continue;
2003 
2004  // Map to disk files where possible, to pick up any missing stat
2005  // information. This also means we don't need to check the unresolved
2006  // headers list when emitting resolved headers in the first loop below.
2007  // FIXME: It'd be preferable to avoid doing this if we were given
2008  // sufficient stat information in the module map.
2009  HS.getModuleMap().resolveHeaderDirectives(M, /*File=*/std::nullopt);
2010 
2011  // If the file didn't exist, we can still create a module if we were given
2012  // enough information in the module map.
2013  for (const auto &U : M->MissingHeaders) {
2014  // Check that we were given enough information to build a module
2015  // without this file existing on disk.
2016  if (!U.Size || (!U.ModTime && IncludeTimestamps)) {
2017  PP->Diag(U.FileNameLoc, diag::err_module_no_size_mtime_for_header)
2018  << WritingModule->getFullModuleName() << U.Size.has_value()
2019  << U.FileName;
2020  continue;
2021  }
2022 
2023  // Form the effective relative pathname for the file.
2024  SmallString<128> Filename(M->Directory->getName());
2025  llvm::sys::path::append(Filename, U.FileName);
2026  PreparePathForOutput(Filename);
2027 
2028  StringRef FilenameDup = strdup(Filename.c_str());
2029  SavedStrings.push_back(FilenameDup.data());
2030 
2031  HeaderFileInfoTrait::key_type Key = {
2032  FilenameDup, *U.Size, IncludeTimestamps ? *U.ModTime : 0};
2033  HeaderFileInfoTrait::data_type Data = {
2034  Empty, false, {}, {M, ModuleMap::headerKindToRole(U.Kind)}};
2035  // FIXME: Deal with cases where there are multiple unresolved header
2036  // directives in different submodules for the same header.
2037  Generator.insert(Key, Data, GeneratorTrait);
2038  ++NumHeaderSearchEntries;
2039  }
2040  auto SubmodulesRange = M->submodules();
2041  Worklist.append(SubmodulesRange.begin(), SubmodulesRange.end());
2042  }
2043  }
2044 
2045  SmallVector<OptionalFileEntryRef, 16> FilesByUID;
2046  HS.getFileMgr().GetUniqueIDMapping(FilesByUID);
2047 
2048  if (FilesByUID.size() > HS.header_file_size())
2049  FilesByUID.resize(HS.header_file_size());
2050 
2051  for (unsigned UID = 0, LastUID = FilesByUID.size(); UID != LastUID; ++UID) {
2052  OptionalFileEntryRef File = FilesByUID[UID];
2053  if (!File)
2054  continue;
2055 
2056  // Get the file info. Skip emitting this file if we have no information on
2057  // it as a header file (in which case HFI will be null) or if it hasn't
2058  // changed since it was loaded. Also skip it if it's for a modular header
2059  // from a different module; in that case, we rely on the module(s)
2060  // containing the header to provide this information.
2061  const HeaderFileInfo *HFI = HS.getExistingLocalFileInfo(*File);
2062  if (!HFI || (HFI->isModuleHeader && !HFI->isCompilingModuleHeader))
2063  continue;
2064 
2065  // Massage the file path into an appropriate form.
2066  StringRef Filename = File->getName();
2067  SmallString<128> FilenameTmp(Filename);
2068  if (PreparePathForOutput(FilenameTmp)) {
2069  // If we performed any translation on the file name at all, we need to
2070  // save this string, since the generator will refer to it later.
2071  Filename = StringRef(strdup(FilenameTmp.c_str()));
2072  SavedStrings.push_back(Filename.data());
2073  }
2074 
2075  bool Included = PP->alreadyIncluded(*File);
2076 
2077  HeaderFileInfoTrait::key_type Key = {
2078  Filename, File->getSize(), getTimestampForOutput(*File)
2079  };
2080  HeaderFileInfoTrait::data_type Data = {
2081  *HFI, Included, HS.getModuleMap().findResolvedModulesForHeader(*File), {}
2082  };
2083  Generator.insert(Key, Data, GeneratorTrait);
2084  ++NumHeaderSearchEntries;
2085  }
2086 
2087  // Create the on-disk hash table in a buffer.
2088  SmallString<4096> TableData;
2089  uint32_t BucketOffset;
2090  {
2091  using namespace llvm::support;
2092 
2093  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(TableData);
2094  // Make sure that no bucket is at offset 0
2095  endian::write<uint32_t>(Out, 0, llvm::endianness::little);
2096  BucketOffset = Generator.Emit(Out, GeneratorTrait);
2097  }
2098 
2099  // Create a blob abbreviation
2100  using namespace llvm;
2101 
2102  auto Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
2103  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(HEADER_SEARCH_TABLE));
2104  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 32));
2105  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 32));
2106  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 32));
2107  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob));
2108  unsigned TableAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
2109 
2110  // Write the header search table
2111  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {HEADER_SEARCH_TABLE, BucketOffset,
2112  NumHeaderSearchEntries, TableData.size()};
2113  TableData.append(GeneratorTrait.strings_begin(),GeneratorTrait.strings_end());
2114  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(TableAbbrev, Record, TableData);
2115 
2116  // Free all of the strings we had to duplicate.
2117  for (unsigned I = 0, N = SavedStrings.size(); I != N; ++I)
2118  free(const_cast<char *>(SavedStrings[I]));
2119 }
2120 
2121 static void emitBlob(llvm::BitstreamWriter &Stream, StringRef Blob,
2122  unsigned SLocBufferBlobCompressedAbbrv,
2123  unsigned SLocBufferBlobAbbrv) {
2124  using RecordDataType = ASTWriter::RecordData::value_type;
2125 
2126  // Compress the buffer if possible. We expect that almost all PCM
2127  // consumers will not want its contents.
2128  SmallVector<uint8_t, 0> CompressedBuffer;
2129  if (llvm::compression::zstd::isAvailable()) {
2130  llvm::compression::zstd::compress(
2131  llvm::arrayRefFromStringRef(Blob.drop_back(1)), CompressedBuffer, 9);
2132  RecordDataType Record[] = {SM_SLOC_BUFFER_BLOB_COMPRESSED, Blob.size() - 1};
2133  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(SLocBufferBlobCompressedAbbrv, Record,
2134  llvm::toStringRef(CompressedBuffer));
2135  return;
2136  }
2137  if (llvm::compression::zlib::isAvailable()) {
2138  llvm::compression::zlib::compress(
2139  llvm::arrayRefFromStringRef(Blob.drop_back(1)), CompressedBuffer);
2140  RecordDataType Record[] = {SM_SLOC_BUFFER_BLOB_COMPRESSED, Blob.size() - 1};
2141  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(SLocBufferBlobCompressedAbbrv, Record,
2142  llvm::toStringRef(CompressedBuffer));
2143  return;
2144  }
2145 
2146  RecordDataType Record[] = {SM_SLOC_BUFFER_BLOB};
2147  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(SLocBufferBlobAbbrv, Record, Blob);
2148 }
2149 
2150 /// Writes the block containing the serialized form of the
2151 /// source manager.
2152 ///
2153 /// TODO: We should probably use an on-disk hash table (stored in a
2154 /// blob), indexed based on the file name, so that we only create
2155 /// entries for files that we actually need. In the common case (no
2156 /// errors), we probably won't have to create file entries for any of
2157 /// the files in the AST.
2158 void ASTWriter::WriteSourceManagerBlock(SourceManager &SourceMgr,
2159  const Preprocessor &PP) {
2160  RecordData Record;
2161 
2162  // Enter the source manager block.
2163  Stream.EnterSubblock(SOURCE_MANAGER_BLOCK_ID, 4);
2164  const uint64_t SourceManagerBlockOffset = Stream.GetCurrentBitNo();
2165 
2166  // Abbreviations for the various kinds of source-location entries.
2167  unsigned SLocFileAbbrv = CreateSLocFileAbbrev(Stream);
2168  unsigned SLocBufferAbbrv = CreateSLocBufferAbbrev(Stream);
2169  unsigned SLocBufferBlobAbbrv = CreateSLocBufferBlobAbbrev(Stream, false);
2170  unsigned SLocBufferBlobCompressedAbbrv =
2171  CreateSLocBufferBlobAbbrev(Stream, true);
2172  unsigned SLocExpansionAbbrv = CreateSLocExpansionAbbrev(Stream);
2173 
2174  // Write out the source location entry table. We skip the first
2175  // entry, which is always the same dummy entry.
2176  std::vector<uint32_t> SLocEntryOffsets;
2177  uint64_t SLocEntryOffsetsBase = Stream.GetCurrentBitNo();
2178  SLocEntryOffsets.reserve(SourceMgr.local_sloc_entry_size() - 1);
2179  for (unsigned I = 1, N = SourceMgr.local_sloc_entry_size();
2180  I != N; ++I) {
2181  // Get this source location entry.
2182  const SrcMgr::SLocEntry *SLoc = &SourceMgr.getLocalSLocEntry(I);
2183  FileID FID = FileID::get(I);
2184  assert(&SourceMgr.getSLocEntry(FID) == SLoc);
2185 
2186  // Record the offset of this source-location entry.
2187  uint64_t Offset = Stream.GetCurrentBitNo() - SLocEntryOffsetsBase;
2188  assert((Offset >> 32) == 0 && "SLocEntry offset too large");
2189 
2190  // Figure out which record code to use.
2191  unsigned Code;
2192  if (SLoc->isFile()) {
2193  const SrcMgr::ContentCache *Cache = &SLoc->getFile().getContentCache();
2194  if (Cache->OrigEntry) {
2195  Code = SM_SLOC_FILE_ENTRY;
2196  } else
2197  Code = SM_SLOC_BUFFER_ENTRY;
2198  } else
2199  Code = SM_SLOC_EXPANSION_ENTRY;
2200  Record.clear();
2201  Record.push_back(Code);
2202 
2203  if (SLoc->isFile()) {
2204  const SrcMgr::FileInfo &File = SLoc->getFile();
2205  const SrcMgr::ContentCache *Content = &File.getContentCache();
2206  // Do not emit files that were not listed as inputs.
2207  if (!IsSLocAffecting[I])
2208  continue;
2209  SLocEntryOffsets.push_back(Offset);
2210  // Starting offset of this entry within this module, so skip the dummy.
2211  Record.push_back(getAdjustedOffset(SLoc->getOffset()) - 2);
2212  AddSourceLocation(File.getIncludeLoc(), Record);
2213  Record.push_back(File.getFileCharacteristic()); // FIXME: stable encoding
2214  Record.push_back(File.hasLineDirectives());
2215 
2216  bool EmitBlob = false;
2217  if (Content->OrigEntry) {
2218  assert(Content->OrigEntry == Content->ContentsEntry &&
2219  "Writing to AST an overridden file is not supported");
2220 
2221  // The source location entry is a file. Emit input file ID.
2222  assert(InputFileIDs[*Content->OrigEntry] != 0 && "Missed file entry");
2223  Record.push_back(InputFileIDs[*Content->OrigEntry]);
2224 
2225  Record.push_back(getAdjustedNumCreatedFIDs(FID));
2226 
2227  FileDeclIDsTy::iterator FDI = FileDeclIDs.find(FID);
2228  if (FDI != FileDeclIDs.end()) {
2229  Record.push_back(FDI->second->FirstDeclIndex);
2230  Record.push_back(FDI->second->DeclIDs.size());
2231  } else {
2232  Record.push_back(0);
2233  Record.push_back(0);
2234  }
2235 
2236  Stream.EmitRecordWithAbbrev(SLocFileAbbrv, Record);
2237 
2238  if (Content->BufferOverridden || Content->IsTransient)
2239  EmitBlob = true;
2240  } else {
2241  // The source location entry is a buffer. The blob associated
2242  // with this entry contains the contents of the buffer.
2243 
2244  // We add one to the size so that we capture the trailing NULL
2245  // that is required by llvm::MemoryBuffer::getMemBuffer (on
2246  // the reader side).
2247  std::optional<llvm::MemoryBufferRef> Buffer =
2248  Content->getBufferOrNone(PP.getDiagnostics(), PP.getFileManager());
2249  StringRef Name = Buffer ? Buffer->getBufferIdentifier() : "";
2250  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(SLocBufferAbbrv, Record,
2251  StringRef(Name.data(), Name.size() + 1));
2252  EmitBlob = true;
2253  }
2254 
2255  if (EmitBlob) {
2256  // Include the implicit terminating null character in the on-disk buffer
2257  // if we're writing it uncompressed.
2258  std::optional<llvm::MemoryBufferRef> Buffer =
2259  Content->getBufferOrNone(PP.getDiagnostics(), PP.getFileManager());
2260  if (!Buffer)
2261  Buffer = llvm::MemoryBufferRef("<<<INVALID BUFFER>>>", "");
2262  StringRef Blob(Buffer->getBufferStart(), Buffer->getBufferSize() + 1);
2263  emitBlob(Stream, Blob, SLocBufferBlobCompressedAbbrv,
2264  SLocBufferBlobAbbrv);
2265  }
2266  } else {
2267  // The source location entry is a macro expansion.
2268  const SrcMgr::ExpansionInfo &Expansion = SLoc->getExpansion();
2269  SLocEntryOffsets.push_back(Offset);
2270  // Starting offset of this entry within this module, so skip the dummy.
2271  Record.push_back(getAdjustedOffset(SLoc->getOffset()) - 2);
2272  LocSeq::State Seq;
2273  AddSourceLocation(Expansion.getSpellingLoc(), Record, Seq);
2274  AddSourceLocation(Expansion.getExpansionLocStart(), Record, Seq);
2275  AddSourceLocation(Expansion.isMacroArgExpansion()
2276  ? SourceLocation()
2277  : Expansion.getExpansionLocEnd(),
2278  Record, Seq);
2279  Record.push_back(Expansion.isExpansionTokenRange());
2280 
2281  // Compute the token length for this macro expansion.
2282  SourceLocation::UIntTy NextOffset = SourceMgr.getNextLocalOffset();
2283  if (I + 1 != N)
2284  NextOffset = SourceMgr.getLocalSLocEntry(I + 1).getOffset();
2285  Record.push_back(getAdjustedOffset(NextOffset - SLoc->getOffset()) - 1);
2286  Stream.EmitRecordWithAbbrev(SLocExpansionAbbrv, Record);
2287  }
2288  }
2289 
2290  Stream.ExitBlock();
2291 
2292  if (SLocEntryOffsets.empty())
2293  return;
2294 
2295  // Write the source-location offsets table into the AST block. This
2296  // table is used for lazily loading source-location information.
2297  using namespace llvm;
2298 
2299  auto Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
2300  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(SOURCE_LOCATION_OFFSETS));
2301  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 16)); // # of slocs
2302  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 16)); // total size
2303  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 32)); // base offset
2304  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob)); // offsets
2305  unsigned SLocOffsetsAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
2306  {
2307  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {
2308  SOURCE_LOCATION_OFFSETS, SLocEntryOffsets.size(),
2309  getAdjustedOffset(SourceMgr.getNextLocalOffset()) - 1 /* skip dummy */,
2310  SLocEntryOffsetsBase - SourceManagerBlockOffset};
2311  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(SLocOffsetsAbbrev, Record,
2312  bytes(SLocEntryOffsets));
2313  }
2314 
2315  // Write the line table. It depends on remapping working, so it must come
2316  // after the source location offsets.
2317  if (SourceMgr.hasLineTable()) {
2318  LineTableInfo &LineTable = SourceMgr.getLineTable();
2319 
2320  Record.clear();
2321 
2322  // Emit the needed file names.
2323  llvm::DenseMap<int, int> FilenameMap;
2324  FilenameMap[-1] = -1; // For unspecified filenames.
2325  for (const auto &L : LineTable) {
2326  if (L.first.ID < 0)
2327  continue;
2328  for (auto &LE : L.second) {
2329  if (FilenameMap.insert(std::make_pair(LE.FilenameID,
2330  FilenameMap.size() - 1)).second)
2331  AddPath(LineTable.getFilename(LE.FilenameID), Record);
2332  }
2333  }
2334  Record.push_back(0);
2335 
2336  // Emit the line entries
2337  for (const auto &L : LineTable) {
2338  // Only emit entries for local files.
2339  if (L.first.ID < 0)
2340  continue;
2341 
2342  AddFileID(L.first, Record);
2343 
2344  // Emit the line entries
2345  Record.push_back(L.second.size());
2346  for (const auto &LE : L.second) {
2347  Record.push_back(LE.FileOffset);
2348  Record.push_back(LE.LineNo);
2349  Record.push_back(FilenameMap[LE.FilenameID]);
2350  Record.push_back((unsigned)LE.FileKind);
2351  Record.push_back(LE.IncludeOffset);
2352  }
2353  }
2354 
2355  Stream.EmitRecord(SOURCE_MANAGER_LINE_TABLE, Record);
2356  }
2357 }
2358 
2359 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
2360 // Preprocessor Serialization
2361 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
2362 
2363 static bool shouldIgnoreMacro(MacroDirective *MD, bool IsModule,
2364  const Preprocessor &PP) {
2365  if (MacroInfo *MI = MD->getMacroInfo())
2366  if (MI->isBuiltinMacro())
2367  return true;
2368 
2369  if (IsModule) {
2370  SourceLocation Loc = MD->getLocation();
2371  if (Loc.isInvalid())
2372  return true;
2373  if (PP.getSourceManager().getFileID(Loc) == PP.getPredefinesFileID())
2374  return true;
2375  }
2376 
2377  return false;
2378 }
2379 
2380 /// Writes the block containing the serialized form of the
2381 /// preprocessor.
2382 void ASTWriter::WritePreprocessor(const Preprocessor &PP, bool IsModule) {
2383  uint64_t MacroOffsetsBase = Stream.GetCurrentBitNo();
2384 
2385  PreprocessingRecord *PPRec = PP.getPreprocessingRecord();
2386  if (PPRec)
2387  WritePreprocessorDetail(*PPRec, MacroOffsetsBase);
2388 
2389  RecordData Record;
2390  RecordData ModuleMacroRecord;
2391 
2392  // If the preprocessor __COUNTER__ value has been bumped, remember it.
2393  if (PP.getCounterValue() != 0) {
2394  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {PP.getCounterValue()};
2395  Stream.EmitRecord(PP_COUNTER_VALUE, Record);
2396  }
2397 
2398  // If we have a recorded #pragma assume_nonnull, remember it so it can be
2399  // replayed when the preamble terminates into the main file.
2400  SourceLocation AssumeNonNullLoc =
2401  PP.getPreambleRecordedPragmaAssumeNonNullLoc();
2402  if (AssumeNonNullLoc.isValid()) {
2403  assert(PP.isRecordingPreamble());
2404  AddSourceLocation(AssumeNonNullLoc, Record);
2405  Stream.EmitRecord(PP_ASSUME_NONNULL_LOC, Record);
2406  Record.clear();
2407  }
2408 
2409  if (PP.isRecordingPreamble() && PP.hasRecordedPreamble()) {
2410  assert(!IsModule);
2411  auto SkipInfo = PP.getPreambleSkipInfo();
2412  if (SkipInfo) {
2413  Record.push_back(true);
2414  AddSourceLocation(SkipInfo->HashTokenLoc, Record);
2415  AddSourceLocation(SkipInfo->IfTokenLoc, Record);
2416  Record.push_back(SkipInfo->FoundNonSkipPortion);
2417  Record.push_back(SkipInfo->FoundElse);
2418  AddSourceLocation(SkipInfo->ElseLoc, Record);
2419  } else {
2420  Record.push_back(false);
2421  }
2422  for (const auto &Cond : PP.getPreambleConditionalStack()) {
2423  AddSourceLocation(Cond.IfLoc, Record);
2424  Record.push_back(Cond.WasSkipping);
2425  Record.push_back(Cond.FoundNonSkip);
2426  Record.push_back(Cond.FoundElse);
2427  }
2428  Stream.EmitRecord(PP_CONDITIONAL_STACK, Record);
2429  Record.clear();
2430  }
2431 
2432  // Enter the preprocessor block.
2433  Stream.EnterSubblock(PREPROCESSOR_BLOCK_ID, 3);
2434 
2435  // If the AST file contains __DATE__ or __TIME__ emit a warning about this.
2436  // FIXME: Include a location for the use, and say which one was used.
2437  if (PP.SawDateOrTime())
2438  PP.Diag(SourceLocation(), diag::warn_module_uses_date_time) << IsModule;
2439 
2440  // Loop over all the macro directives that are live at the end of the file,
2441  // emitting each to the PP section.
2442 
2443  // Construct the list of identifiers with macro directives that need to be
2444  // serialized.
2445  SmallVector<const IdentifierInfo *, 128> MacroIdentifiers;
2446  // It is meaningless to emit macros for named modules. It only wastes times
2447  // and spaces.
2448  if (!isWritingStdCXXNamedModules())
2449  for (auto &Id : PP.getIdentifierTable())
2450  if (Id.second->hadMacroDefinition() &&
2451  (!Id.second->isFromAST() ||
2452  Id.second->hasChangedSinceDeserialization()))
2453  MacroIdentifiers.push_back(Id.second);
2454  // Sort the set of macro definitions that need to be serialized by the
2455  // name of the macro, to provide a stable ordering.
2456  llvm::sort(MacroIdentifiers, llvm::deref<std::less<>>());
2457 
2458  // Emit the macro directives as a list and associate the offset with the
2459  // identifier they belong to.
2460  for (const IdentifierInfo *Name : MacroIdentifiers) {
2461  MacroDirective *MD = PP.getLocalMacroDirectiveHistory(Name);
2462  uint64_t StartOffset = Stream.GetCurrentBitNo() - MacroOffsetsBase;
2463  assert((StartOffset >> 32) == 0 && "Macro identifiers offset too large");
2464 
2465  // Write out any exported module macros.
2466  bool EmittedModuleMacros = false;
2467  // C+=20 Header Units are compiled module interfaces, but they preserve
2468  // macros that are live (i.e. have a defined value) at the end of the
2469  // compilation. So when writing a header unit, we preserve only the final
2470  // value of each macro (and discard any that are undefined). Header units
2471  // do not have sub-modules (although they might import other header units).
2472  // PCH files, conversely, retain the history of each macro's define/undef
2473  // and of leaf macros in sub modules.
2474  if (IsModule && WritingModule->isHeaderUnit()) {
2475  // This is for the main TU when it is a C++20 header unit.
2476  // We preserve the final state of defined macros, and we do not emit ones
2477  // that are undefined.
2478  if (!MD || shouldIgnoreMacro(MD, IsModule, PP) ||
2479  MD->getKind() == MacroDirective::MD_Undefine)
2480  continue;
2481  AddSourceLocation(MD->getLocation(), Record);
2482  Record.push_back(MD->getKind());
2483  if (auto *DefMD = dyn_cast<DefMacroDirective>(MD)) {
2484  Record.push_back(getMacroRef(DefMD->getInfo(), Name));
2485  } else if (auto *VisMD = dyn_cast<VisibilityMacroDirective>(MD)) {
2486  Record.push_back(VisMD->isPublic());
2487  }
2488  ModuleMacroRecord.push_back(getSubmoduleID(WritingModule));
2489  ModuleMacroRecord.push_back(getMacroRef(MD->getMacroInfo(), Name));
2490  Stream.EmitRecord(PP_MODULE_MACRO, ModuleMacroRecord);
2491  ModuleMacroRecord.clear();
2492  EmittedModuleMacros = true;
2493  } else {
2494  // Emit the macro directives in reverse source order.
2495  for (; MD; MD = MD->getPrevious()) {
2496  // Once we hit an ignored macro, we're done: the rest of the chain
2497  // will all be ignored macros.
2498  if (shouldIgnoreMacro(MD, IsModule, PP))
2499  break;
2500  AddSourceLocation(MD->getLocation(), Record);
2501  Record.push_back(MD->getKind());
2502  if (auto *DefMD = dyn_cast<DefMacroDirective>(MD)) {
2503  Record.push_back(getMacroRef(DefMD->getInfo(), Name));
2504  } else if (auto *VisMD = dyn_cast<VisibilityMacroDirective>(MD)) {
2505  Record.push_back(VisMD->isPublic());
2506  }
2507  }
2508 
2509  // We write out exported module macros for PCH as well.
2510  auto Leafs = PP.getLeafModuleMacros(Name);
2511  SmallVector<ModuleMacro *, 8> Worklist(Leafs.begin(), Leafs.end());
2512  llvm::DenseMap<ModuleMacro *, unsigned> Visits;
2513  while (!Worklist.empty()) {
2514  auto *Macro = Worklist.pop_back_val();
2515 
2516  // Emit a record indicating this submodule exports this macro.
2517  ModuleMacroRecord.push_back(getSubmoduleID(Macro->getOwningModule()));
2518  ModuleMacroRecord.push_back(getMacroRef(Macro->getMacroInfo(), Name));
2519  for (auto *M : Macro->overrides())
2520  ModuleMacroRecord.push_back(getSubmoduleID(M->getOwningModule()));
2521 
2522  Stream.EmitRecord(PP_MODULE_MACRO, ModuleMacroRecord);
2523  ModuleMacroRecord.clear();
2524 
2525  // Enqueue overridden macros once we've visited all their ancestors.
2526  for (auto *M : Macro->overrides())
2527  if (++Visits[M] == M->getNumOverridingMacros())
2528  Worklist.push_back(M);
2529 
2530  EmittedModuleMacros = true;
2531  }
2532  }
2533  if (Record.empty() && !EmittedModuleMacros)
2534  continue;
2535 
2536  IdentMacroDirectivesOffsetMap[Name] = StartOffset;
2537  Stream.EmitRecord(PP_MACRO_DIRECTIVE_HISTORY, Record);
2538  Record.clear();
2539  }
2540 
2541  /// Offsets of each of the macros into the bitstream, indexed by
2542  /// the local macro ID
2543  ///
2544  /// For each identifier that is associated with a macro, this map
2545  /// provides the offset into the bitstream where that macro is
2546  /// defined.
2547  std::vector<uint32_t> MacroOffsets;
2548 
2549  for (unsigned I = 0, N = MacroInfosToEmit.size(); I != N; ++I) {
2550  const IdentifierInfo *Name = MacroInfosToEmit[I].Name;
2551  MacroInfo *MI = MacroInfosToEmit[I].MI;
2552  MacroID ID = MacroInfosToEmit[I].ID;
2553 
2554  if (ID < FirstMacroID) {
2555  assert(0 && "Loaded MacroInfo entered MacroInfosToEmit ?");
2556  continue;
2557  }
2558 
2559  // Record the local offset of this macro.
2560  unsigned Index = ID - FirstMacroID;
2561  if (Index >= MacroOffsets.size())
2562  MacroOffsets.resize(Index + 1);
2563 
2564  uint64_t Offset = Stream.GetCurrentBitNo() - MacroOffsetsBase;
2565  assert((Offset >> 32) == 0 && "Macro offset too large");
2566  MacroOffsets[Index] = Offset;
2567 
2568  AddIdentifierRef(Name, Record);
2569  AddSourceLocation(MI->getDefinitionLoc(), Record);
2570  AddSourceLocation(MI->getDefinitionEndLoc(), Record);
2571  Record.push_back(MI->isUsed());
2572  Record.push_back(MI->isUsedForHeaderGuard());
2573  Record.push_back(MI->getNumTokens());
2574  unsigned Code;
2575  if (MI->isObjectLike()) {
2576  Code = PP_MACRO_OBJECT_LIKE;
2577  } else {
2578  Code = PP_MACRO_FUNCTION_LIKE;
2579 
2580  Record.push_back(MI->isC99Varargs());
2581  Record.push_back(MI->isGNUVarargs());
2582  Record.push_back(MI->hasCommaPasting());
2583  Record.push_back(MI->getNumParams());
2584  for (const IdentifierInfo *Param : MI->params())
2585  AddIdentifierRef(Param, Record);
2586  }
2587 
2588  // If we have a detailed preprocessing record, record the macro definition
2589  // ID that corresponds to this macro.
2590  if (PPRec)
2591  Record.push_back(MacroDefinitions[PPRec->findMacroDefinition(MI)]);
2592 
2593  Stream.EmitRecord(Code, Record);
2594  Record.clear();
2595 
2596  // Emit the tokens array.
2597  for (unsigned TokNo = 0, e = MI->getNumTokens(); TokNo != e; ++TokNo) {
2598  // Note that we know that the preprocessor does not have any annotation
2599  // tokens in it because they are created by the parser, and thus can't
2600  // be in a macro definition.
2601  const Token &Tok = MI->getReplacementToken(TokNo);
2602  AddToken(Tok, Record);
2603  Stream.EmitRecord(PP_TOKEN, Record);
2604  Record.clear();
2605  }
2606  ++NumMacros;
2607  }
2608 
2609  Stream.ExitBlock();
2610 
2611  // Write the offsets table for macro IDs.
2612  using namespace llvm;
2613 
2614  auto Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
2615  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(MACRO_OFFSET));
2616  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 32)); // # of macros
2617  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 32)); // first ID
2618  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 32)); // base offset
2619  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob));
2620 
2621  unsigned MacroOffsetAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
2622  {
2623  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {MACRO_OFFSET, MacroOffsets.size(),
2624  FirstMacroID - NUM_PREDEF_MACRO_IDS,
2625  MacroOffsetsBase - ASTBlockStartOffset};
2626  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(MacroOffsetAbbrev, Record, bytes(MacroOffsets));
2627  }
2628 }
2629 
2630 void ASTWriter::WritePreprocessorDetail(PreprocessingRecord &PPRec,
2631  uint64_t MacroOffsetsBase) {
2632  if (PPRec.local_begin() == PPRec.local_end())
2633  return;
2634 
2635  SmallVector<PPEntityOffset, 64> PreprocessedEntityOffsets;
2636 
2637  // Enter the preprocessor block.
2638  Stream.EnterSubblock(PREPROCESSOR_DETAIL_BLOCK_ID, 3);
2639 
2640  // If the preprocessor has a preprocessing record, emit it.
2641  unsigned NumPreprocessingRecords = 0;
2642  using namespace llvm;
2643 
2644  // Set up the abbreviation for
2645  unsigned InclusionAbbrev = 0;
2646  {
2647  auto Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
2648  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(PPD_INCLUSION_DIRECTIVE));
2649  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 32)); // filename length
2650  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 1)); // in quotes
2651  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 2)); // kind
2652  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 1)); // imported module
2653  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob));
2654  InclusionAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
2655  }
2656 
2657  unsigned FirstPreprocessorEntityID
2658  = (Chain ? PPRec.getNumLoadedPreprocessedEntities() : 0)
2659  + NUM_PREDEF_PP_ENTITY_IDS;
2660  unsigned NextPreprocessorEntityID = FirstPreprocessorEntityID;
2661  RecordData Record;
2662  for (PreprocessingRecord::iterator E = PPRec.local_begin(),
2663  EEnd = PPRec.local_end();
2664  E != EEnd;
2665  (void)++E, ++NumPreprocessingRecords, ++NextPreprocessorEntityID) {
2666  Record.clear();
2667 
2668  uint64_t Offset = Stream.GetCurrentBitNo() - MacroOffsetsBase;
2669  assert((Offset >> 32) == 0 && "Preprocessed entity offset too large");
2670  PreprocessedEntityOffsets.push_back(
2671  PPEntityOffset(getAdjustedRange((*E)->getSourceRange()), Offset));
2672 
2673  if (auto *MD = dyn_cast<MacroDefinitionRecord>(*E)) {
2674  // Record this macro definition's ID.
2675  MacroDefinitions[MD] = NextPreprocessorEntityID;
2676 
2677  AddIdentifierRef(MD->getName(), Record);
2678  Stream.EmitRecord(PPD_MACRO_DEFINITION, Record);
2679  continue;
2680  }
2681 
2682  if (auto *ME = dyn_cast<MacroExpansion>(*E)) {
2683  Record.push_back(ME->isBuiltinMacro());
2684  if (ME->isBuiltinMacro())
2685  AddIdentifierRef(ME->getName(), Record);
2686  else
2687  Record.push_back(MacroDefinitions[ME->getDefinition()]);
2688  Stream.EmitRecord(PPD_MACRO_EXPANSION, Record);
2689  continue;
2690  }
2691 
2692  if (auto *ID = dyn_cast<InclusionDirective>(*E)) {
2693  Record.push_back(PPD_INCLUSION_DIRECTIVE);
2694  Record.push_back(ID->getFileName().size());
2695  Record.push_back(ID->wasInQuotes());
2696  Record.push_back(static_cast<unsigned>(ID->getKind()));
2697  Record.push_back(ID->importedModule());
2698  SmallString<64> Buffer;
2699  Buffer += ID->getFileName();
2700  // Check that the FileEntry is not null because it was not resolved and
2701  // we create a PCH even with compiler errors.
2702  if (ID->getFile())
2703  Buffer += ID->getFile()->getName();
2704  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(InclusionAbbrev, Record, Buffer);
2705  continue;
2706  }
2707 
2708  llvm_unreachable("Unhandled PreprocessedEntity in ASTWriter");
2709  }
2710  Stream.ExitBlock();
2711 
2712  // Write the offsets table for the preprocessing record.
2713  if (NumPreprocessingRecords > 0) {
2714  assert(PreprocessedEntityOffsets.size() == NumPreprocessingRecords);
2715 
2716  // Write the offsets table for identifier IDs.
2717  using namespace llvm;
2718 
2719  auto Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
2720  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(PPD_ENTITIES_OFFSETS));
2721  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 32)); // first pp entity
2722  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob));
2723  unsigned PPEOffsetAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
2724 
2725  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {PPD_ENTITIES_OFFSETS,
2726  FirstPreprocessorEntityID -
2727  NUM_PREDEF_PP_ENTITY_IDS};
2728  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(PPEOffsetAbbrev, Record,
2729  bytes(PreprocessedEntityOffsets));
2730  }
2731 
2732  // Write the skipped region table for the preprocessing record.
2733  ArrayRef<SourceRange> SkippedRanges = PPRec.getSkippedRanges();
2734  if (SkippedRanges.size() > 0) {
2735  std::vector<PPSkippedRange> SerializedSkippedRanges;
2736  SerializedSkippedRanges.reserve(SkippedRanges.size());
2737  for (auto const& Range : SkippedRanges)
2738  SerializedSkippedRanges.emplace_back(Range);
2739 
2740  using namespace llvm;
2741  auto Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
2742  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(PPD_SKIPPED_RANGES));
2743  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob));
