2744  unsigned PPESkippedRangeAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
2745 
2746  Record.clear();
2747  Record.push_back(PPD_SKIPPED_RANGES);
2748  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(PPESkippedRangeAbbrev, Record,
2749  bytes(SerializedSkippedRanges));
2750  }
2751 }
2752 
2753 unsigned ASTWriter::getLocalOrImportedSubmoduleID(const Module *Mod) {
2754  if (!Mod)
2755  return 0;
2756 
2757  auto Known = SubmoduleIDs.find(Mod);
2758  if (Known != SubmoduleIDs.end())
2759  return Known->second;
2760 
2761  auto *Top = Mod->getTopLevelModule();
2762  if (Top != WritingModule &&
2763  (getLangOpts().CompilingPCH ||
2764  !Top->fullModuleNameIs(StringRef(getLangOpts().CurrentModule))))
2765  return 0;
2766 
2767  return SubmoduleIDs[Mod] = NextSubmoduleID++;
2768 }
2769 
2770 unsigned ASTWriter::getSubmoduleID(Module *Mod) {
2771  unsigned ID = getLocalOrImportedSubmoduleID(Mod);
2772  // FIXME: This can easily happen, if we have a reference to a submodule that
2773  // did not result in us loading a module file for that submodule. For
2774  // instance, a cross-top-level-module 'conflict' declaration will hit this.
2775  // assert((ID || !Mod) &&
2776  // "asked for module ID for non-local, non-imported module");
2777  return ID;
2778 }
2779 
2780 /// Compute the number of modules within the given tree (including the
2781 /// given module).
2782 static unsigned getNumberOfModules(Module *Mod) {
2783  unsigned ChildModules = 0;
2784  for (auto *Submodule : Mod->submodules())
2785  ChildModules += getNumberOfModules(Submodule);
2786 
2787  return ChildModules + 1;
2788 }
2789 
2790 void ASTWriter::WriteSubmodules(Module *WritingModule) {
2791  // Enter the submodule description block.
2792  Stream.EnterSubblock(SUBMODULE_BLOCK_ID, /*bits for abbreviations*/5);
2793 
2794  // Write the abbreviations needed for the submodules block.
2795  using namespace llvm;
2796 
2797  auto Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
2798  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(SUBMODULE_DEFINITION));
2799  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 6)); // ID
2800  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 6)); // Parent
2801  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 4)); // Kind
2802  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 8)); // Definition location
2803  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 1)); // IsFramework
2804  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 1)); // IsExplicit
2805  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 1)); // IsSystem
2806  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 1)); // IsExternC
2807  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 1)); // InferSubmodules...
2808  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 1)); // InferExplicit...
2809  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 1)); // InferExportWild...
2810  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 1)); // ConfigMacrosExh...
2811  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 1)); // ModuleMapIsPriv...
2812  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 1)); // NamedModuleHasN...
2813  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob)); // Name
2814  unsigned DefinitionAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
2815 
2816  Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
2817  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(SUBMODULE_UMBRELLA_HEADER));
2818  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob)); // Name
2819  unsigned UmbrellaAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
2820 
2821  Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
2822  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(SUBMODULE_HEADER));
2823  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob)); // Name
2824  unsigned HeaderAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
2825 
2826  Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
2827  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(SUBMODULE_TOPHEADER));
2828  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob)); // Name
2829  unsigned TopHeaderAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
2830 
2831  Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
2832  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(SUBMODULE_UMBRELLA_DIR));
2833  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob)); // Name
2834  unsigned UmbrellaDirAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
2835 
2836  Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
2837  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(SUBMODULE_REQUIRES));
2838  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 1)); // State
2839  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob)); // Feature
2840  unsigned RequiresAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
2841 
2842  Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
2843  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(SUBMODULE_EXCLUDED_HEADER));
2844  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob)); // Name
2845  unsigned ExcludedHeaderAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
2846 
2847  Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
2848  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(SUBMODULE_TEXTUAL_HEADER));
2849  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob)); // Name
2850  unsigned TextualHeaderAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
2851 
2852  Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
2853  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(SUBMODULE_PRIVATE_HEADER));
2854  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob)); // Name
2855  unsigned PrivateHeaderAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
2856 
2857  Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
2858  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(SUBMODULE_PRIVATE_TEXTUAL_HEADER));
2859  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob)); // Name
2860  unsigned PrivateTextualHeaderAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
2861 
2862  Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
2863  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(SUBMODULE_LINK_LIBRARY));
2864  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 1)); // IsFramework
2865  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob)); // Name
2866  unsigned LinkLibraryAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
2867 
2868  Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
2869  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(SUBMODULE_CONFIG_MACRO));
2870  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob)); // Macro name
2871  unsigned ConfigMacroAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
2872 
2873  Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
2874  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(SUBMODULE_CONFLICT));
2875  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 6)); // Other module
2876  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob)); // Message
2877  unsigned ConflictAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
2878 
2879  Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
2880  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(SUBMODULE_EXPORT_AS));
2881  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob)); // Macro name
2882  unsigned ExportAsAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
2883 
2884  // Write the submodule metadata block.
2885  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {
2886  getNumberOfModules(WritingModule),
2887  FirstSubmoduleID - NUM_PREDEF_SUBMODULE_IDS};
2888  Stream.EmitRecord(SUBMODULE_METADATA, Record);
2889 
2890  // Write all of the submodules.
2891  std::queue<Module *> Q;
2892  Q.push(WritingModule);
2893  while (!Q.empty()) {
2894  Module *Mod = Q.front();
2895  Q.pop();
2896  unsigned ID = getSubmoduleID(Mod);
2897 
2898  uint64_t ParentID = 0;
2899  if (Mod->Parent) {
2900  assert(SubmoduleIDs[Mod->Parent] && "Submodule parent not written?");
2901  ParentID = SubmoduleIDs[Mod->Parent];
2902  }
2903 
2904  uint64_t DefinitionLoc =
2905  SourceLocationEncoding::encode(getAdjustedLocation(Mod->DefinitionLoc));
2906 
2907  // Emit the definition of the block.
2908  {
2909  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {SUBMODULE_DEFINITION,
2910  ID,
2911  ParentID,
2912  (RecordData::value_type)Mod->Kind,
2913  DefinitionLoc,
2914  Mod->IsFramework,
2915  Mod->IsExplicit,
2916  Mod->IsSystem,
2917  Mod->IsExternC,
2918  Mod->InferSubmodules,
2919  Mod->InferExplicitSubmodules,
2920  Mod->InferExportWildcard,
2921  Mod->ConfigMacrosExhaustive,
2922  Mod->ModuleMapIsPrivate,
2923  Mod->NamedModuleHasInit};
2924  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(DefinitionAbbrev, Record, Mod->Name);
2925  }
2926 
2927  // Emit the requirements.
2928  for (const auto &R : Mod->Requirements) {
2929  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {SUBMODULE_REQUIRES, R.second};
2930  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(RequiresAbbrev, Record, R.first);
2931  }
2932 
2933  // Emit the umbrella header, if there is one.
2934  if (std::optional<Module::Header> UmbrellaHeader =
2935  Mod->getUmbrellaHeaderAsWritten()) {
2936  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {SUBMODULE_UMBRELLA_HEADER};
2937  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(UmbrellaAbbrev, Record,
2938  UmbrellaHeader->NameAsWritten);
2939  } else if (std::optional<Module::DirectoryName> UmbrellaDir =
2940  Mod->getUmbrellaDirAsWritten()) {
2941  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {SUBMODULE_UMBRELLA_DIR};
2942  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(UmbrellaDirAbbrev, Record,
2943  UmbrellaDir->NameAsWritten);
2944  }
2945 
2946  // Emit the headers.
2947  struct {
2948  unsigned RecordKind;
2949  unsigned Abbrev;
2950  Module::HeaderKind HeaderKind;
2951  } HeaderLists[] = {
2952  {SUBMODULE_HEADER, HeaderAbbrev, Module::HK_Normal},
2953  {SUBMODULE_TEXTUAL_HEADER, TextualHeaderAbbrev, Module::HK_Textual},
2954  {SUBMODULE_PRIVATE_HEADER, PrivateHeaderAbbrev, Module::HK_Private},
2955  {SUBMODULE_PRIVATE_TEXTUAL_HEADER, PrivateTextualHeaderAbbrev,
2956  Module::HK_PrivateTextual},
2957  {SUBMODULE_EXCLUDED_HEADER, ExcludedHeaderAbbrev, Module::HK_Excluded}
2958  };
2959  for (auto &HL : HeaderLists) {
2960  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {HL.RecordKind};
2961  for (auto &H : Mod->Headers[HL.HeaderKind])
2962  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(HL.Abbrev, Record, H.NameAsWritten);
2963  }
2964 
2965  // Emit the top headers.
2966  {
2967  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {SUBMODULE_TOPHEADER};
2968  for (FileEntryRef H : Mod->getTopHeaders(PP->getFileManager())) {
2969  SmallString<128> HeaderName(H.getName());
2970  PreparePathForOutput(HeaderName);
2971  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(TopHeaderAbbrev, Record, HeaderName);
2972  }
2973  }
2974 
2975  // Emit the imports.
2976  if (!Mod->Imports.empty()) {
2977  RecordData Record;
2978  for (auto *I : Mod->Imports)
2979  Record.push_back(getSubmoduleID(I));
2980  Stream.EmitRecord(SUBMODULE_IMPORTS, Record);
2981  }
2982 
2983  // Emit the modules affecting compilation that were not imported.
2984  if (!Mod->AffectingClangModules.empty()) {
2985  RecordData Record;
2986  for (auto *I : Mod->AffectingClangModules)
2987  Record.push_back(getSubmoduleID(I));
2988  Stream.EmitRecord(SUBMODULE_AFFECTING_MODULES, Record);
2989  }
2990 
2991  // Emit the exports.
2992  if (!Mod->Exports.empty()) {
2993  RecordData Record;
2994  for (const auto &E : Mod->Exports) {
2995  // FIXME: This may fail; we don't require that all exported modules
2996  // are local or imported.
2997  Record.push_back(getSubmoduleID(E.getPointer()));
2998  Record.push_back(E.getInt());
2999  }
3000  Stream.EmitRecord(SUBMODULE_EXPORTS, Record);
3001  }
3002 
3003  //FIXME: How do we emit the 'use'd modules? They may not be submodules.
3004  // Might be unnecessary as use declarations are only used to build the
3005  // module itself.
3006 
3007  // TODO: Consider serializing undeclared uses of modules.
3008 
3009  // Emit the link libraries.
3010  for (const auto &LL : Mod->LinkLibraries) {
3011  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {SUBMODULE_LINK_LIBRARY,
3012  LL.IsFramework};
3013  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(LinkLibraryAbbrev, Record, LL.Library);
3014  }
3015 
3016  // Emit the conflicts.
3017  for (const auto &C : Mod->Conflicts) {
3018  // FIXME: This may fail; we don't require that all conflicting modules
3019  // are local or imported.
3020  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {SUBMODULE_CONFLICT,
3021  getSubmoduleID(C.Other)};
3022  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(ConflictAbbrev, Record, C.Message);
3023  }
3024 
3025  // Emit the configuration macros.
3026  for (const auto &CM : Mod->ConfigMacros) {
3027  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {SUBMODULE_CONFIG_MACRO};
3028  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(ConfigMacroAbbrev, Record, CM);
3029  }
3030 
3031  // Emit the reachable initializers.
3032  // The initializer may only be unreachable in reduced BMI.
3033  RecordData Inits;
3034  for (Decl *D : Context->getModuleInitializers(Mod))
3035  if (wasDeclEmitted(D))
3036  Inits.push_back(GetDeclRef(D));
3037  if (!Inits.empty())
3038  Stream.EmitRecord(SUBMODULE_INITIALIZERS, Inits);
3039 
3040  // Emit the name of the re-exported module, if any.
3041  if (!Mod->ExportAsModule.empty()) {
3042  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {SUBMODULE_EXPORT_AS};
3043  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(ExportAsAbbrev, Record, Mod->ExportAsModule);
3044  }
3045 
3046  // Queue up the submodules of this module.
3047  for (auto *M : Mod->submodules())
3048  Q.push(M);
3049  }
3050 
3051  Stream.ExitBlock();
3052 
3053  assert((NextSubmoduleID - FirstSubmoduleID ==
3054  getNumberOfModules(WritingModule)) &&
3055  "Wrong # of submodules; found a reference to a non-local, "
3056  "non-imported submodule?");
3057 }
3058 
3059 void ASTWriter::WritePragmaDiagnosticMappings(const DiagnosticsEngine &Diag,
3060  bool isModule) {
3061  llvm::SmallDenseMap<const DiagnosticsEngine::DiagState *, unsigned, 64>
3062  DiagStateIDMap;
3063  unsigned CurrID = 0;
3064  RecordData Record;
3065 
3066  auto EncodeDiagStateFlags =
3067  [](const DiagnosticsEngine::DiagState *DS) -> unsigned {
3068  unsigned Result = (unsigned)DS->ExtBehavior;
3069  for (unsigned Val :
3070  {(unsigned)DS->IgnoreAllWarnings, (unsigned)DS->EnableAllWarnings,
3071  (unsigned)DS->WarningsAsErrors, (unsigned)DS->ErrorsAsFatal,
3072  (unsigned)DS->SuppressSystemWarnings})
3073  Result = (Result << 1) | Val;
3074  return Result;
3075  };
3076 
3077  unsigned Flags = EncodeDiagStateFlags(Diag.DiagStatesByLoc.FirstDiagState);
3078  Record.push_back(Flags);
3079 
3080  auto AddDiagState = [&](const DiagnosticsEngine::DiagState *State,
3081  bool IncludeNonPragmaStates) {
3082  // Ensure that the diagnostic state wasn't modified since it was created.
3083  // We will not correctly round-trip this information otherwise.
3084  assert(Flags == EncodeDiagStateFlags(State) &&
3085  "diag state flags vary in single AST file");
3086 
3087  // If we ever serialize non-pragma mappings outside the initial state, the
3088  // code below will need to consider more than getDefaultMapping.
3089  assert(!IncludeNonPragmaStates ||
3090  State == Diag.DiagStatesByLoc.FirstDiagState);
3091 
3092  unsigned &DiagStateID = DiagStateIDMap[State];
3093  Record.push_back(DiagStateID);
3094 
3095  if (DiagStateID == 0) {
3096  DiagStateID = ++CurrID;
3097  SmallVector<std::pair<unsigned, DiagnosticMapping>> Mappings;
3098 
3099  // Add a placeholder for the number of mappings.
3100  auto SizeIdx = Record.size();
3101  Record.emplace_back();
3102  for (const auto &I : *State) {
3103  // Maybe skip non-pragmas.
3104  if (!I.second.isPragma() && !IncludeNonPragmaStates)
3105  continue;
3106  // Skip default mappings. We have a mapping for every diagnostic ever
3107  // emitted, regardless of whether it was customized.
3108  if (!I.second.isPragma() &&
3109  I.second == DiagnosticIDs::getDefaultMapping(I.first))
3110  continue;
3111  Mappings.push_back(I);
3112  }
3113 
3114  // Sort by diag::kind for deterministic output.
3115  llvm::sort(Mappings, [](const auto &LHS, const auto &RHS) {
3116  return LHS.first < RHS.first;
3117  });
3118 
3119  for (const auto &I : Mappings) {
3120  Record.push_back(I.first);
3121  Record.push_back(I.second.serialize());
3122  }
3123  // Update the placeholder.
3124  Record[SizeIdx] = (Record.size() - SizeIdx) / 2;
3125  }
3126  };
3127 
3128  AddDiagState(Diag.DiagStatesByLoc.FirstDiagState, isModule);
3129 
3130  // Reserve a spot for the number of locations with state transitions.
3131  auto NumLocationsIdx = Record.size();
3132  Record.emplace_back();
3133 
3134  // Emit the state transitions.
3135  unsigned NumLocations = 0;
3136  for (auto &FileIDAndFile : Diag.DiagStatesByLoc.Files) {
3137  if (!FileIDAndFile.first.isValid() ||
3138  !FileIDAndFile.second.HasLocalTransitions)
3139  continue;
3140  ++NumLocations;
3141 
3142  AddFileID(FileIDAndFile.first, Record);
3143 
3144  Record.push_back(FileIDAndFile.second.StateTransitions.size());
3145  for (auto &StatePoint : FileIDAndFile.second.StateTransitions) {
3146  Record.push_back(getAdjustedOffset(StatePoint.Offset));
3147  AddDiagState(StatePoint.State, false);
3148  }
3149  }
3150 
3151  // Backpatch the number of locations.
3152  Record[NumLocationsIdx] = NumLocations;
3153 
3154  // Emit CurDiagStateLoc. Do it last in order to match source order.
3155  //
3156  // This also protects against a hypothetical corner case with simulating
3157  // -Werror settings for implicit modules in the ASTReader, where reading
3158  // CurDiagState out of context could change whether warning pragmas are
3159  // treated as errors.
3160  AddSourceLocation(Diag.DiagStatesByLoc.CurDiagStateLoc, Record);
3161  AddDiagState(Diag.DiagStatesByLoc.CurDiagState, false);
3162 
3163  Stream.EmitRecord(DIAG_PRAGMA_MAPPINGS, Record);
3164 }

3166 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3167 // Type Serialization
3168 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3169 
3170 /// Write the representation of a type to the AST stream.
3171 void ASTWriter::WriteType(QualType T) {
3172  TypeIdx &IdxRef = TypeIdxs[T];
3173  if (IdxRef.getIndex() == 0) // we haven't seen this type before.
3174  IdxRef = TypeIdx(NextTypeID++);
3175  TypeIdx Idx = IdxRef;
3176 
3177  assert(Idx.getIndex() >= FirstTypeID && "Re-writing a type from a prior AST");
3178 
3179  // Emit the type's representation.
3180  uint64_t Offset = ASTTypeWriter(*this).write(T) - DeclTypesBlockStartOffset;
3181 
3182  // Record the offset for this type.
3183  unsigned Index = Idx.getIndex() - FirstTypeID;
3184  if (TypeOffsets.size() == Index)
3185  TypeOffsets.emplace_back(Offset);
3186  else if (TypeOffsets.size() < Index) {
3187  TypeOffsets.resize(Index + 1);
3188  TypeOffsets[Index].setBitOffset(Offset);
3189  } else {
3190  llvm_unreachable("Types emitted in wrong order");
3191  }
3192 }
3193 
3194 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3195 // Declaration Serialization
3196 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3197 
3198 /// Write the block containing all of the declaration IDs
3199 /// lexically declared within the given DeclContext.
3200 ///
3201 /// \returns the offset of the DECL_CONTEXT_LEXICAL block within the
3202 /// bitstream, or 0 if no block was written.
3203 uint64_t ASTWriter::WriteDeclContextLexicalBlock(ASTContext &Context,
3204  DeclContext *DC) {
3205  if (DC->decls_empty())
3206  return 0;
3207 
3208  // In reduced BMI, we don't care the declarations in functions.
3209  if (GeneratingReducedBMI && DC->isFunctionOrMethod())
3210  return 0;
3211 
3212  uint64_t Offset = Stream.GetCurrentBitNo();
3213  SmallVector<DeclID, 128> KindDeclPairs;
3214  for (const auto *D : DC->decls()) {
3215  if (DoneWritingDeclsAndTypes && !wasDeclEmitted(D))
3216  continue;
3217 
3218  KindDeclPairs.push_back(D->getKind());
3219  KindDeclPairs.push_back(GetDeclRef(D));
3220  }
3221 
3222  ++NumLexicalDeclContexts;
3223  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {DECL_CONTEXT_LEXICAL};
3224  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(DeclContextLexicalAbbrev, Record,
3225  bytes(KindDeclPairs));
3226  return Offset;
3227 }
3228 
3229 void ASTWriter::WriteTypeDeclOffsets() {
3230  using namespace llvm;
3231 
3232  // Write the type offsets array
3233  auto Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
3234  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(TYPE_OFFSET));
3235  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 32)); // # of types
3236  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 32)); // base type index
3237  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob)); // types block
3238  unsigned TypeOffsetAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
3239  {
3240  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {TYPE_OFFSET, TypeOffsets.size(),
3241  FirstTypeID - NUM_PREDEF_TYPE_IDS};
3242  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(TypeOffsetAbbrev, Record, bytes(TypeOffsets));
3243  }
3244 
3245  // Write the declaration offsets array
3246  Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
3247  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(DECL_OFFSET));
3248  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 32)); // # of declarations
3249  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 32)); // base decl ID
3250  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob)); // declarations block
3251  unsigned DeclOffsetAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
3252  {
3253  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {DECL_OFFSET, DeclOffsets.size(),
3254  FirstDeclID - NUM_PREDEF_DECL_IDS};
3255  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(DeclOffsetAbbrev, Record, bytes(DeclOffsets));
3256  }
3257 }
3258 
3259 void ASTWriter::WriteFileDeclIDsMap() {
3260  using namespace llvm;
3261 
3262  SmallVector<std::pair<FileID, DeclIDInFileInfo *>, 64> SortedFileDeclIDs;
3263  SortedFileDeclIDs.reserve(FileDeclIDs.size());
3264  for (const auto &P : FileDeclIDs)
3265  SortedFileDeclIDs.push_back(std::make_pair(P.first, P.second.get()));
3266  llvm::sort(SortedFileDeclIDs, llvm::less_first());
3267 
3268  // Join the vectors of DeclIDs from all files.
3269  SmallVector<DeclID, 256> FileGroupedDeclIDs;
3270  for (auto &FileDeclEntry : SortedFileDeclIDs) {
3271  DeclIDInFileInfo &Info = *FileDeclEntry.second;
3272  Info.FirstDeclIndex = FileGroupedDeclIDs.size();
3273  llvm::stable_sort(Info.DeclIDs);
3274  for (auto &LocDeclEntry : Info.DeclIDs)
3275  FileGroupedDeclIDs.push_back(LocDeclEntry.second);
3276  }
3277 
3278  auto Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
3279  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(FILE_SORTED_DECLS));
3280  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 32));
3281  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob));
3282  unsigned AbbrevCode = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
3283  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {FILE_SORTED_DECLS,
3284  FileGroupedDeclIDs.size()};
3285  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(AbbrevCode, Record, bytes(FileGroupedDeclIDs));
3286 }
3287 
3288 void ASTWriter::WriteComments() {
3289  Stream.EnterSubblock(COMMENTS_BLOCK_ID, 3);
3290  auto _ = llvm::make_scope_exit([this] { Stream.ExitBlock(); });
3291  if (!PP->getPreprocessorOpts().WriteCommentListToPCH)
3292  return;
3293 
3294  // Don't write comments to BMI to reduce the size of BMI.
3295  // If language services (e.g., clangd) want such abilities,
3296  // we can offer a special option then.
3297  if (isWritingStdCXXNamedModules())
3298  return;
3299 
3300  RecordData Record;
3301  for (const auto &FO : Context->Comments.OrderedComments) {
3302  for (const auto &OC : FO.second) {
3303  const RawComment *I = OC.second;
3304  Record.clear();
3305  AddSourceRange(I->getSourceRange(), Record);
3306  Record.push_back(I->getKind());
3307  Record.push_back(I->isTrailingComment());
3308  Record.push_back(I->isAlmostTrailingComment());
3309  Stream.EmitRecord(COMMENTS_RAW_COMMENT, Record);
3310  }
3311  }
3312 }
3313 
3314 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3315 // Global Method Pool and Selector Serialization
3316 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3317 
3318 namespace {
3319 
3320 // Trait used for the on-disk hash table used in the method pool.
3321 class ASTMethodPoolTrait {
3322  ASTWriter &Writer;
3323 
3324 public:
3325  using key_type = Selector;
3326  using key_type_ref = key_type;
3327 
3328  struct data_type {
3329  SelectorID ID;
3330  ObjCMethodList Instance, Factory;
3331  };
3332  using data_type_ref = const data_type &;
3333 
3334  using hash_value_type = unsigned;
3335  using offset_type = unsigned;
3336 
3337  explicit ASTMethodPoolTrait(ASTWriter &Writer) : Writer(Writer) {}
3338 
3339  static hash_value_type ComputeHash(Selector Sel) {
3340  return serialization::ComputeHash(Sel);
3341  }
3342 
3343  std::pair<unsigned, unsigned>
3344  EmitKeyDataLength(raw_ostream& Out, Selector Sel,
3345  data_type_ref Methods) {
3346  unsigned KeyLen = 2 + (Sel.getNumArgs()? Sel.getNumArgs() * 4 : 4);
3347  unsigned DataLen = 4 + 2 + 2; // 2 bytes for each of the method counts
3348  for (const ObjCMethodList *Method = &Methods.Instance; Method;
3349  Method = Method->getNext())
3350  if (ShouldWriteMethodListNode(Method))
3351  DataLen += sizeof(DeclID);
3352  for (const ObjCMethodList *Method = &Methods.Factory; Method;
3353  Method = Method->getNext())
3354  if (ShouldWriteMethodListNode(Method))
3355  DataLen += sizeof(DeclID);
3356  return emitULEBKeyDataLength(KeyLen, DataLen, Out);
3357  }
3358 
3359  void EmitKey(raw_ostream& Out, Selector Sel, unsigned) {
3360  using namespace llvm::support;
3361 
3362  endian::Writer LE(Out, llvm::endianness::little);
3363  uint64_t Start = Out.tell();
3364  assert((Start >> 32) == 0 && "Selector key offset too large");
3365  Writer.SetSelectorOffset(Sel, Start);
3366  unsigned N = Sel.getNumArgs();
3367  LE.write<uint16_t>(N);
3368  if (N == 0)
3369  N = 1;
3370  for (unsigned I = 0; I != N; ++I)
3371  LE.write<uint32_t>(
3372  Writer.getIdentifierRef(Sel.getIdentifierInfoForSlot(I)));
3373  }
3374 
3375  void EmitData(raw_ostream& Out, key_type_ref,
3376  data_type_ref Methods, unsigned DataLen) {
3377  using namespace llvm::support;
3378 
3379  endian::Writer LE(Out, llvm::endianness::little);
3380  uint64_t Start = Out.tell(); (void)Start;
3381  LE.write<uint32_t>(Methods.ID);
3382  unsigned NumInstanceMethods = 0;
3383  for (const ObjCMethodList *Method = &Methods.Instance; Method;
3384  Method = Method->getNext())
3385  if (ShouldWriteMethodListNode(Method))
3386  ++NumInstanceMethods;
3387 
3388  unsigned NumFactoryMethods = 0;
3389  for (const ObjCMethodList *Method = &Methods.Factory; Method;
3390  Method = Method->getNext())
3391  if (ShouldWriteMethodListNode(Method))
3392  ++NumFactoryMethods;
3393 
3394  unsigned InstanceBits = Methods.Instance.getBits();
3395  assert(InstanceBits < 4);
3396  unsigned InstanceHasMoreThanOneDeclBit =
3397  Methods.Instance.hasMoreThanOneDecl();
3398  unsigned FullInstanceBits = (NumInstanceMethods << 3) |
3399  (InstanceHasMoreThanOneDeclBit << 2) |
3400  InstanceBits;
3401  unsigned FactoryBits = Methods.Factory.getBits();
3402  assert(FactoryBits < 4);
3403  unsigned FactoryHasMoreThanOneDeclBit =
3404  Methods.Factory.hasMoreThanOneDecl();
3405  unsigned FullFactoryBits = (NumFactoryMethods << 3) |
3406  (FactoryHasMoreThanOneDeclBit << 2) |
3407  FactoryBits;
3408  LE.write<uint16_t>(FullInstanceBits);
3409  LE.write<uint16_t>(FullFactoryBits);
3410  for (const ObjCMethodList *Method = &Methods.Instance; Method;
3411  Method = Method->getNext())
3412  if (ShouldWriteMethodListNode(Method))
3413  LE.write<DeclID>(Writer.getDeclID(Method->getMethod()));
3414  for (const ObjCMethodList *Method = &Methods.Factory; Method;
3415  Method = Method->getNext())
3416  if (ShouldWriteMethodListNode(Method))
3417  LE.write<DeclID>(Writer.getDeclID(Method->getMethod()));
3418 
3419  assert(Out.tell() - Start == DataLen && "Data length is wrong");
3420  }
3421 
3422 private:
3423  static bool ShouldWriteMethodListNode(const ObjCMethodList *Node) {
3424  return (Node->getMethod() && !Node->getMethod()->isFromASTFile());
3425  }
3426 };
3427 
3428 } // namespace
3429 
3430 /// Write ObjC data: selectors and the method pool.
3431 ///
3432 /// The method pool contains both instance and factory methods, stored
3433 /// in an on-disk hash table indexed by the selector. The hash table also
3434 /// contains an empty entry for every other selector known to Sema.
3435 void ASTWriter::WriteSelectors(Sema &SemaRef) {
3436  using namespace llvm;
3437 
3438  // Do we have to do anything at all?
3439  if (SemaRef.MethodPool.empty() && SelectorIDs.empty())
3440  return;
3441  unsigned NumTableEntries = 0;
3442  // Create and write out the blob that contains selectors and the method pool.
3443  {
3444  llvm::OnDiskChainedHashTableGenerator<ASTMethodPoolTrait> Generator;
3445  ASTMethodPoolTrait Trait(*this);
3446 
3447  // Create the on-disk hash table representation. We walk through every
3448  // selector we've seen and look it up in the method pool.
3449  SelectorOffsets.resize(NextSelectorID - FirstSelectorID);
3450  for (auto &SelectorAndID : SelectorIDs) {
3451  Selector S = SelectorAndID.first;
3452  SelectorID ID = SelectorAndID.second;
3453  Sema::GlobalMethodPool::iterator F = SemaRef.MethodPool.find(S);
3454  ASTMethodPoolTrait::data_type Data = {
3455  ID,
3456  ObjCMethodList(),
3457  ObjCMethodList()
3458  };
3459  if (F != SemaRef.MethodPool.end()) {
3460  Data.Instance = F->second.first;
3461  Data.Factory = F->second.second;
3462  }
3463  // Only write this selector if it's not in an existing AST or something
3464  // changed.
3465  if (Chain && ID < FirstSelectorID) {
3466  // Selector already exists. Did it change?
3467  bool changed = false;
3468  for (ObjCMethodList *M = &Data.Instance; M && M->getMethod();
3469  M = M->getNext()) {
3470  if (!M->getMethod()->isFromASTFile()) {
3471  changed = true;
3472  Data.Instance = *M;
3473  break;
3474  }
3475  }
3476  for (ObjCMethodList *M = &Data.Factory; M && M->getMethod();
3477  M = M->getNext()) {
3478  if (!M->getMethod()->isFromASTFile()) {
3479  changed = true;
3480  Data.Factory = *M;
3481  break;
3482  }
3483  }
3484  if (!changed)
3485  continue;
3486  } else if (Data.Instance.getMethod() || Data.Factory.getMethod()) {
3487  // A new method pool entry.
3488  ++NumTableEntries;
3489  }
3490  Generator.insert(S, Data, Trait);
3491  }
3492 
3493  // Create the on-disk hash table in a buffer.
3494  SmallString<4096> MethodPool;
3495  uint32_t BucketOffset;
3496  {
3497  using namespace llvm::support;
3498 
3499  ASTMethodPoolTrait Trait(*this);
3500  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(MethodPool);
3501  // Make sure that no bucket is at offset 0
3502  endian::write<uint32_t>(Out, 0, llvm::endianness::little);
3503  BucketOffset = Generator.Emit(Out, Trait);
3504  }
3505 
3506  // Create a blob abbreviation
3507  auto Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
3508  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(METHOD_POOL));
3509  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 32));
3510  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 32));
3511  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob));
3512  unsigned MethodPoolAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
3513 
3514  // Write the method pool
3515  {
3516  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {METHOD_POOL, BucketOffset,
3517  NumTableEntries};
3518  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(MethodPoolAbbrev, Record, MethodPool);
3519  }
3520 
3521  // Create a blob abbreviation for the selector table offsets.
3522  Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
3523  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(SELECTOR_OFFSETS));
3524  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 32)); // size
3525  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 32)); // first ID
3526  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob));
3527  unsigned SelectorOffsetAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
3528 
3529  // Write the selector offsets table.
3530  {
3531  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {
3532  SELECTOR_OFFSETS, SelectorOffsets.size(),
3533  FirstSelectorID - NUM_PREDEF_SELECTOR_IDS};
3534  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(SelectorOffsetAbbrev, Record,
3535  bytes(SelectorOffsets));
3536  }
3537  }
3538 }
3539 
3540 /// Write the selectors referenced in @selector expression into AST file.
3541 void ASTWriter::WriteReferencedSelectorsPool(Sema &SemaRef) {
3542  using namespace llvm;
3543 
3544  if (SemaRef.ReferencedSelectors.empty())
3545  return;
3546 
3547  RecordData Record;
3548  ASTRecordWriter Writer(*this, Record);
3549 
3550  // Note: this writes out all references even for a dependent AST. But it is
3551  // very tricky to fix, and given that @selector shouldn't really appear in
3552  // headers, probably not worth it. It's not a correctness issue.
3553  for (auto &SelectorAndLocation : SemaRef.ReferencedSelectors) {
3554  Selector Sel = SelectorAndLocation.first;
3555  SourceLocation Loc = SelectorAndLocation.second;
3556  Writer.AddSelectorRef(Sel);
3557  Writer.AddSourceLocation(Loc);
3558  }
3559  Writer.Emit(REFERENCED_SELECTOR_POOL);
3560 }
3561 
3562 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3563 // Identifier Table Serialization
3564 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3565 
3566 /// Determine the declaration that should be put into the name lookup table to
3567 /// represent the given declaration in this module. This is usually D itself,
3568 /// but if D was imported and merged into a local declaration, we want the most
3569 /// recent local declaration instead. The chosen declaration will be the most
3570 /// recent declaration in any module that imports this one.
3571 static NamedDecl *getDeclForLocalLookup(const LangOptions &LangOpts,
3572  NamedDecl *D) {
3573  if (!LangOpts.Modules || !D->isFromASTFile())
3574  return D;
3575 
3576  if (Decl *Redecl = D->getPreviousDecl()) {
3577  // For Redeclarable decls, a prior declaration might be local.
3578  for (; Redecl; Redecl = Redecl->getPreviousDecl()) {
3579  // If we find a local decl, we're done.
3580  if (!Redecl->isFromASTFile()) {
3581  // Exception: in very rare cases (for injected-class-names), not all
3582  // redeclarations are in the same semantic context. Skip ones in a
3583  // different context. They don't go in this lookup table at all.
3584  if (!Redecl->getDeclContext()->getRedeclContext()->Equals(
3585  D->getDeclContext()->getRedeclContext()))
3586  continue;
3587  return cast<NamedDecl>(Redecl);
3588  }
3589 
3590  // If we find a decl from a (chained-)PCH stop since we won't find a
3591  // local one.
3592  if (Redecl->getOwningModuleID() == 0)
3593  break;
3594  }
3595  } else if (Decl *First = D->getCanonicalDecl()) {
3596  // For Mergeable decls, the first decl might be local.
3597  if (!First->isFromASTFile())
3598  return cast<NamedDecl>(First);
3599  }
3600 
3601  // All declarations are imported. Our most recent declaration will also be
3602  // the most recent one in anyone who imports us.
3603  return D;
3604 }
3605 
3606 namespace {
3607 
3608 class ASTIdentifierTableTrait {
3609  ASTWriter &Writer;
3610  Preprocessor &PP;
3611  IdentifierResolver &IdResolver;
3612  bool IsModule;
3613  bool NeedDecls;
3614  ASTWriter::RecordData *InterestingIdentifierOffsets;
3615 
3616  /// Determines whether this is an "interesting" identifier that needs a
3617  /// full IdentifierInfo structure written into the hash table. Notably, this
3618  /// doesn't check whether the name has macros defined; use PublicMacroIterator
3619  /// to check that.
3620  bool isInterestingIdentifier(const IdentifierInfo *II, uint64_t MacroOffset) {
3621  bool IsInteresting =
3622  II->getNotableIdentifierID() !=
3623  tok::NotableIdentifierKind::not_notable ||
3624  II->getBuiltinID() != Builtin::ID::NotBuiltin ||
3625  II->getObjCKeywordID() != tok::ObjCKeywordKind::objc_not_keyword;
3626  if (MacroOffset || II->isPoisoned() || (!IsModule && IsInteresting) ||
3627  II->hasRevertedTokenIDToIdentifier() ||
3628  (NeedDecls && II->getFETokenInfo()))
3629  return true;
3630 
3631  return false;
3632  }
3633 
3634 public:
3635  using key_type = const IdentifierInfo *;
3636  using key_type_ref = key_type;
3637 
3638  using data_type = IdentID;
3639  using data_type_ref = data_type;
3640 
3641  using hash_value_type = unsigned;
3642  using offset_type = unsigned;
3643 
3644  ASTIdentifierTableTrait(ASTWriter &Writer, Preprocessor &PP,
3645  IdentifierResolver &IdResolver, bool IsModule,
3646  ASTWriter::RecordData *InterestingIdentifierOffsets)
3647  : Writer(Writer), PP(PP), IdResolver(IdResolver), IsModule(IsModule),
3648  NeedDecls(!IsModule || !Writer.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus),
3649  InterestingIdentifierOffsets(InterestingIdentifierOffsets) {}
3650 
3651  bool needDecls() const { return NeedDecls; }
3652 
3653  static hash_value_type ComputeHash(const IdentifierInfo* II) {
3654  return llvm::djbHash(II->getName());
3655  }
3656 
3657  bool isInterestingIdentifier(const IdentifierInfo *II) {
3658  auto MacroOffset = Writer.getMacroDirectivesOffset(II);
3659  return isInterestingIdentifier(II, MacroOffset);
3660  }
3661 
3662  bool isInterestingNonMacroIdentifier(const IdentifierInfo *II) {
3663  return isInterestingIdentifier(II, 0);
3664  }
3665 
3666  std::pair<unsigned, unsigned>
3667  EmitKeyDataLength(raw_ostream &Out, const IdentifierInfo *II, IdentID ID) {
3668  // Record the location of the identifier data. This is used when generating
3669  // the mapping from persistent IDs to strings.
3670  Writer.SetIdentifierOffset(II, Out.tell());
3671 
3672  auto MacroOffset = Writer.getMacroDirectivesOffset(II);
3673 
3674  // Emit the offset of the key/data length information to the interesting
3675  // identifiers table if necessary.
3676  if (InterestingIdentifierOffsets &&
3677  isInterestingIdentifier(II, MacroOffset))
3678  InterestingIdentifierOffsets->push_back(Out.tell());
3679 
3680  unsigned KeyLen = II->getLength() + 1;
3681  unsigned DataLen = 4; // 4 bytes for the persistent ID << 1
3682  if (isInterestingIdentifier(II, MacroOffset)) {
3683  DataLen += 2; // 2 bytes for builtin ID
3684  DataLen += 2; // 2 bytes for flags
3685  if (MacroOffset)
3686  DataLen += 4; // MacroDirectives offset.
3687 
3688  if (NeedDecls)
3689  DataLen += std::distance(IdResolver.begin(II), IdResolver.end()) *
3690  sizeof(DeclID);
3691  }
3692  return emitULEBKeyDataLength(KeyLen, DataLen, Out);
3693  }
3694 
3695  void EmitKey(raw_ostream &Out, const IdentifierInfo *II, unsigned KeyLen) {
3696  Out.write(II->getNameStart(), KeyLen);
3697  }
3698 
3699  void EmitData(raw_ostream &Out, const IdentifierInfo *II, IdentID ID,
3700  unsigned) {
3701  using namespace llvm::support;
3702 
3703  endian::Writer LE(Out, llvm::endianness::little);
3704 
3705  auto MacroOffset = Writer.getMacroDirectivesOffset(II);
3706  if (!isInterestingIdentifier(II, MacroOffset)) {
3707  LE.write<uint32_t>(ID << 1);
3708  return;
3709  }
3710 
3711  LE.write<uint32_t>((ID << 1) | 0x01);
3712  uint32_t Bits = (uint32_t)II->getObjCOrBuiltinID();
3713  assert((Bits & 0xffff) == Bits && "ObjCOrBuiltinID too big for ASTReader.");
3714  LE.write<uint16_t>(Bits);
3715  Bits = 0;
3716  bool HadMacroDefinition = MacroOffset != 0;
3717  Bits = (Bits << 1) | unsigned(HadMacroDefinition);
3718  Bits = (Bits << 1) | unsigned(II->isExtensionToken());
3719  Bits = (Bits << 1) | unsigned(II->isPoisoned());
3720  Bits = (Bits << 1) | unsigned(II->hasRevertedTokenIDToIdentifier());
3721  Bits = (Bits << 1) | unsigned(II->isCPlusPlusOperatorKeyword());
3722  LE.write<uint16_t>(Bits);
3723 
3724  if (HadMacroDefinition)
3725  LE.write<uint32_t>(MacroOffset);
3726 
3727  if (NeedDecls) {
3728  // Emit the declaration IDs in reverse order, because the
3729  // IdentifierResolver provides the declarations as they would be
3730  // visible (e.g., the function "stat" would come before the struct
3731  // "stat"), but the ASTReader adds declarations to the end of the list
3732  // (so we need to see the struct "stat" before the function "stat").
3733  // Only emit declarations that aren't from a chained PCH, though.
3734  SmallVector<NamedDecl *, 16> Decls(IdResolver.decls(II));
3735  for (NamedDecl *D : llvm::reverse(Decls))
3736  LE.write<DeclID>(
3737  Writer.getDeclID(getDeclForLocalLookup(PP.getLangOpts(), D)));
3738  }
3739  }
3740 };
3741 
3742 } // namespace
3743 
3744 /// Write the identifier table into the AST file.
3745 ///
3746 /// The identifier table consists of a blob containing string data
3747 /// (the actual identifiers themselves) and a separate "offsets" index
3748 /// that maps identifier IDs to locations within the blob.
3749 void ASTWriter::WriteIdentifierTable(Preprocessor &PP,
3750  IdentifierResolver &IdResolver,
3751  bool IsModule) {
3752  using namespace llvm;
3753 
3754  RecordData InterestingIdents;
3755 
3756  // Create and write out the blob that contains the identifier
3757  // strings.
3758  {
3759  llvm::OnDiskChainedHashTableGenerator<ASTIdentifierTableTrait> Generator;
3760  ASTIdentifierTableTrait Trait(*this, PP, IdResolver, IsModule,
3761  IsModule ? &InterestingIdents : nullptr);
3762 
3763  // Look for any identifiers that were named while processing the
3764  // headers, but are otherwise not needed. We add these to the hash
3765  // table to enable checking of the predefines buffer in the case
3766  // where the user adds new macro definitions when building the AST
3767  // file.
3768  SmallVector<const IdentifierInfo *, 128> IIs;
3769  for (const auto &ID : PP.getIdentifierTable())
3770  if (Trait.isInterestingNonMacroIdentifier(ID.second))
3771  IIs.push_back(ID.second);
3772  // Sort the identifiers lexicographically before getting the references so
3773  // that their order is stable.
3774  llvm::sort(IIs, llvm::deref<std::less<>>());
3775  for (const IdentifierInfo *II : IIs)
3776  getIdentifierRef(II);
3777 
3778  // Create the on-disk hash table representation. We only store offsets
3779  // for identifiers that appear here for the first time.
3780  IdentifierOffsets.resize(NextIdentID - FirstIdentID);
3781  for (auto IdentIDPair : IdentifierIDs) {
3782  const IdentifierInfo *II = IdentIDPair.first;
3783  IdentID ID = IdentIDPair.second;
3784  assert(II && "NULL identifier in identifier table");
3785 
3786  // Write out identifiers if either the ID is local or the identifier has
3787  // changed since it was loaded.
3788  if (ID >= FirstIdentID || !Chain || !II->isFromAST() ||
3789  II->hasChangedSinceDeserialization() ||
3790  (Trait.needDecls() &&
3791  II->hasFETokenInfoChangedSinceDeserialization()))
3792  Generator.insert(II, ID, Trait);
3793  }
3794 
3795  // Create the on-disk hash table in a buffer.
3796  SmallString<4096> IdentifierTable;
3797  uint32_t BucketOffset;
3798  {
3799  using namespace llvm::support;
3800 
3801  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(IdentifierTable);
3802  // Make sure that no bucket is at offset 0
3803  endian::write<uint32_t>(Out, 0, llvm::endianness::little);
3804  BucketOffset = Generator.Emit(Out, Trait);
3805  }
3806 
3807  // Create a blob abbreviation
3808  auto Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
3809  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(IDENTIFIER_TABLE));
3810  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 32));
3811  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob));
3812  unsigned IDTableAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
3813 
3814  // Write the identifier table
3815  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {IDENTIFIER_TABLE, BucketOffset};
3816  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(IDTableAbbrev, Record, IdentifierTable);
3817  }
3818 
3819  // Write the offsets table for identifier IDs.
3820  auto Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
3821  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(IDENTIFIER_OFFSET));
3822  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 32)); // # of identifiers
3823  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Fixed, 32)); // first ID
3824  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob));
3825  unsigned IdentifierOffsetAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
3826 
3827 #ifndef NDEBUG
3828  for (unsigned I = 0, N = IdentifierOffsets.size(); I != N; ++I)
3829  assert(IdentifierOffsets[I] && "Missing identifier offset?");
3830 #endif
3831 
3832  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {IDENTIFIER_OFFSET,
3833  IdentifierOffsets.size(),
3834  FirstIdentID - NUM_PREDEF_IDENT_IDS};
3835  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(IdentifierOffsetAbbrev, Record,
3836  bytes(IdentifierOffsets));
3837 
3838  // In C++, write the list of interesting identifiers (those that are
3839  // defined as macros, poisoned, or similar unusual things).
3840  if (!InterestingIdents.empty())
3841  Stream.EmitRecord(INTERESTING_IDENTIFIERS, InterestingIdents);
3842 }
3843 
3844 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3845 // DeclContext's Name Lookup Table Serialization
3846 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3847 
3848 namespace {
3849 
3850 // Trait used for the on-disk hash table used in the method pool.
3851 class ASTDeclContextNameLookupTrait {
3852  ASTWriter &Writer;
3853  llvm::SmallVector<DeclID, 64> DeclIDs;
3854 
3855 public:
3856  using key_type = DeclarationNameKey;
3857  using key_type_ref = key_type;
3858 
3859  /// A start and end index into DeclIDs, representing a sequence of decls.
3860  using data_type = std::pair<unsigned, unsigned>;
3861  using data_type_ref = const data_type &;
3862 
3863  using hash_value_type = unsigned;
3864  using offset_type = unsigned;
3865 
3866  explicit ASTDeclContextNameLookupTrait(ASTWriter &Writer) : Writer(Writer) {}
3867 
3868  template<typename Coll>
3869  data_type getData(const Coll &Decls) {
3870  unsigned Start = DeclIDs.size();
3871  for (NamedDecl *D : Decls) {
3872  NamedDecl *DeclForLocalLookup =
3873  getDeclForLocalLookup(Writer.getLangOpts(), D);
3874 
3875  if (Writer.getDoneWritingDeclsAndTypes() &&
3876  !Writer.wasDeclEmitted(DeclForLocalLookup))
3877  continue;
3878 
3879  DeclIDs.push_back(Writer.GetDeclRef(DeclForLocalLookup));
3880  }
3881  return std::make_pair(Start, DeclIDs.size());
3882  }
3883 
3884  data_type ImportData(const reader::ASTDeclContextNameLookupTrait::data_type &FromReader) {
3885  unsigned Start = DeclIDs.size();
3886  DeclIDs.insert(DeclIDs.end(), DeclIDIterator(FromReader.begin()),
3887  DeclIDIterator(FromReader.end()));
3888  return std::make_pair(Start, DeclIDs.size());
3889  }
3890 
3891  static bool EqualKey(key_type_ref a, key_type_ref b) {
3892  return a == b;
3893  }
3894 
3895  hash_value_type ComputeHash(DeclarationNameKey Name) {
3896  return Name.getHash();
3897  }
3898 
3899  void EmitFileRef(raw_ostream &Out, ModuleFile *F) const {
3900  assert(Writer.hasChain() &&
3901  "have reference to loaded module file but no chain?");
3902 
3903  using namespace llvm::support;
3904 
3905  endian::write<uint32_t>(Out, Writer.getChain()->getModuleFileID(F),
3906  llvm::endianness::little);
3907  }
3908 
3909  std::pair<unsigned, unsigned> EmitKeyDataLength(raw_ostream &Out,
3910  DeclarationNameKey Name,
3911  data_type_ref Lookup) {
3912  unsigned KeyLen = 1;
3913  switch (Name.getKind()) {
3914  case DeclarationName::Identifier:
3915  case DeclarationName::ObjCZeroArgSelector:
3916  case DeclarationName::ObjCOneArgSelector:
3917  case DeclarationName::ObjCMultiArgSelector:
3918  case DeclarationName::CXXLiteralOperatorName:
3919  case DeclarationName::CXXDeductionGuideName:
3920  KeyLen += 4;
3921  break;
3922  case DeclarationName::CXXOperatorName:
3923  KeyLen += 1;
3924  break;
3925  case DeclarationName::CXXConstructorName:
3926  case DeclarationName::CXXDestructorName:
3927  case DeclarationName::CXXConversionFunctionName:
3928  case DeclarationName::CXXUsingDirective:
3929  break;
3930  }
3931 
3932  // length of DeclIDs.
3933  unsigned DataLen = sizeof(DeclID) * (Lookup.second - Lookup.first);
3934 
3935  return emitULEBKeyDataLength(KeyLen, DataLen, Out);
3936  }
3937 
3938  void EmitKey(raw_ostream &Out, DeclarationNameKey Name, unsigned) {
3939  using namespace llvm::support;
3940 
3941  endian::Writer LE(Out, llvm::endianness::little);
3942  LE.write<uint8_t>(Name.getKind());
3943  switch (Name.getKind()) {
3944  case DeclarationName::Identifier:
3945  case DeclarationName::CXXLiteralOperatorName:
3946  case DeclarationName::CXXDeductionGuideName:
3947  LE.write<uint32_t>(Writer.getIdentifierRef(Name.getIdentifier()));
3948  return;
3949  case DeclarationName::ObjCZeroArgSelector:
3950  case DeclarationName::ObjCOneArgSelector:
3951  case DeclarationName::ObjCMultiArgSelector:
3952  LE.write<uint32_t>(Writer.getSelectorRef(Name.getSelector()));
3953  return;
3954  case DeclarationName::CXXOperatorName:
3955  assert(Name.getOperatorKind() < NUM_OVERLOADED_OPERATORS &&
3956  "Invalid operator?");
3957  LE.write<uint8_t>(Name.getOperatorKind());
3958  return;
3959  case DeclarationName::CXXConstructorName:
3960  case DeclarationName::CXXDestructorName:
3961  case DeclarationName::CXXConversionFunctionName:
3962  case DeclarationName::CXXUsingDirective:
3963  return;
3964  }
3965 
3966  llvm_unreachable("Invalid name kind?");
3967  }
3968 
3969  void EmitData(raw_ostream &Out, key_type_ref, data_type Lookup,
3970  unsigned DataLen) {
3971  using namespace llvm::support;
3972 
3973  endian::Writer LE(Out, llvm::endianness::little);
3974  uint64_t Start = Out.tell(); (void)Start;
3975  for (unsigned I = Lookup.first, N = Lookup.second; I != N; ++I)
3976  LE.write<DeclID>(DeclIDs[I]);
3977  assert(Out.tell() - Start == DataLen && "Data length is wrong");
3978  }
3979 };
3980 
3981 } // namespace
3982 
3983 bool ASTWriter::isLookupResultExternal(StoredDeclsList &Result,
3984  DeclContext *DC) {
3985  return Result.hasExternalDecls() &&
3986  DC->hasNeedToReconcileExternalVisibleStorage();
3987 }
3988 
3989 bool ASTWriter::isLookupResultEntirelyExternalOrUnreachable(
3990  StoredDeclsList &Result, DeclContext *DC) {
3991  for (auto *D : Result.getLookupResult()) {
3992  auto *LocalD = getDeclForLocalLookup(getLangOpts(), D);
3993  if (LocalD->isFromASTFile())
3994  continue;
3995 
3996  // We can only be sure whether the local declaration is reachable
3997  // after we done writing the declarations and types.
3998  if (DoneWritingDeclsAndTypes && !wasDeclEmitted(LocalD))
3999  continue;
4000 
4001  return false;
4002  }
4003 
4004  return true;
4005 }
4006 
4007 void
4008 ASTWriter::GenerateNameLookupTable(const DeclContext *ConstDC,
4009  llvm::SmallVectorImpl<char> &LookupTable) {
4010  assert(!ConstDC->hasLazyLocalLexicalLookups() &&
4011  !ConstDC->hasLazyExternalLexicalLookups() &&
4012  "must call buildLookups first");
4013 
4014  // FIXME: We need to build the lookups table, which is logically const.
4015  auto *DC = const_cast<DeclContext*>(ConstDC);
4016  assert(DC == DC->getPrimaryContext() && "only primary DC has lookup table");
4017 
4018  // Create the on-disk hash table representation.
4019  MultiOnDiskHashTableGenerator<reader::ASTDeclContextNameLookupTrait,
4020  ASTDeclContextNameLookupTrait> Generator;
4021  ASTDeclContextNameLookupTrait Trait(*this);
4022 
4023  // The first step is to collect the declaration names which we need to
4024  // serialize into the name lookup table, and to collect them in a stable
4025  // order.
4026  SmallVector<DeclarationName, 16> Names;
4027 
4028  // We also build up small sets of the constructor and conversion function
4029  // names which are visible.
4030  llvm::SmallPtrSet<DeclarationName, 8> ConstructorNameSet, ConversionNameSet;
4031 
4032  for (auto &Lookup : *DC->buildLookup()) {
4033  auto &Name = Lookup.first;
4034  auto &Result = Lookup.second;
4035 
4036  // If there are no local declarations in our lookup result, we
4037  // don't need to write an entry for the name at all. If we can't
4038  // write out a lookup set without performing more deserialization,
4039  // just skip this entry.
4040  //
4041  // Also in reduced BMI, we'd like to avoid writing unreachable
4042  // declarations in GMF, so we need to avoid writing declarations
4043  // that entirely external or unreachable.
4044  //
4045  // FIMXE: It looks sufficient to test
4046  // isLookupResultEntirelyExternalOrUnreachable here. But due to bug we have
4047  // to test isLookupResultExternal here. See
4048  // https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/61065 for details.
4049  if ((GeneratingReducedBMI || isLookupResultExternal(Result, DC)) &&
4050  isLookupResultEntirelyExternalOrUnreachable(Result, DC))
4051  continue;
4052 
4053  // We also skip empty results. If any of the results could be external and
4054  // the currently available results are empty, then all of the results are
4055  // external and we skip it above. So the only way we get here with an empty
4056  // results is when no results could have been external *and* we have
4057  // external results.
4058  //
4059  // FIXME: While we might want to start emitting on-disk entries for negative
4060  // lookups into a decl context as an optimization, today we *have* to skip
4061  // them because there are names with empty lookup results in decl contexts
4062  // which we can't emit in any stable ordering: we lookup constructors and
4063  // conversion functions in the enclosing namespace scope creating empty
4064  // results for them. This in almost certainly a bug in Clang's name lookup,
4065  // but that is likely to be hard or impossible to fix and so we tolerate it
4066  // here by omitting lookups with empty results.
4067  if (Lookup.second.getLookupResult().empty())
4068  continue;
4069 
4070  switch (Lookup.first.getNameKind()) {
4071  default:
4072  Names.push_back(Lookup.first);
4073  break;
4074 
4075  case DeclarationName::CXXConstructorName:
4076  assert(isa<CXXRecordDecl>(DC) &&
4077  "Cannot have a constructor name outside of a class!");
4078  ConstructorNameSet.insert(Name);
4079  break;
4080 
4081  case DeclarationName::CXXConversionFunctionName:
4082  assert(isa<CXXRecordDecl>(DC) &&
4083  "Cannot have a conversion function name outside of a class!");
4084  ConversionNameSet.insert(Name);
4085  break;
4086  }
4087  }
4088 
4089  // Sort the names into a stable order.
4090  llvm::sort(Names);
4091 
4092  if (auto *D = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(DC)) {
4093  // We need to establish an ordering of constructor and conversion function
4094  // names, and they don't have an intrinsic ordering.
4095 
4096  // First we try the easy case by forming the current context's constructor
4097  // name and adding that name first. This is a very useful optimization to
4098  // avoid walking the lexical declarations in many cases, and it also
4099  // handles the only case where a constructor name can come from some other
4100  // lexical context -- when that name is an implicit constructor merged from
4101  // another declaration in the redecl chain. Any non-implicit constructor or
4102  // conversion function which doesn't occur in all the lexical contexts
4103  // would be an ODR violation.
4104  auto ImplicitCtorName = Context->DeclarationNames.getCXXConstructorName(
4105  Context->getCanonicalType(Context->getRecordType(D)));
4106  if (ConstructorNameSet.erase(ImplicitCtorName))
4107  Names.push_back(ImplicitCtorName);
4108 
4109  // If we still have constructors or conversion functions, we walk all the
4110  // names in the decl and add the constructors and conversion functions
4111  // which are visible in the order they lexically occur within the context.
4112  if (!ConstructorNameSet.empty() || !ConversionNameSet.empty())
4113  for (Decl *ChildD : cast<CXXRecordDecl>(DC)->decls())
4114  if (auto *ChildND = dyn_cast<NamedDecl>(ChildD)) {
4115  auto Name = ChildND->getDeclName();
4116  switch (Name.getNameKind()) {
4117  default:
4118  continue;
4119 
4120  case DeclarationName::CXXConstructorName:
4121  if (ConstructorNameSet.erase(Name))
4122  Names.push_back(Name);
4123  break;
4124 
4125  case DeclarationName::CXXConversionFunctionName:
4126  if (ConversionNameSet.erase(Name))
4127  Names.push_back(Name);
4128  break;
4129  }
4130 
4131  if (ConstructorNameSet.empty() && ConversionNameSet.empty())
4132  break;
4133  }
4134 
4135  assert(ConstructorNameSet.empty() && "Failed to find all of the visible "
4136  "constructors by walking all the "
4137  "lexical members of the context.");
4138  assert(ConversionNameSet.empty() && "Failed to find all of the visible "
4139  "conversion functions by walking all "
4140  "the lexical members of the context.");
4141  }
4142 
4143  // Next we need to do a lookup with each name into this decl context to fully
4144  // populate any results from external sources. We don't actually use the
4145  // results of these lookups because we only want to use the results after all
4146  // results have been loaded and the pointers into them will be stable.
4147  for (auto &Name : Names)
4148  DC->lookup(Name);
4149 
4150  // Now we need to insert the results for each name into the hash table. For
4151  // constructor names and conversion function names, we actually need to merge
4152  // all of the results for them into one list of results each and insert
4153  // those.
4154  SmallVector<NamedDecl *, 8> ConstructorDecls;
4155  SmallVector<NamedDecl *, 8> ConversionDecls;
4156 
4157  // Now loop over the names, either inserting them or appending for the two
4158  // special cases.
4159  for (auto &Name : Names) {
4160  DeclContext::lookup_result Result = DC->noload_lookup(Name);
4161 
4162  switch (Name.getNameKind()) {
4163  default:
4164  Generator.insert(Name, Trait.getData(Result), Trait);
4165  break;
4166 
4167  case DeclarationName::CXXConstructorName:
4168  ConstructorDecls.append(Result.begin(), Result.end());
4169  break;
4170 
4171  case DeclarationName::CXXConversionFunctionName:
4172  ConversionDecls.append(Result.begin(), Result.end());
4173  break;
4174  }
4175  }
4176 
4177  // Handle our two special cases if we ended up having any. We arbitrarily use
4178  // the first declaration's name here because the name itself isn't part of
4179  // the key, only the kind of name is used.
4180  if (!ConstructorDecls.empty())
4181  Generator.insert(ConstructorDecls.front()->getDeclName(),
4182  Trait.getData(ConstructorDecls), Trait);
4183  if (!ConversionDecls.empty())
4184  Generator.insert(ConversionDecls.front()->getDeclName(),
4185  Trait.getData(ConversionDecls), Trait);
4186 
4187  // Create the on-disk hash table. Also emit the existing imported and
4188  // merged table if there is one.
4189  auto *Lookups = Chain ? Chain->getLoadedLookupTables(DC) : nullptr;
4190  Generator.emit(LookupTable, Trait, Lookups ? &Lookups->Table : nullptr);
4191 }
4192 
4193 /// Write the block containing all of the declaration IDs
4194 /// visible from the given DeclContext.
4195 ///
4196 /// \returns the offset of the DECL_CONTEXT_VISIBLE block within the
4197 /// bitstream, or 0 if no block was written.
4198 uint64_t ASTWriter::WriteDeclContextVisibleBlock(ASTContext &Context,
4199  DeclContext *DC) {
4200  // If we imported a key declaration of this namespace, write the visible
4201  // lookup results as an update record for it rather than including them
4202  // on this declaration. We will only look at key declarations on reload.
4203  if (isa<NamespaceDecl>(DC) && Chain &&
4204  Chain->getKeyDeclaration(cast<Decl>(DC))->isFromASTFile()) {
4205  // Only do this once, for the first local declaration of the namespace.
4206  for (auto *Prev = cast<NamespaceDecl>(DC)->getPreviousDecl(); Prev;
4207  Prev = Prev->getPreviousDecl())
4208  if (!Prev->isFromASTFile())
4209  return 0;
4210 
4211  // Note that we need to emit an update record for the primary context.
4212  UpdatedDeclContexts.insert(DC->getPrimaryContext());
4213 
4214  // Make sure all visible decls are written. They will be recorded later. We
4215  // do this using a side data structure so we can sort the names into
4216  // a deterministic order.
4217  StoredDeclsMap *Map = DC->getPrimaryContext()->buildLookup();
4218  SmallVector<std::pair<DeclarationName, DeclContext::lookup_result>, 16>
4219  LookupResults;
4220  if (Map) {
4221  LookupResults.reserve(Map->size());
4222  for (auto &Entry : *Map)
4223  LookupResults.push_back(
4224  std::make_pair(Entry.first, Entry.second.getLookupResult()));
4225  }
4226 
4227  llvm::sort(LookupResults, llvm::less_first());
4228  for (auto &NameAndResult : LookupResults) {
4229  DeclarationName Name = NameAndResult.first;
4230  DeclContext::lookup_result Result = NameAndResult.second;
4231  if (Name.getNameKind() == DeclarationName::CXXConstructorName ||
4232  Name.getNameKind() == DeclarationName::CXXConversionFunctionName) {
4233  // We have to work around a name lookup bug here where negative lookup
4234  // results for these names get cached in namespace lookup tables (these
4235  // names should never be looked up in a namespace).
4236  assert(Result.empty() && "Cannot have a constructor or conversion "
4237  "function name in a namespace!");
4238  continue;
4239  }
4240 
4241  for (NamedDecl *ND : Result) {
4242  if (ND->isFromASTFile())
4243  continue;
4244 
4245  if (DoneWritingDeclsAndTypes && !wasDeclEmitted(ND))
4246  continue;
4247 
4248  GetDeclRef(ND);
4249  }
4250  }
4251 
4252  return 0;
4253  }
4254 
4255  if (DC->getPrimaryContext() != DC)
4256  return 0;
4257 
4258  // Skip contexts which don't support name lookup.
4259  if (!DC->isLookupContext())
4260  return 0;
4261 
4262  // If not in C++, we perform name lookup for the translation unit via the
4263  // IdentifierInfo chains, don't bother to build a visible-declarations table.
4264  if (DC->isTranslationUnit() && !Context.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
4265  return 0;
4266 
4267  // Serialize the contents of the mapping used for lookup. Note that,
4268  // although we have two very different code paths, the serialized
4269  // representation is the same for both cases: a declaration name,
4270  // followed by a size, followed by references to the visible
4271  // declarations that have that name.
4272  uint64_t Offset = Stream.GetCurrentBitNo();
4273  StoredDeclsMap *Map = DC->buildLookup();
4274  if (!Map || Map->empty())
4275  return 0;
4276 
4277  // Create the on-disk hash table in a buffer.
4278  SmallString<4096> LookupTable;
4279  GenerateNameLookupTable(DC, LookupTable);
4280 
4281  // Write the lookup table
4282  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {DECL_CONTEXT_VISIBLE};
4283  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(DeclContextVisibleLookupAbbrev, Record,
4284  LookupTable);
4285  ++NumVisibleDeclContexts;
4286  return Offset;
4287 }
4288 
4289 /// Write an UPDATE_VISIBLE block for the given context.
4290 ///
4291 /// UPDATE_VISIBLE blocks contain the declarations that are added to an existing
4292 /// DeclContext in a dependent AST file. As such, they only exist for the TU
4293 /// (in C++), for namespaces, and for classes with forward-declared unscoped
4294 /// enumeration members (in C++11).
4295 void ASTWriter::WriteDeclContextVisibleUpdate(const DeclContext *DC) {
4296  StoredDeclsMap *Map = DC->getLookupPtr();
4297  if (!Map || Map->empty())
4298  return;
4299 
4300  // Create the on-disk hash table in a buffer.
4301  SmallString<4096> LookupTable;
4302  GenerateNameLookupTable(DC, LookupTable);
4303 
4304  // If we're updating a namespace, select a key declaration as the key for the
4305  // update record; those are the only ones that will be checked on reload.
4306  if (isa<NamespaceDecl>(DC))
4307  DC = cast<DeclContext>(Chain->getKeyDeclaration(cast<Decl>(DC)));
4308 
4309  // Write the lookup table
4310  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {UPDATE_VISIBLE, getDeclID(cast<Decl>(DC))};
4311  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(UpdateVisibleAbbrev, Record, LookupTable);
4312 }

4315 void ASTWriter::WriteFPPragmaOptions(const FPOptionsOverride &Opts) {
4316  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {Opts.getAsOpaqueInt()};
4317  Stream.EmitRecord(FP_PRAGMA_OPTIONS, Record);

4320 /// Write an OPENCL_EXTENSIONS block for the given OpenCLOptions.
4321 void ASTWriter::WriteOpenCLExtensions(Sema &SemaRef) {
4322  if (!SemaRef.Context.getLangOpts().OpenCL)
4323  return;
4324 
4325  const OpenCLOptions &Opts = SemaRef.getOpenCLOptions();
4326  RecordData Record;
4327  for (const auto &I:Opts.OptMap) {
4328  AddString(I.getKey(), Record);
4329  auto V = I.getValue();
4330  Record.push_back(V.Supported ? 1 : 0);
4331  Record.push_back(V.Enabled ? 1 : 0);
4332  Record.push_back(V.WithPragma ? 1 : 0);
4333  Record.push_back(V.Avail);
4334  Record.push_back(V.Core);
4335  Record.push_back(V.Opt);
4336  }
4337  Stream.EmitRecord(OPENCL_EXTENSIONS, Record);
4338 }

4345 
4346 void ASTWriter::WriteObjCCategories() {
4347  SmallVector<ObjCCategoriesInfo, 2> CategoriesMap;
4348  RecordData Categories;
4349 
4350  for (unsigned I = 0, N = ObjCClassesWithCategories.size(); I != N; ++I) {
4351  unsigned Size = 0;
4352  unsigned StartIndex = Categories.size();
4353 
4354  ObjCInterfaceDecl *Class = ObjCClassesWithCategories[I];
4355 
4356  // Allocate space for the size.
4357  Categories.push_back(0);
4358 
4359  // Add the categories.
4360  for (ObjCInterfaceDecl::known_categories_iterator
4361  Cat = Class->known_categories_begin(),
4362  CatEnd = Class->known_categories_end();
4363  Cat != CatEnd; ++Cat, ++Size) {
4364  assert(getDeclID(*Cat) != 0 && "Bogus category");
4365  AddDeclRef(*Cat, Categories);
4366  }
4367 
4368  // Update the size.
4369  Categories[StartIndex] = Size;
4370 
4371  // Record this interface -> category map.
4372  ObjCCategoriesInfo CatInfo = { getDeclID(Class), StartIndex };
4373  CategoriesMap.push_back(CatInfo);
4374  }
4375 
4376  // Sort the categories map by the definition ID, since the reader will be
4377  // performing binary searches on this information.
4378  llvm::array_pod_sort(CategoriesMap.begin(), CategoriesMap.end());
4379 
4380  // Emit the categories map.
4381  using namespace llvm;
4382 
4383  auto Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
4384  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(OBJC_CATEGORIES_MAP));
4385  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 6)); // # of entries
4386  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob));
4387  unsigned AbbrevID = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
4388 
4389  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {OBJC_CATEGORIES_MAP, CategoriesMap.size()};
4390  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(AbbrevID, Record,
4391  reinterpret_cast<char *>(CategoriesMap.data()),
4392  CategoriesMap.size() * sizeof(ObjCCategoriesInfo));
4393 
4394  // Emit the category lists.
4395  Stream.EmitRecord(OBJC_CATEGORIES, Categories);
4396 }
4397 
4398 void ASTWriter::WriteLateParsedTemplates(Sema &SemaRef) {
4399  Sema::LateParsedTemplateMapT &LPTMap = SemaRef.LateParsedTemplateMap;
4400 
4401  if (LPTMap.empty())
4402  return;
4403 
4404  RecordData Record;
4405  for (auto &LPTMapEntry : LPTMap) {
4406  const FunctionDecl *FD = LPTMapEntry.first;
4407  LateParsedTemplate &LPT = *LPTMapEntry.second;
4408  AddDeclRef(FD, Record);
4409  AddDeclRef(LPT.D, Record);
4410  Record.push_back(LPT.FPO.getAsOpaqueInt());
4411  Record.push_back(LPT.Toks.size());
4412 
4413  for (const auto &Tok : LPT.Toks) {
4414  AddToken(Tok, Record);
4415  }
4416  }
4417  Stream.EmitRecord(LATE_PARSED_TEMPLATE, Record);
4418 }

4444 /// Write the state of 'pragma align/pack' at the end of the module.
4445 void ASTWriter::WritePackPragmaOptions(Sema &SemaRef) {
4446  // Don't serialize pragma align/pack state for modules, since it should only
4447  // take effect on a per-submodule basis.
4448  if (WritingModule)
4449  return;
4450 
4451  RecordData Record;
4452  AddAlignPackInfo(SemaRef.AlignPackStack.CurrentValue, Record);
4453  AddSourceLocation(SemaRef.AlignPackStack.CurrentPragmaLocation, Record);
4454  Record.push_back(SemaRef.AlignPackStack.Stack.size());
4455  for (const auto &StackEntry : SemaRef.AlignPackStack.Stack) {
4456  AddAlignPackInfo(StackEntry.Value, Record);
4457  AddSourceLocation(StackEntry.PragmaLocation, Record);
4458  AddSourceLocation(StackEntry.PragmaPushLocation, Record);
4459  AddString(StackEntry.StackSlotLabel, Record);
4460  }
4461  Stream.EmitRecord(ALIGN_PACK_PRAGMA_OPTIONS, Record);
4462 }
4463 
4464 /// Write the state of 'pragma float_control' at the end of the module.
4465 void ASTWriter::WriteFloatControlPragmaOptions(Sema &SemaRef) {
4466  // Don't serialize pragma float_control state for modules,
4467  // since it should only take effect on a per-submodule basis.
4468  if (WritingModule)
4469  return;
4470 
4471  RecordData Record;
4472  Record.push_back(SemaRef.FpPragmaStack.CurrentValue.getAsOpaqueInt());
4473  AddSourceLocation(SemaRef.FpPragmaStack.CurrentPragmaLocation, Record);
4474  Record.push_back(SemaRef.FpPragmaStack.Stack.size());
4475  for (const auto &StackEntry : SemaRef.FpPragmaStack.Stack) {
4476  Record.push_back(StackEntry.Value.getAsOpaqueInt());
4477  AddSourceLocation(StackEntry.PragmaLocation, Record);
4478  AddSourceLocation(StackEntry.PragmaPushLocation, Record);
4479  AddString(StackEntry.StackSlotLabel, Record);
4480  }
4481  Stream.EmitRecord(FLOAT_CONTROL_PRAGMA_OPTIONS, Record);
4482 }
4483 
4484 void ASTWriter::WriteModuleFileExtension(Sema &SemaRef,
4485  ModuleFileExtensionWriter &Writer) {
4486  // Enter the extension block.
4487  Stream.EnterSubblock(EXTENSION_BLOCK_ID, 4);
4488 
4489  // Emit the metadata record abbreviation.
4490  auto Abv = std::make_shared<llvm::BitCodeAbbrev>();
4491  Abv->Add(llvm::BitCodeAbbrevOp(EXTENSION_METADATA));
4492  Abv->Add(llvm::BitCodeAbbrevOp(llvm::BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 6));
4493  Abv->Add(llvm::BitCodeAbbrevOp(llvm::BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 6));
4494  Abv->Add(llvm::BitCodeAbbrevOp(llvm::BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 6));
4495  Abv->Add(llvm::BitCodeAbbrevOp(llvm::BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 6));
4496  Abv->Add(llvm::BitCodeAbbrevOp(llvm::BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob));
4497  unsigned Abbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abv));
4498 
4499  // Emit the metadata record.
4500  RecordData Record;
4501  auto Metadata = Writer.getExtension()->getExtensionMetadata();
4502  Record.push_back(EXTENSION_METADATA);
4503  Record.push_back(Metadata.MajorVersion);
4504  Record.push_back(Metadata.MinorVersion);
4505  Record.push_back(Metadata.BlockName.size());
4506  Record.push_back(Metadata.UserInfo.size());
4507  SmallString<64> Buffer;
4508  Buffer += Metadata.BlockName;
4509  Buffer += Metadata.UserInfo;
4510  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(Abbrev, Record, Buffer);
4511 
4512  // Emit the contents of the extension block.
4513  Writer.writeExtensionContents(SemaRef, Stream);
4514 
4515  // Exit the extension block.
4516  Stream.ExitBlock();
4517 }

4523 void ASTRecordWriter::AddAttr(const Attr *A) {
4524  auto &Record = *this;
4525  // FIXME: Clang can't handle the serialization/deserialization of
4526  // preferred_name properly now. See
4527  // https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/56490 for example.
4528  if (!A || (isa<PreferredNameAttr>(A) &&
4529  Writer->isWritingStdCXXNamedModules()))
4530  return Record.push_back(0);
4531 
4532  Record.push_back(A->getKind() + 1); // FIXME: stable encoding, target attrs
4533 
4534  Record.AddIdentifierRef(A->getAttrName());
4535  Record.AddIdentifierRef(A->getScopeName());
4536  Record.AddSourceRange(A->getRange());
4537  Record.AddSourceLocation(A->getScopeLoc());
4538  Record.push_back(A->getParsedKind());
4539  Record.push_back(A->getSyntax());
4540  Record.push_back(A->getAttributeSpellingListIndexRaw());
4541  Record.push_back(A->isRegularKeywordAttribute());
4542 
4543 #include "clang/Serialization/AttrPCHWrite.inc"
4544 }
4545 
4546 /// Emit the list of attributes to the specified record.
4547 void ASTRecordWriter::AddAttributes(ArrayRef<const Attr *> Attrs) {
4548  push_back(Attrs.size());
4549  for (const auto *A : Attrs)
4550  AddAttr(A);
4551 }
4552 
4553 void ASTWriter::AddToken(const Token &Tok, RecordDataImpl &Record) {
4554  AddSourceLocation(Tok.getLocation(), Record);
4555  // FIXME: Should translate token kind to a stable encoding.
4556  Record.push_back(Tok.getKind());
4557  // FIXME: Should translate token flags to a stable encoding.
4558  Record.push_back(Tok.getFlags());
4559 
4560  if (Tok.isAnnotation()) {
4561  AddSourceLocation(Tok.getAnnotationEndLoc(), Record);
4562  switch (Tok.getKind()) {
4563  case tok::annot_pragma_loop_hint: {
4564  auto *Info = static_cast<PragmaLoopHintInfo *>(Tok.getAnnotationValue());
4565  AddToken(Info->PragmaName, Record);
4566  AddToken(Info->Option, Record);
4567  Record.push_back(Info->Toks.size());
4568  for (const auto &T : Info->Toks)
4569  AddToken(T, Record);
4570  break;
4571  }
4572  case tok::annot_pragma_pack: {
4573  auto *Info =
4574  static_cast<Sema::PragmaPackInfo *>(Tok.getAnnotationValue());
4575  Record.push_back(static_cast<unsigned>(Info->Action));
4576  AddString(Info->SlotLabel, Record);
4577  AddToken(Info->Alignment, Record);
4578  break;
4579  }
4580  // Some annotation tokens do not use the PtrData field.
4581  case tok::annot_pragma_openmp:
4582  case tok::annot_pragma_openmp_end:
4583  case tok::annot_pragma_unused:
4584  case tok::annot_pragma_openacc:
4585  case tok::annot_pragma_openacc_end:
4586  break;
4587  default:
4588  llvm_unreachable("missing serialization code for annotation token");
4589  }
4590  } else {
4591  Record.push_back(Tok.getLength());
4592  // FIXME: When reading literal tokens, reconstruct the literal pointer if it
4593  // is needed.
4594  AddIdentifierRef(Tok.getIdentifierInfo(), Record);
4595  }
4596 }
4597 
4598 void ASTWriter::AddString(StringRef Str, RecordDataImpl &Record) {
4599  Record.push_back(Str.size());
4600  Record.insert(Record.end(), Str.begin(), Str.end());
4601 }
4602 
4603 bool ASTWriter::PreparePathForOutput(SmallVectorImpl<char> &Path) {
4604  assert(Context && "should have context when outputting path");
4605 
4606  // Leave special file names as they are.
4607  StringRef PathStr(Path.data(), Path.size());
4608  if (PathStr == "<built-in>" || PathStr == "<command line>")
4609  return false;
4610 
4611  bool Changed =
4612  cleanPathForOutput(Context->getSourceManager().getFileManager(), Path);
4613 
4614  // Remove a prefix to make the path relative, if relevant.
4615  const char *PathBegin = Path.data();
4616  const char *PathPtr =
4617  adjustFilenameForRelocatableAST(PathBegin, BaseDirectory);
4618  if (PathPtr != PathBegin) {
4619  Path.erase(Path.begin(), Path.begin() + (PathPtr - PathBegin));
4620  Changed = true;
4621  }
4622 
4623  return Changed;
4624 }
4625 
4626 void ASTWriter::AddPath(StringRef Path, RecordDataImpl &Record) {
4627  SmallString<128> FilePath(Path);
4628  PreparePathForOutput(FilePath);
4629  AddString(FilePath, Record);
4630 }
4631 
4632 void ASTWriter::EmitRecordWithPath(unsigned Abbrev, RecordDataRef Record,
4633  StringRef Path) {
4634  SmallString<128> FilePath(Path);
4635  PreparePathForOutput(FilePath);
4636  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(Abbrev, Record, FilePath);
4637 }

4639 void ASTWriter::AddVersionTuple(const VersionTuple &Version,
4640  RecordDataImpl &Record) {
4641  Record.push_back(Version.getMajor());
4642  if (std::optional<unsigned> Minor = Version.getMinor())
4643  Record.push_back(*Minor + 1);
4644  else
4645  Record.push_back(0);
4646  if (std::optional<unsigned> Subminor = Version.getSubminor())
4647  Record.push_back(*Subminor + 1);
4648  else
4649  Record.push_back(0);
4650 }

4652 /// Note that the identifier II occurs at the given offset
4653 /// within the identifier table.
4654 void ASTWriter::SetIdentifierOffset(const IdentifierInfo *II, uint32_t Offset) {
4655  IdentID ID = IdentifierIDs[II];
4656  // Only store offsets new to this AST file. Other identifier names are looked
4657  // up earlier in the chain and thus don't need an offset.
4658  if (ID >= FirstIdentID)
4659  IdentifierOffsets[ID - FirstIdentID] = Offset;
4660 }
4661 
4662 /// Note that the selector Sel occurs at the given offset
4663 /// within the method pool/selector table.
4664 void ASTWriter::SetSelectorOffset(Selector Sel, uint32_t Offset) {
4665  unsigned ID = SelectorIDs[Sel];
4666  assert(ID && "Unknown selector");
4667  // Don't record offsets for selectors that are also available in a different
4668  // file.
4669  if (ID < FirstSelectorID)
4670  return;
4671  SelectorOffsets[ID - FirstSelectorID] = Offset;
4672 }

4701 ASTFileSignature ASTWriter::WriteAST(Sema &SemaRef, StringRef OutputFile,
4702  Module *WritingModule, StringRef isysroot,
4703  bool ShouldCacheASTInMemory) {
4704  llvm::TimeTraceScope scope("WriteAST", OutputFile);
4705  WritingAST = true;
4706 
4707  ASTHasCompilerErrors =
4708  SemaRef.PP.getDiagnostics().hasUncompilableErrorOccurred();
4709 
4710  // Emit the file header.
4711  Stream.Emit((unsigned)'C', 8);
4712  Stream.Emit((unsigned)'P', 8);
4713  Stream.Emit((unsigned)'C', 8);
4714  Stream.Emit((unsigned)'H', 8);
4715 
4716  WriteBlockInfoBlock();
4717 
4718  Context = &SemaRef.Context;
4719  PP = &SemaRef.PP;
4720  this->WritingModule = WritingModule;
4721  ASTFileSignature Signature = WriteASTCore(SemaRef, isysroot, WritingModule);
4722  Context = nullptr;
4723  PP = nullptr;
4724  this->WritingModule = nullptr;
4725  this->BaseDirectory.clear();
4726 
4727  WritingAST = false;
4728  if (ShouldCacheASTInMemory) {
4729  // Construct MemoryBuffer and update buffer manager.
4730  ModuleCache.addBuiltPCM(OutputFile,
4731  llvm::MemoryBuffer::getMemBufferCopy(
4732  StringRef(Buffer.begin(), Buffer.size())));
4733  }
4734  return Signature;
4735 }

4739  for (typename Vector::iterator I = Vec.begin(nullptr, true), E = Vec.end();
4740  I != E; ++I) {
4741  Writer.GetDeclRef(*I);
4742  }
4743 }
