4747  ASTWriter::RecordData &Record) {
4748  for (typename Vector::iterator I = Vec.begin(nullptr, true), E = Vec.end();
4749  I != E; ++I) {
4750  Writer.AddEmittedDeclRef(*I, Record);
4751  }
4752 }
4753 
4754 void ASTWriter::computeNonAffectingInputFiles() {
4755  SourceManager &SrcMgr = PP->getSourceManager();
4756  unsigned N = SrcMgr.local_sloc_entry_size();
4757 
4758  IsSLocAffecting.resize(N, true);
4759 
4760  if (!WritingModule)
4761  return;
4762 
4763  auto AffectingModuleMaps = GetAffectingModuleMaps(*PP, WritingModule);
4764 
4765  unsigned FileIDAdjustment = 0;
4766  unsigned OffsetAdjustment = 0;
4767 
4768  NonAffectingFileIDAdjustments.reserve(N);
4769  NonAffectingOffsetAdjustments.reserve(N);
4770 
4771  NonAffectingFileIDAdjustments.push_back(FileIDAdjustment);
4772  NonAffectingOffsetAdjustments.push_back(OffsetAdjustment);
4773 
4774  for (unsigned I = 1; I != N; ++I) {
4775  const SrcMgr::SLocEntry *SLoc = &SrcMgr.getLocalSLocEntry(I);
4776  FileID FID = FileID::get(I);
4777  assert(&SrcMgr.getSLocEntry(FID) == SLoc);
4778 
4779  if (!SLoc->isFile())
4780  continue;
4781  const SrcMgr::FileInfo &File = SLoc->getFile();
4782  const SrcMgr::ContentCache *Cache = &File.getContentCache();
4783  if (!Cache->OrigEntry)
4784  continue;
4785 
4786  // Don't prune anything other than module maps.
4787  if (!isModuleMap(File.getFileCharacteristic()))
4788  continue;
4789 
4790  // Don't prune module maps if all are guaranteed to be affecting.
4791  if (!AffectingModuleMaps)
4792  continue;
4793 
4794  // Don't prune module maps that are affecting.
4795  if (llvm::is_contained(*AffectingModuleMaps, *Cache->OrigEntry))
4796  continue;
4797 
4798  IsSLocAffecting[I] = false;
4799 
4800  FileIDAdjustment += 1;
4801  // Even empty files take up one element in the offset table.
4802  OffsetAdjustment += SrcMgr.getFileIDSize(FID) + 1;
4803 
4804  // If the previous file was non-affecting as well, just extend its entry
4805  // with our information.
4806  if (!NonAffectingFileIDs.empty() &&
4807  NonAffectingFileIDs.back().ID == FID.ID - 1) {
4808  NonAffectingFileIDs.back() = FID;
4809  NonAffectingRanges.back().setEnd(SrcMgr.getLocForEndOfFile(FID));
4810  NonAffectingFileIDAdjustments.back() = FileIDAdjustment;
4811  NonAffectingOffsetAdjustments.back() = OffsetAdjustment;
4812  continue;
4813  }
4814 
4815  NonAffectingFileIDs.push_back(FID);
4816  NonAffectingRanges.emplace_back(SrcMgr.getLocForStartOfFile(FID),
4817  SrcMgr.getLocForEndOfFile(FID));
4818  NonAffectingFileIDAdjustments.push_back(FileIDAdjustment);
4819  NonAffectingOffsetAdjustments.push_back(OffsetAdjustment);
4820  }
4821 
4822  if (!PP->getHeaderSearchInfo().getHeaderSearchOpts().ModulesIncludeVFSUsage)
4823  return;
4824 
4825  FileManager &FileMgr = PP->getFileManager();
4826  FileMgr.trackVFSUsage(true);
4827  // Lookup the paths in the VFS to trigger `-ivfsoverlay` usage tracking.
4828  for (StringRef Path :
4829  PP->getHeaderSearchInfo().getHeaderSearchOpts().VFSOverlayFiles)
4830  FileMgr.getVirtualFileSystem().exists(Path);
4831  for (unsigned I = 1; I != N; ++I) {
4832  if (IsSLocAffecting[I]) {
4833  const SrcMgr::SLocEntry *SLoc = &SrcMgr.getLocalSLocEntry(I);
4834  if (!SLoc->isFile())
4835  continue;
4836  const SrcMgr::FileInfo &File = SLoc->getFile();
4837  const SrcMgr::ContentCache *Cache = &File.getContentCache();
4838  if (!Cache->OrigEntry)
4839  continue;
4840  FileMgr.getVirtualFileSystem().exists(
4841  Cache->OrigEntry->getNameAsRequested());
4842  }
4843  }
4844  FileMgr.trackVFSUsage(false);
4845 }
4846 
4847 void ASTWriter::PrepareWritingSpecialDecls(Sema &SemaRef) {
4848  ASTContext &Context = SemaRef.Context;
4849 
4850  bool isModule = WritingModule != nullptr;
4851 
4852  // Set up predefined declaration IDs.
4853  auto RegisterPredefDecl = [&] (Decl *D, PredefinedDeclIDs ID) {
4854  if (D) {
4855  assert(D->isCanonicalDecl() && "predefined decl is not canonical");
4856  DeclIDs[D] = ID;
4857  }
4858  };
4859  RegisterPredefDecl(Context.getTranslationUnitDecl(),
4860  PREDEF_DECL_TRANSLATION_UNIT_ID);
4861  RegisterPredefDecl(Context.ObjCIdDecl, PREDEF_DECL_OBJC_ID_ID);
4862  RegisterPredefDecl(Context.ObjCSelDecl, PREDEF_DECL_OBJC_SEL_ID);
4863  RegisterPredefDecl(Context.ObjCClassDecl, PREDEF_DECL_OBJC_CLASS_ID);
4864  RegisterPredefDecl(Context.ObjCProtocolClassDecl,
4865  PREDEF_DECL_OBJC_PROTOCOL_ID);
4866  RegisterPredefDecl(Context.Int128Decl, PREDEF_DECL_INT_128_ID);
4867  RegisterPredefDecl(Context.UInt128Decl, PREDEF_DECL_UNSIGNED_INT_128_ID);
4868  RegisterPredefDecl(Context.ObjCInstanceTypeDecl,
4869  PREDEF_DECL_OBJC_INSTANCETYPE_ID);
4870  RegisterPredefDecl(Context.BuiltinVaListDecl, PREDEF_DECL_BUILTIN_VA_LIST_ID);
4871  RegisterPredefDecl(Context.VaListTagDecl, PREDEF_DECL_VA_LIST_TAG);
4872  RegisterPredefDecl(Context.BuiltinMSVaListDecl,
4873  PREDEF_DECL_BUILTIN_MS_VA_LIST_ID);
4874  RegisterPredefDecl(Context.MSGuidTagDecl,
4875  PREDEF_DECL_BUILTIN_MS_GUID_ID);
4876  RegisterPredefDecl(Context.ExternCContext, PREDEF_DECL_EXTERN_C_CONTEXT_ID);
4877  RegisterPredefDecl(Context.MakeIntegerSeqDecl,
4878  PREDEF_DECL_MAKE_INTEGER_SEQ_ID);
4879  RegisterPredefDecl(Context.CFConstantStringTypeDecl,
4880  PREDEF_DECL_CF_CONSTANT_STRING_ID);
4881  RegisterPredefDecl(Context.CFConstantStringTagDecl,
4882  PREDEF_DECL_CF_CONSTANT_STRING_TAG_ID);
4883  RegisterPredefDecl(Context.TypePackElementDecl,
4884  PREDEF_DECL_TYPE_PACK_ELEMENT_ID);
4885 
4886  const TranslationUnitDecl *TU = Context.getTranslationUnitDecl();
4887 
4888  // Force all top level declarations to be emitted.
4889  //
4890  // We start emitting top level declarations from the module purview to
4891  // implement the eliding unreachable declaration feature.
4892  for (const auto *D : TU->noload_decls()) {
4893  if (D->isFromASTFile())
4894  continue;
4895 
4896  if (GeneratingReducedBMI) {
4897  if (D->isFromExplicitGlobalModule())
4898  continue;
4899 
4900  // Don't force emitting static entities.
4901  //
4902  // Technically, all static entities shouldn't be in reduced BMI. The
4903  // language also specifies that the program exposes TU-local entities
4904  // is ill-formed. However, in practice, there are a lot of projects
4905  // uses `static inline` in the headers. So we can't get rid of all
4906  // static entities in reduced BMI now.
4907  if (auto *ND = dyn_cast<NamedDecl>(D);
4908  ND && ND->getFormalLinkage() == Linkage::Internal)
4909  continue;
4910  }
4911 
4912  GetDeclRef(D);
4913  }
4914 
4915  if (GeneratingReducedBMI)
4916  return;
4917 
4918  // Writing all of the tentative definitions in this file, in
4919  // TentativeDefinitions order. Generally, this record will be empty for
4920  // headers.
4921  RecordData TentativeDefinitions;
4922  AddLazyVectorDecls(*this, SemaRef.TentativeDefinitions);
4923 
4924  // Writing all of the file scoped decls in this file.
4925  if (!isModule)
4926  AddLazyVectorDecls(*this, SemaRef.UnusedFileScopedDecls);
4927 
4928  // Writing all of the delegating constructors we still need
4929  // to resolve.
4930  if (!isModule)
4931  AddLazyVectorDecls(*this, SemaRef.DelegatingCtorDecls);
4932 
4933  // Writing all of the ext_vector declarations.
4934  AddLazyVectorDecls(*this, SemaRef.ExtVectorDecls);
4935 
4936  // Writing all of the VTable uses information.
4937  if (!SemaRef.VTableUses.empty())
4938  for (unsigned I = 0, N = SemaRef.VTableUses.size(); I != N; ++I)
4939  GetDeclRef(SemaRef.VTableUses[I].first);
4940 
4941  // Writing all of the UnusedLocalTypedefNameCandidates.
4942  for (const TypedefNameDecl *TD : SemaRef.UnusedLocalTypedefNameCandidates)
4943  GetDeclRef(TD);
4944 
4945  // Writing all of pending implicit instantiations.
4946  for (const auto &I : SemaRef.PendingInstantiations)
4947  GetDeclRef(I.first);
4948  assert(SemaRef.PendingLocalImplicitInstantiations.empty() &&
4949  "There are local ones at end of translation unit!");
4950 
4951  // Writing some declaration references.
4952  if (SemaRef.StdNamespace || SemaRef.StdBadAlloc || SemaRef.StdAlignValT) {
4953  GetDeclRef(SemaRef.getStdNamespace());
4954  GetDeclRef(SemaRef.getStdBadAlloc());
4955  GetDeclRef(SemaRef.getStdAlignValT());
4956  }
4957 
4958  if (Context.getcudaConfigureCallDecl())
4959  GetDeclRef(Context.getcudaConfigureCallDecl());
4960 
4961  // Writing all of the known namespaces.
4962  for (const auto &I : SemaRef.KnownNamespaces)
4963  if (!I.second)
4964  GetDeclRef(I.first);
4965 
4966  // Writing all used, undefined objects that require definitions.
4967  SmallVector<std::pair<NamedDecl *, SourceLocation>, 16> Undefined;
4968  SemaRef.getUndefinedButUsed(Undefined);
4969  for (const auto &I : Undefined)
4970  GetDeclRef(I.first);
4971 
4972  // Writing all delete-expressions that we would like to
4973  // analyze later in AST.
4974  if (!isModule)
4975  for (const auto &DeleteExprsInfo :
4976  SemaRef.getMismatchingDeleteExpressions())
4977  GetDeclRef(DeleteExprsInfo.first);
4978 
4979  // Make sure visible decls, added to DeclContexts previously loaded from
4980  // an AST file, are registered for serialization. Likewise for template
4981  // specializations added to imported templates.
4982  for (const auto *I : DeclsToEmitEvenIfUnreferenced)
4983  GetDeclRef(I);
4984  DeclsToEmitEvenIfUnreferenced.clear();
4985 
4986  // Make sure all decls associated with an identifier are registered for
4987  // serialization, if we're storing decls with identifiers.
4988  if (!WritingModule || !getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
4989  llvm::SmallVector<const IdentifierInfo*, 256> IIs;
4990  for (const auto &ID : SemaRef.PP.getIdentifierTable()) {
4991  const IdentifierInfo *II = ID.second;
4992  if (!Chain || !II->isFromAST() || II->hasChangedSinceDeserialization())
4993  IIs.push_back(II);
4994  }
4995  // Sort the identifiers to visit based on their name.
4996  llvm::sort(IIs, llvm::deref<std::less<>>());
4997  for (const IdentifierInfo *II : IIs)
4998  for (const Decl *D : SemaRef.IdResolver.decls(II))
4999  GetDeclRef(D);
5000  }
5001 
5002  // Write all of the DeclsToCheckForDeferredDiags.
5003  for (auto *D : SemaRef.DeclsToCheckForDeferredDiags)
5004  GetDeclRef(D);
5005 }
5006 
5007 void ASTWriter::WriteSpecialDeclRecords(Sema &SemaRef) {
5008  ASTContext &Context = SemaRef.Context;
5009 
5010  bool isModule = WritingModule != nullptr;
5011 
5012  // Write the record containing external, unnamed definitions.
5013  if (!EagerlyDeserializedDecls.empty())
5014  Stream.EmitRecord(EAGERLY_DESERIALIZED_DECLS, EagerlyDeserializedDecls);
5015 
5016  if (!ModularCodegenDecls.empty())
5017  Stream.EmitRecord(MODULAR_CODEGEN_DECLS, ModularCodegenDecls);
5018 
5019  // Write the record containing tentative definitions.
5020  RecordData TentativeDefinitions;
5021  AddLazyVectorEmiitedDecls(*this, SemaRef.TentativeDefinitions,
5022  TentativeDefinitions);
5023  if (!TentativeDefinitions.empty())
5024  Stream.EmitRecord(TENTATIVE_DEFINITIONS, TentativeDefinitions);
5025 
5026  // Write the record containing unused file scoped decls.
5027  RecordData UnusedFileScopedDecls;
5028  if (!isModule)
5029  AddLazyVectorEmiitedDecls(*this, SemaRef.UnusedFileScopedDecls,
5030  UnusedFileScopedDecls);
5031  if (!UnusedFileScopedDecls.empty())
5032  Stream.EmitRecord(UNUSED_FILESCOPED_DECLS, UnusedFileScopedDecls);
5033 
5034  // Write the record containing ext_vector type names.
5035  RecordData ExtVectorDecls;
5036  AddLazyVectorEmiitedDecls(*this, SemaRef.ExtVectorDecls, ExtVectorDecls);
5037  if (!ExtVectorDecls.empty())
5038  Stream.EmitRecord(EXT_VECTOR_DECLS, ExtVectorDecls);
5039 
5040  // Write the record containing VTable uses information.
5041  RecordData VTableUses;
5042  if (!SemaRef.VTableUses.empty()) {
5043  for (unsigned I = 0, N = SemaRef.VTableUses.size(); I != N; ++I) {
5044  CXXRecordDecl *D = SemaRef.VTableUses[I].first;
5045  if (!wasDeclEmitted(D))
5046  continue;
5047 
5048  AddDeclRef(D, VTableUses);
5049  AddSourceLocation(SemaRef.VTableUses[I].second, VTableUses);
5050  VTableUses.push_back(SemaRef.VTablesUsed[D]);
5051  }
5052  Stream.EmitRecord(VTABLE_USES, VTableUses);
5053  }
5054 
5055  // Write the record containing potentially unused local typedefs.
5056  RecordData UnusedLocalTypedefNameCandidates;
5057  for (const TypedefNameDecl *TD : SemaRef.UnusedLocalTypedefNameCandidates)
5058  AddEmittedDeclRef(TD, UnusedLocalTypedefNameCandidates);
5059  if (!UnusedLocalTypedefNameCandidates.empty())
5060  Stream.EmitRecord(UNUSED_LOCAL_TYPEDEF_NAME_CANDIDATES,
5061  UnusedLocalTypedefNameCandidates);
5062 
5063  // Write the record containing pending implicit instantiations.
5064  RecordData PendingInstantiations;
5065  for (const auto &I : SemaRef.PendingInstantiations) {
5066  if (!wasDeclEmitted(I.first))
5067  continue;
5068 
5069  AddDeclRef(I.first, PendingInstantiations);
5070  AddSourceLocation(I.second, PendingInstantiations);
5071  }
5072  if (!PendingInstantiations.empty())
5073  Stream.EmitRecord(PENDING_IMPLICIT_INSTANTIATIONS, PendingInstantiations);
5074 
5075  // Write the record containing declaration references of Sema.
5076  RecordData SemaDeclRefs;
5077  if (SemaRef.StdNamespace || SemaRef.StdBadAlloc || SemaRef.StdAlignValT) {
5078  auto AddEmittedDeclRefOrZero = [this, &SemaDeclRefs](Decl *D) {
5079  if (!D || !wasDeclEmitted(D))
5080  SemaDeclRefs.push_back(0);
5081  else
5082  SemaDeclRefs.push_back(getDeclID(D));
5083  };
5084 
5085  AddEmittedDeclRefOrZero(SemaRef.getStdNamespace());
5086  AddEmittedDeclRefOrZero(SemaRef.getStdBadAlloc());
5087  AddEmittedDeclRefOrZero(SemaRef.getStdAlignValT());
5088  }
5089  if (!SemaDeclRefs.empty())
5090  Stream.EmitRecord(SEMA_DECL_REFS, SemaDeclRefs);
5091 
5092  // Write the record containing decls to be checked for deferred diags.
5093  SmallVector<serialization::DeclID, 64> DeclsToCheckForDeferredDiags;
5094  for (auto *D : SemaRef.DeclsToCheckForDeferredDiags)
5095  if (wasDeclEmitted(D))
5096  DeclsToCheckForDeferredDiags.push_back(getDeclID(D));
5097  if (!DeclsToCheckForDeferredDiags.empty())
5098  Stream.EmitRecord(DECLS_TO_CHECK_FOR_DEFERRED_DIAGS,
5099  DeclsToCheckForDeferredDiags);
5100 
5101  // Write the record containing CUDA-specific declaration references.
5102  RecordData CUDASpecialDeclRefs;
5103  if (auto *CudaCallDecl = Context.getcudaConfigureCallDecl();
5104  CudaCallDecl && wasDeclEmitted(CudaCallDecl)) {
5105  AddDeclRef(CudaCallDecl, CUDASpecialDeclRefs);
5106  Stream.EmitRecord(CUDA_SPECIAL_DECL_REFS, CUDASpecialDeclRefs);
5107  }
5108 
5109  // Write the delegating constructors.
5110  RecordData DelegatingCtorDecls;
5111  if (!isModule)
5112  AddLazyVectorEmiitedDecls(*this, SemaRef.DelegatingCtorDecls,
5113  DelegatingCtorDecls);
5114  if (!DelegatingCtorDecls.empty())
5115  Stream.EmitRecord(DELEGATING_CTORS, DelegatingCtorDecls);
5116 
5117  // Write the known namespaces.
5118  RecordData KnownNamespaces;
5119  for (const auto &I : SemaRef.KnownNamespaces) {
5120  if (!I.second && wasDeclEmitted(I.first))
5121  AddDeclRef(I.first, KnownNamespaces);
5122  }
5123  if (!KnownNamespaces.empty())
5124  Stream.EmitRecord(KNOWN_NAMESPACES, KnownNamespaces);
5125 
5126  // Write the undefined internal functions and variables, and inline functions.
5127  RecordData UndefinedButUsed;
5128  SmallVector<std::pair<NamedDecl *, SourceLocation>, 16> Undefined;
5129  SemaRef.getUndefinedButUsed(Undefined);
5130  for (const auto &I : Undefined) {
5131  if (!wasDeclEmitted(I.first))
5132  continue;
5133 
5134  AddDeclRef(I.first, UndefinedButUsed);
5135  AddSourceLocation(I.second, UndefinedButUsed);
5136  }
5137  if (!UndefinedButUsed.empty())
5138  Stream.EmitRecord(UNDEFINED_BUT_USED, UndefinedButUsed);
5139 
5140  // Write all delete-expressions that we would like to
5141  // analyze later in AST.
5142  RecordData DeleteExprsToAnalyze;
5143  if (!isModule) {
5144  for (const auto &DeleteExprsInfo :
5145  SemaRef.getMismatchingDeleteExpressions()) {
5146  if (!wasDeclEmitted(DeleteExprsInfo.first))
5147  continue;
5148 
5149  AddDeclRef(DeleteExprsInfo.first, DeleteExprsToAnalyze);
5150  DeleteExprsToAnalyze.push_back(DeleteExprsInfo.second.size());
5151  for (const auto &DeleteLoc : DeleteExprsInfo.second) {
5152  AddSourceLocation(DeleteLoc.first, DeleteExprsToAnalyze);
5153  DeleteExprsToAnalyze.push_back(DeleteLoc.second);
5154  }
5155  }
5156  }
5157  if (!DeleteExprsToAnalyze.empty())
5158  Stream.EmitRecord(DELETE_EXPRS_TO_ANALYZE, DeleteExprsToAnalyze);
5159 }
5160 
5161 ASTFileSignature ASTWriter::WriteASTCore(Sema &SemaRef, StringRef isysroot,
5162  Module *WritingModule) {
5163  using namespace llvm;
5164 
5165  bool isModule = WritingModule != nullptr;
5166 
5167  // Make sure that the AST reader knows to finalize itself.
5168  if (Chain)
5169  Chain->finalizeForWriting();
5170 
5171  ASTContext &Context = SemaRef.Context;
5172  Preprocessor &PP = SemaRef.PP;
5173 
5174  // This needs to be done very early, since everything that writes
5175  // SourceLocations or FileIDs depends on it.
5176  computeNonAffectingInputFiles();
5177 
5178  writeUnhashedControlBlock(PP, Context);
5179 
5180  // Write the set of weak, undeclared identifiers. We always write the
5181  // entire table, since later PCH files in a PCH chain are only interested in
5182  // the results at the end of the chain.
5183  RecordData WeakUndeclaredIdentifiers;
5184  for (const auto &WeakUndeclaredIdentifierList :
5185  SemaRef.WeakUndeclaredIdentifiers) {
5186  const IdentifierInfo *const II = WeakUndeclaredIdentifierList.first;
5187  for (const auto &WI : WeakUndeclaredIdentifierList.second) {
5188  AddIdentifierRef(II, WeakUndeclaredIdentifiers);
5189  AddIdentifierRef(WI.getAlias(), WeakUndeclaredIdentifiers);
5190  AddSourceLocation(WI.getLocation(), WeakUndeclaredIdentifiers);
5191  }
5192  }
5193 
5194  PrepareWritingSpecialDecls(SemaRef);
5195 
5196  // Write the control block
5197  WriteControlBlock(PP, Context, isysroot);
5198 
5199  // Write the remaining AST contents.
5200  Stream.FlushToWord();
5201  ASTBlockRange.first = Stream.GetCurrentBitNo() >> 3;
5202  Stream.EnterSubblock(AST_BLOCK_ID, 5);
5203  ASTBlockStartOffset = Stream.GetCurrentBitNo();
5204 
5205  // This is so that older clang versions, before the introduction
5206  // of the control block, can read and reject the newer PCH format.
5207  {
5208  RecordData Record = {VERSION_MAJOR};
5209  Stream.EmitRecord(METADATA_OLD_FORMAT, Record);
5210  }
5211 
5212  // For method pool in the module, if it contains an entry for a selector,
5213  // the entry should be complete, containing everything introduced by that
5214  // module and all modules it imports. It's possible that the entry is out of
5215  // date, so we need to pull in the new content here.
5216 
5217  // It's possible that updateOutOfDateSelector can update SelectorIDs. To be
5218  // safe, we copy all selectors out.
5219  llvm::SmallVector<Selector, 256> AllSelectors;
5220  for (auto &SelectorAndID : SelectorIDs)
5221  AllSelectors.push_back(SelectorAndID.first);
5222  for (auto &Selector : AllSelectors)
5223  SemaRef.updateOutOfDateSelector(Selector);
5224 
5225  // Form the record of special types.
5226  RecordData SpecialTypes;
5227  AddTypeRef(Context.getRawCFConstantStringType(), SpecialTypes);
5228  AddTypeRef(Context.getFILEType(), SpecialTypes);
5229  AddTypeRef(Context.getjmp_bufType(), SpecialTypes);
5230  AddTypeRef(Context.getsigjmp_bufType(), SpecialTypes);
5231  AddTypeRef(Context.ObjCIdRedefinitionType, SpecialTypes);
5232  AddTypeRef(Context.ObjCClassRedefinitionType, SpecialTypes);
5233  AddTypeRef(Context.ObjCSelRedefinitionType, SpecialTypes);
5234  AddTypeRef(Context.getucontext_tType(), SpecialTypes);
5235 
5236  if (Chain) {
5237  // Write the mapping information describing our module dependencies and how
5238  // each of those modules were mapped into our own offset/ID space, so that
5239  // the reader can build the appropriate mapping to its own offset/ID space.
5240  // The map consists solely of a blob with the following format:
5241  // *(module-kind:i8
5242  // module-name-len:i16 module-name:len*i8
5243  // source-location-offset:i32
5244  // identifier-id:i32
5245  // preprocessed-entity-id:i32
5246  // macro-definition-id:i32
5247  // submodule-id:i32
5248  // selector-id:i32
5249  // declaration-id:i32
5250  // c++-base-specifiers-id:i32
5251  // type-id:i32)
5252  //
5253  // module-kind is the ModuleKind enum value. If it is MK_PrebuiltModule,
5254  // MK_ExplicitModule or MK_ImplicitModule, then the module-name is the
5255  // module name. Otherwise, it is the module file name.
5256  auto Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
5257  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(MODULE_OFFSET_MAP));
5258  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob));
5259  unsigned ModuleOffsetMapAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
5260  SmallString<2048> Buffer;
5261  {
5262  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(Buffer);
5263  for (ModuleFile &M : Chain->ModuleMgr) {
5264  using namespace llvm::support;
5265 
5266  endian::Writer LE(Out, llvm::endianness::little);
5267  LE.write<uint8_t>(static_cast<uint8_t>(M.Kind));
5268  StringRef Name = M.isModule() ? M.ModuleName : M.FileName;
5269  LE.write<uint16_t>(Name.size());
5270  Out.write(Name.data(), Name.size());
5271 
5272  // Note: if a base ID was uint max, it would not be possible to load
5273  // another module after it or have more than one entity inside it.
5274  uint32_t None = std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max();
5275 
5276  auto writeBaseIDOrNone = [&](auto BaseID, bool ShouldWrite) {
5277  assert(BaseID < std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max() && "base id too high");
5278  if (ShouldWrite)
5279  LE.write<uint32_t>(BaseID);
5280  else
5281  LE.write<uint32_t>(None);
5282  };
5283 
5284  // These values should be unique within a chain, since they will be read
5285  // as keys into ContinuousRangeMaps.
5286  writeBaseIDOrNone(M.SLocEntryBaseOffset, M.LocalNumSLocEntries);
5287  writeBaseIDOrNone(M.BaseIdentifierID, M.LocalNumIdentifiers);
5288  writeBaseIDOrNone(M.BaseMacroID, M.LocalNumMacros);
5289  writeBaseIDOrNone(M.BasePreprocessedEntityID,
5290  M.NumPreprocessedEntities);
5291  writeBaseIDOrNone(M.BaseSubmoduleID, M.LocalNumSubmodules);
5292  writeBaseIDOrNone(M.BaseSelectorID, M.LocalNumSelectors);
5293  writeBaseIDOrNone(M.BaseDeclID, M.LocalNumDecls);
5294  writeBaseIDOrNone(M.BaseTypeIndex, M.LocalNumTypes);
5295  }
5296  }
5297  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {MODULE_OFFSET_MAP};
5298  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(ModuleOffsetMapAbbrev, Record,
5299  Buffer.data(), Buffer.size());
5300  }
5301 
5302  WriteDeclAndTypes(Context);
5303 
5304  WriteFileDeclIDsMap();
5305  WriteSourceManagerBlock(Context.getSourceManager(), PP);
5306  WriteComments();
5307  WritePreprocessor(PP, isModule);
5308  WriteHeaderSearch(PP.getHeaderSearchInfo());
5309  WriteSelectors(SemaRef);
5310  WriteReferencedSelectorsPool(SemaRef);
5311  WriteLateParsedTemplates(SemaRef);
5312  WriteIdentifierTable(PP, SemaRef.IdResolver, isModule);
5313  WriteFPPragmaOptions(SemaRef.CurFPFeatureOverrides());
5314  WriteOpenCLExtensions(SemaRef);
5315  WriteCUDAPragmas(SemaRef);
5316 
5317  // If we're emitting a module, write out the submodule information.
5318  if (WritingModule)
5319  WriteSubmodules(WritingModule);
5320 
5321  Stream.EmitRecord(SPECIAL_TYPES, SpecialTypes);
5322 
5323  WriteSpecialDeclRecords(SemaRef);
5324 
5325  // Write the record containing weak undeclared identifiers.
5326  if (!WeakUndeclaredIdentifiers.empty())
5327  Stream.EmitRecord(WEAK_UNDECLARED_IDENTIFIERS,
5328  WeakUndeclaredIdentifiers);
5329 
5330  if (!WritingModule) {
5331  // Write the submodules that were imported, if any.
5332  struct ModuleInfo {
5333  uint64_t ID;
5334  Module *M;
5335  ModuleInfo(uint64_t ID, Module *M) : ID(ID), M(M) {}
5336  };
5337  llvm::SmallVector<ModuleInfo, 64> Imports;
5338  for (const auto *I : Context.local_imports()) {
5339  assert(SubmoduleIDs.contains(I->getImportedModule()));
5340  Imports.push_back(ModuleInfo(SubmoduleIDs[I->getImportedModule()],
5341  I->getImportedModule()));
5342  }
5343 
5344  if (!Imports.empty()) {
5345  auto Cmp = [](const ModuleInfo &A, const ModuleInfo &B) {
5346  return A.ID < B.ID;
5347  };
5348  auto Eq = [](const ModuleInfo &A, const ModuleInfo &B) {
5349  return A.ID == B.ID;
5350  };
5351 
5352  // Sort and deduplicate module IDs.
5353  llvm::sort(Imports, Cmp);
5354  Imports.erase(std::unique(Imports.begin(), Imports.end(), Eq),
5355  Imports.end());
5356 
5357  RecordData ImportedModules;
5358  for (const auto &Import : Imports) {
5359  ImportedModules.push_back(Import.ID);
5360  // FIXME: If the module has macros imported then later has declarations
5361  // imported, this location won't be the right one as a location for the
5362  // declaration imports.
5363  AddSourceLocation(PP.getModuleImportLoc(Import.M), ImportedModules);
5364  }
5365 
5366  Stream.EmitRecord(IMPORTED_MODULES, ImportedModules);
5367  }
5368  }
5369 
5370  WriteObjCCategories();
5371  if(!WritingModule) {
5372  WriteOptimizePragmaOptions(SemaRef);
5373  WriteMSStructPragmaOptions(SemaRef);
5374  WriteMSPointersToMembersPragmaOptions(SemaRef);
5375  }
5376  WritePackPragmaOptions(SemaRef);
5377  WriteFloatControlPragmaOptions(SemaRef);
5378 
5379  // Some simple statistics
5380  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {
5381  NumStatements, NumMacros, NumLexicalDeclContexts, NumVisibleDeclContexts};
5382  Stream.EmitRecord(STATISTICS, Record);
5383  Stream.ExitBlock();
5384  Stream.FlushToWord();
5385  ASTBlockRange.second = Stream.GetCurrentBitNo() >> 3;
5386 
5387  // Write the module file extension blocks.
5388  for (const auto &ExtWriter : ModuleFileExtensionWriters)
5389  WriteModuleFileExtension(SemaRef, *ExtWriter);
5390 
5391  return backpatchSignature();
5392 }
5393 
5394 void ASTWriter::EnteringModulePurview() {
5395  // In C++20 named modules, all entities before entering the module purview
5396  // lives in the GMF.
5397  if (GeneratingReducedBMI)
5398  DeclUpdatesFromGMF.swap(DeclUpdates);
5399 }
5400 
5401 // Add update records for all mangling numbers and static local numbers.
5402 // These aren't really update records, but this is a convenient way of
5403 // tagging this rare extra data onto the declarations.
5404 void ASTWriter::AddedManglingNumber(const Decl *D, unsigned Number) {
5405  if (D->isFromASTFile())
5406  return;
5407 
5408  DeclUpdates[D].push_back(DeclUpdate(UPD_MANGLING_NUMBER, Number));
5409 }
5410 void ASTWriter::AddedStaticLocalNumbers(const Decl *D, unsigned Number) {
5411  if (D->isFromASTFile())
5412  return;
5413 
5414  DeclUpdates[D].push_back(DeclUpdate(UPD_STATIC_LOCAL_NUMBER, Number));
5415 }
5416 
5417 void ASTWriter::AddedAnonymousNamespace(const TranslationUnitDecl *TU,
5418  NamespaceDecl *AnonNamespace) {
5419  // If the translation unit has an anonymous namespace, and we don't already
5420  // have an update block for it, write it as an update block.
5421  // FIXME: Why do we not do this if there's already an update block?
5422  if (NamespaceDecl *NS = TU->getAnonymousNamespace()) {
5423  ASTWriter::UpdateRecord &Record = DeclUpdates[TU];
5424  if (Record.empty())
5425  Record.push_back(DeclUpdate(UPD_CXX_ADDED_ANONYMOUS_NAMESPACE, NS));
5426  }
5427 }
5428 
5429 void ASTWriter::WriteDeclAndTypes(ASTContext &Context) {
5430  // Keep writing types, declarations, and declaration update records
5431  // until we've emitted all of them.
5432  RecordData DeclUpdatesOffsetsRecord;
5433  Stream.EnterSubblock(DECLTYPES_BLOCK_ID, /*bits for abbreviations*/5);
5434  DeclTypesBlockStartOffset = Stream.GetCurrentBitNo();
5435  WriteTypeAbbrevs();
5436  WriteDeclAbbrevs();
5437  do {
5438  WriteDeclUpdatesBlocks(DeclUpdatesOffsetsRecord);
5439  while (!DeclTypesToEmit.empty()) {
5440  DeclOrType DOT = DeclTypesToEmit.front();
5441  DeclTypesToEmit.pop();
5442  if (DOT.isType())
5443  WriteType(DOT.getType());
5444  else
5445  WriteDecl(Context, DOT.getDecl());
5446  }
5447  } while (!DeclUpdates.empty());
5448 
5449  DoneWritingDeclsAndTypes = true;
5450 
5451  // DelayedNamespace is only meaningful in reduced BMI.
5452  // See the comments of DelayedNamespace for details.
5453  assert(DelayedNamespace.empty() || GeneratingReducedBMI);
5454  RecordData DelayedNamespaceRecord;
5455  for (NamespaceDecl *NS : DelayedNamespace) {
5456  uint64_t LexicalOffset = WriteDeclContextLexicalBlock(Context, NS);
5457  uint64_t VisibleOffset = WriteDeclContextVisibleBlock(Context, NS);
5458 
5459  // Write the offset relative to current block.
5460  if (LexicalOffset)
5461  LexicalOffset -= DeclTypesBlockStartOffset;
5462 
5463  if (VisibleOffset)
5464  VisibleOffset -= DeclTypesBlockStartOffset;
5465 
5466  DelayedNamespaceRecord.push_back(getDeclID(NS));
5467  DelayedNamespaceRecord.push_back(LexicalOffset);
5468  DelayedNamespaceRecord.push_back(VisibleOffset);
5469  }
5470 
5471  // The process of writing lexical and visible block for delayed namespace
5472  // shouldn't introduce any new decls, types or update to emit.
5473  assert(DeclTypesToEmit.empty());
5474  assert(DeclUpdates.empty());
5475 
5476  Stream.ExitBlock();
5477 
5478  // These things can only be done once we've written out decls and types.
5479  WriteTypeDeclOffsets();
5480  if (!DeclUpdatesOffsetsRecord.empty())
5481  Stream.EmitRecord(DECL_UPDATE_OFFSETS, DeclUpdatesOffsetsRecord);
5482 
5483  if (!DelayedNamespaceRecord.empty())
5484  Stream.EmitRecord(DELAYED_NAMESPACE_LEXICAL_VISIBLE_RECORD,
5485  DelayedNamespaceRecord);
5486 
5487  const TranslationUnitDecl *TU = Context.getTranslationUnitDecl();
5488  // Create a lexical update block containing all of the declarations in the
5489  // translation unit that do not come from other AST files.
5490  SmallVector<DeclID, 128> NewGlobalKindDeclPairs;
5491  for (const auto *D : TU->noload_decls()) {
5492  if (D->isFromASTFile())
5493  continue;
5494 
5495  // In reduced BMI, skip unreached declarations.
5496  if (!wasDeclEmitted(D))
5497  continue;
5498 
5499  NewGlobalKindDeclPairs.push_back(D->getKind());
5500  NewGlobalKindDeclPairs.push_back(GetDeclRef(D));
5501  }
5502 
5503  auto Abv = std::make_shared<llvm::BitCodeAbbrev>();
5504  Abv->Add(llvm::BitCodeAbbrevOp(TU_UPDATE_LEXICAL));
5505  Abv->Add(llvm::BitCodeAbbrevOp(llvm::BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob));
5506  unsigned TuUpdateLexicalAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abv));
5507 
5508  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {TU_UPDATE_LEXICAL};
5509  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(TuUpdateLexicalAbbrev, Record,
5510  bytes(NewGlobalKindDeclPairs));
5511 
5512  Abv = std::make_shared<llvm::BitCodeAbbrev>();
5513  Abv->Add(llvm::BitCodeAbbrevOp(UPDATE_VISIBLE));
5514  Abv->Add(llvm::BitCodeAbbrevOp(llvm::BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 6));
5515  Abv->Add(llvm::BitCodeAbbrevOp(llvm::BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob));
5516  UpdateVisibleAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abv));
5517 
5518  // And a visible updates block for the translation unit.
5519  WriteDeclContextVisibleUpdate(TU);
5520 
5521  // If we have any extern "C" names, write out a visible update for them.
5522  if (Context.ExternCContext)
5523  WriteDeclContextVisibleUpdate(Context.ExternCContext);
5524 
5525  // Write the visible updates to DeclContexts.
5526  for (auto *DC : UpdatedDeclContexts)
5527  WriteDeclContextVisibleUpdate(DC);
5528 }
5529 
5530 void ASTWriter::WriteDeclUpdatesBlocks(RecordDataImpl &OffsetsRecord) {
5531  if (DeclUpdates.empty())
5532  return;
5533 
5534  DeclUpdateMap LocalUpdates;
5535  LocalUpdates.swap(DeclUpdates);
5536 
5537  for (auto &DeclUpdate : LocalUpdates) {
5538  const Decl *D = DeclUpdate.first;
5539 
5540  bool HasUpdatedBody = false;
5541  bool HasAddedVarDefinition = false;
5542  RecordData RecordData;
5543  ASTRecordWriter Record(*this, RecordData);
5544  for (auto &Update : DeclUpdate.second) {
5545  DeclUpdateKind Kind = (DeclUpdateKind)Update.getKind();
5546 
5547  // An updated body is emitted last, so that the reader doesn't need
5548  // to skip over the lazy body to reach statements for other records.
5549  if (Kind == UPD_CXX_ADDED_FUNCTION_DEFINITION)
5550  HasUpdatedBody = true;
5551  else if (Kind == UPD_CXX_ADDED_VAR_DEFINITION)
5552  HasAddedVarDefinition = true;
5553  else
5554  Record.push_back(Kind);
5555 
5556  switch (Kind) {
5557  case UPD_CXX_ADDED_IMPLICIT_MEMBER:
5558  case UPD_CXX_ADDED_TEMPLATE_SPECIALIZATION:
5559  case UPD_CXX_ADDED_ANONYMOUS_NAMESPACE:
5560  assert(Update.getDecl() && "no decl to add?");
5561  Record.push_back(GetDeclRef(Update.getDecl()));
5562  break;
5563 
5564  case UPD_CXX_ADDED_FUNCTION_DEFINITION:
5565  case UPD_CXX_ADDED_VAR_DEFINITION:
5566  break;
5567 
5568  case UPD_CXX_POINT_OF_INSTANTIATION:
5569  // FIXME: Do we need to also save the template specialization kind here?
5570  Record.AddSourceLocation(Update.getLoc());
5571  break;
5572 
5573  case UPD_CXX_INSTANTIATED_DEFAULT_ARGUMENT:
5574  Record.AddStmt(const_cast<Expr *>(
5575  cast<ParmVarDecl>(Update.getDecl())->getDefaultArg()));
5576  break;
5577 
5578  case UPD_CXX_INSTANTIATED_DEFAULT_MEMBER_INITIALIZER:
5579  Record.AddStmt(
5580  cast<FieldDecl>(Update.getDecl())->getInClassInitializer());
5581  break;
5582 
5583  case UPD_CXX_INSTANTIATED_CLASS_DEFINITION: {
5584  auto *RD = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D);
5585  UpdatedDeclContexts.insert(RD->getPrimaryContext());
5586  Record.push_back(RD->isParamDestroyedInCallee());
5587  Record.push_back(llvm::to_underlying(RD->getArgPassingRestrictions()));
5588  Record.AddCXXDefinitionData(RD);
5589  Record.AddOffset(WriteDeclContextLexicalBlock(
5590  *Context, const_cast<CXXRecordDecl *>(RD)));
5591 
5592  // This state is sometimes updated by template instantiation, when we
5593  // switch from the specialization referring to the template declaration
5594  // to it referring to the template definition.
5595  if (auto *MSInfo = RD->getMemberSpecializationInfo()) {
5596  Record.push_back(MSInfo->getTemplateSpecializationKind());
5597  Record.AddSourceLocation(MSInfo->getPointOfInstantiation());
5598  } else {
5599  auto *Spec = cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(RD);
5600  Record.push_back(Spec->getTemplateSpecializationKind());
5601  Record.AddSourceLocation(Spec->getPointOfInstantiation());
5602 
5603  // The instantiation might have been resolved to a partial
5604  // specialization. If so, record which one.
5605  auto From = Spec->getInstantiatedFrom();
5606  if (auto PartialSpec =
5607  From.dyn_cast<ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl*>()) {
5608  Record.push_back(true);
5609  Record.AddDeclRef(PartialSpec);
5610  Record.AddTemplateArgumentList(
5611  &Spec->getTemplateInstantiationArgs());
5612  } else {
5613  Record.push_back(false);
5614  }
5615  }
5616  Record.push_back(llvm::to_underlying(RD->getTagKind()));
5617  Record.AddSourceLocation(RD->getLocation());
5618  Record.AddSourceLocation(RD->getBeginLoc());
5619  Record.AddSourceRange(RD->getBraceRange());
5620 
5621  // Instantiation may change attributes; write them all out afresh.
5622  Record.push_back(D->hasAttrs());
5623  if (D->hasAttrs())
5624  Record.AddAttributes(D->getAttrs());
5625 
5626  // FIXME: Ensure we don't get here for explicit instantiations.
5627  break;
5628  }
5629 
5630  case UPD_CXX_RESOLVED_DTOR_DELETE:
5631  Record.AddDeclRef(Update.getDecl());
5632  Record.AddStmt(cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(D)->getOperatorDeleteThisArg());
5633  break;
5634 
5635  case UPD_CXX_RESOLVED_EXCEPTION_SPEC: {
5636  auto prototype =
5637  cast<FunctionDecl>(D)->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
5638  Record.writeExceptionSpecInfo(prototype->getExceptionSpecInfo());
5639  break;
5640  }
5641 
5642  case UPD_CXX_DEDUCED_RETURN_TYPE:
5643  Record.push_back(GetOrCreateTypeID(Update.getType()));
5644  break;
5645 
5646  case UPD_DECL_MARKED_USED:
5647  break;
5648 
5649  case UPD_MANGLING_NUMBER:
5650  case UPD_STATIC_LOCAL_NUMBER:
5651  Record.push_back(Update.getNumber());
5652  break;
5653 
5654  case UPD_DECL_MARKED_OPENMP_THREADPRIVATE:
5655  Record.AddSourceRange(
5656  D->getAttr<OMPThreadPrivateDeclAttr>()->getRange());
5657  break;
5658 
5659  case UPD_DECL_MARKED_OPENMP_ALLOCATE: {
5660  auto *A = D->getAttr<OMPAllocateDeclAttr>();
5661  Record.push_back(A->getAllocatorType());
5662  Record.AddStmt(A->getAllocator());
5663  Record.AddStmt(A->getAlignment());
5664  Record.AddSourceRange(A->getRange());
5665  break;
5666  }
5667 
5668  case UPD_DECL_MARKED_OPENMP_DECLARETARGET:
5669  Record.push_back(D->getAttr<OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr>()->getMapType());
5670  Record.AddSourceRange(
5671  D->getAttr<OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr>()->getRange());
5672  break;
5673 
5674  case UPD_DECL_EXPORTED:
5675  Record.push_back(getSubmoduleID(Update.getModule()));
5676  break;
5677 
5678  case UPD_ADDED_ATTR_TO_RECORD:
5679  Record.AddAttributes(llvm::ArrayRef(Update.getAttr()));
5680  break;
5681  }
5682  }
5683 
5684  // Add a trailing update record, if any. These must go last because we
5685  // lazily load their attached statement.
5686  if (!GeneratingReducedBMI || !CanElideDeclDef(D)) {
5687  if (HasUpdatedBody) {
5688  const auto *Def = cast<FunctionDecl>(D);
5689  Record.push_back(UPD_CXX_ADDED_FUNCTION_DEFINITION);
5690  Record.push_back(Def->isInlined());
5691  Record.AddSourceLocation(Def->getInnerLocStart());
5692  Record.AddFunctionDefinition(Def);
5693  } else if (HasAddedVarDefinition) {
5694  const auto *VD = cast<VarDecl>(D);
5695  Record.push_back(UPD_CXX_ADDED_VAR_DEFINITION);
5696  Record.push_back(VD->isInline());
5697  Record.push_back(VD->isInlineSpecified());
5698  Record.AddVarDeclInit(VD);
5699  }
5700  }
5701 
5702  OffsetsRecord.push_back(GetDeclRef(D));
5703  OffsetsRecord.push_back(Record.Emit(DECL_UPDATES));
5704  }
5705 }
5706 
5707 void ASTWriter::AddAlignPackInfo(const Sema::AlignPackInfo &Info,
5708  RecordDataImpl &Record) {
5709  uint32_t Raw = Sema::AlignPackInfo::getRawEncoding(Info);
5710  Record.push_back(Raw);
5711 }

5713 FileID ASTWriter::getAdjustedFileID(FileID FID) const {
5714  if (FID.isInvalid() || PP->getSourceManager().isLoadedFileID(FID) ||
5715  NonAffectingFileIDs.empty())
5716  return FID;
5717  auto It = llvm::lower_bound(NonAffectingFileIDs, FID);
5718  unsigned Idx = std::distance(NonAffectingFileIDs.begin(), It);
5719  unsigned Offset = NonAffectingFileIDAdjustments[Idx];
5720  return FileID::get(FID.getOpaqueValue() - Offset);
5721 }
5722 
5723 unsigned ASTWriter::getAdjustedNumCreatedFIDs(FileID FID) const {
5724  unsigned NumCreatedFIDs = PP->getSourceManager()
5725  .getLocalSLocEntry(FID.ID)
5726  .getFile()
5727  .NumCreatedFIDs;
5728 
5729  unsigned AdjustedNumCreatedFIDs = 0;
5730  for (unsigned I = FID.ID, N = I + NumCreatedFIDs; I != N; ++I)
5731  if (IsSLocAffecting[I])
5732  ++AdjustedNumCreatedFIDs;
5733  return AdjustedNumCreatedFIDs;
5734 }

5736 SourceLocation ASTWriter::getAdjustedLocation(SourceLocation Loc) const {
5737  if (Loc.isInvalid())
5738  return Loc;
5739  return Loc.getLocWithOffset(-getAdjustment(Loc.getOffset()));
5740 }

5744  getAdjustedLocation(Range.getEnd()));

5747 SourceLocation::UIntTy
5748 ASTWriter::getAdjustedOffset(SourceLocation::UIntTy Offset) const {
5749  return Offset - getAdjustment(Offset);
5750 }
5751 
5752 SourceLocation::UIntTy
5753 ASTWriter::getAdjustment(SourceLocation::UIntTy Offset) const {
5754  if (NonAffectingRanges.empty())
5755  return 0;
5756 
5757  if (PP->getSourceManager().isLoadedOffset(Offset))
5758  return 0;
5759 
5760  if (Offset > NonAffectingRanges.back().getEnd().getOffset())
5761  return NonAffectingOffsetAdjustments.back();
5762 
5763  if (Offset < NonAffectingRanges.front().getBegin().getOffset())
5764  return 0;
5765 
5766  auto Contains = [](const SourceRange &Range, SourceLocation::UIntTy Offset) {
5767  return Range.getEnd().getOffset() < Offset;
5768  };
5769 
5770  auto It = llvm::lower_bound(NonAffectingRanges, Offset, Contains);
5771  unsigned Idx = std::distance(NonAffectingRanges.begin(), It);
5772  return NonAffectingOffsetAdjustments[Idx];
5773 }

5809 MacroID ASTWriter::getMacroRef(MacroInfo *MI, const IdentifierInfo *Name) {
5810  // Don't emit builtin macros like __LINE__ to the AST file unless they
5811  // have been redefined by the header (in which case they are not
5812  // isBuiltinMacro).
5813  if (!MI || MI->isBuiltinMacro())
5814  return 0;
5815 
5816  MacroID &ID = MacroIDs[MI];
5817  if (ID == 0) {
5818  ID = NextMacroID++;
5819  MacroInfoToEmitData Info = { Name, MI, ID };
5820  MacroInfosToEmit.push_back(Info);
5821  }
5822  return ID;
5823 }

5826  if (!MI || MI->isBuiltinMacro())
5827  return 0;
5828 
5829  assert(MacroIDs.contains(MI) && "Macro not emitted!");
5830  return MacroIDs[MI];
5831 }

5840 
5841 SelectorID ASTWriter::getSelectorRef(Selector Sel) {
5842  if (Sel.getAsOpaquePtr() == nullptr) {
5843  return 0;
5844  }
5845 
5846  SelectorID SID = SelectorIDs[Sel];
5847  if (SID == 0 && Chain) {
5848  // This might trigger a ReadSelector callback, which will set the ID for
5849  // this selector.
5850  Chain->LoadSelector(Sel);
5851  SID = SelectorIDs[Sel];
5852  }
5853  if (SID == 0) {
5854  SID = NextSelectorID++;
5855  SelectorIDs[Sel] = SID;
5856  }
5857  return SID;
5858 }

5864 void ASTRecordWriter::AddTemplateArgumentLocInfo(
5865  TemplateArgument::ArgKind Kind, const TemplateArgumentLocInfo &Arg) {
5866  switch (Kind) {
5867  case TemplateArgument::Expression:
5868  AddStmt(Arg.getAsExpr());
5869  break;
5870  case TemplateArgument::Type:
5871  AddTypeSourceInfo(Arg.getAsTypeSourceInfo());
5872  break;
5873  case TemplateArgument::Template:
5874  AddNestedNameSpecifierLoc(Arg.getTemplateQualifierLoc());
5875  AddSourceLocation(Arg.getTemplateNameLoc());
5876  break;
5877  case TemplateArgument::TemplateExpansion:
5878  AddNestedNameSpecifierLoc(Arg.getTemplateQualifierLoc());
5879  AddSourceLocation(Arg.getTemplateNameLoc());
5880  AddSourceLocation(Arg.getTemplateEllipsisLoc());
5881  break;
5882  case TemplateArgument::Null:
5883  case TemplateArgument::Integral:
5884  case TemplateArgument::Declaration:
5885  case TemplateArgument::NullPtr:
5886  case TemplateArgument::StructuralValue:
5887  case TemplateArgument::Pack:
5888  // FIXME: Is this right?
5889  break;
5890  }
5891 }
5892 
5893 void ASTRecordWriter::AddTemplateArgumentLoc(const TemplateArgumentLoc &Arg) {
5894  AddTemplateArgument(Arg.getArgument());
5895 
5896  if (Arg.getArgument().getKind() == TemplateArgument::Expression) {
5897  bool InfoHasSameExpr
5898  = Arg.getArgument().getAsExpr() == Arg.getLocInfo().getAsExpr();
5899  Record->push_back(InfoHasSameExpr);
5900  if (InfoHasSameExpr)
5901  return; // Avoid storing the same expr twice.
5902  }
5903  AddTemplateArgumentLocInfo(Arg.getArgument().getKind(), Arg.getLocInfo());
5904 }

5916 void ASTRecordWriter::AddTypeLoc(TypeLoc TL, LocSeq *OuterSeq) {
5917  LocSeq::State Seq(OuterSeq);
5918  TypeLocWriter TLW(*this, Seq);
5919  for (; !TL.isNull(); TL = TL.getNextTypeLoc())
5920  TLW.Visit(TL);
5921 }

5926 
5927 TypeID ASTWriter::GetOrCreateTypeID(QualType T) {
5928  assert(Context);
5929  return MakeTypeID(*Context, T, [&](QualType T) -> TypeIdx {
5930  if (T.isNull())
5931  return TypeIdx();
5932  assert(!T.getLocalFastQualifiers());
5933 
5934  TypeIdx &Idx = TypeIdxs[T];
5935  if (Idx.getIndex() == 0) {
5936  if (DoneWritingDeclsAndTypes) {
5937  assert(0 && "New type seen after serializing all the types to emit!");
5938  return TypeIdx();
5939  }
5940 
5941  // We haven't seen this type before. Assign it a new ID and put it
5942  // into the queue of types to emit.
5943  Idx = TypeIdx(NextTypeID++);
5944  DeclTypesToEmit.push(T);
5945  }
5946  return Idx;
5947  });
5948 }
5949 
5950 TypeID ASTWriter::getTypeID(QualType T) const {
5951  assert(Context);
5952  return MakeTypeID(*Context, T, [&](QualType T) -> TypeIdx {
5953  if (T.isNull())
5954  return TypeIdx();
5955  assert(!T.getLocalFastQualifiers());
5956 
5957  TypeIdxMap::const_iterator I = TypeIdxs.find(T);
5958  assert(I != TypeIdxs.end() && "Type not emitted!");
5959  return I->second;
5960  });
5961 }

5963 void ASTWriter::AddEmittedDeclRef(const Decl *D, RecordDataImpl &Record) {
5964  if (!wasDeclEmitted(D))
5965  return;
5966 
5967  Record.push_back(GetDeclRef(D));
5968 }

5970 void ASTWriter::AddDeclRef(const Decl *D, RecordDataImpl &Record) {
5971  Record.push_back(GetDeclRef(D));
5972 }
5973 
5974 DeclID ASTWriter::GetDeclRef(const Decl *D) {
5975  assert(WritingAST && "Cannot request a declaration ID before AST writing");
5976 
5977  if (!D) {
5978  return 0;
5979  }
5980 
5981  // If the DeclUpdate from the GMF gets touched, emit it.
5982  if (auto *Iter = DeclUpdatesFromGMF.find(D);
5983  Iter != DeclUpdatesFromGMF.end()) {
5984  for (DeclUpdate &Update : Iter->second)
5985  DeclUpdates[D].push_back(Update);
5986  DeclUpdatesFromGMF.erase(Iter);
5987  }
5988 
5989  // If D comes from an AST file, its declaration ID is already known and
5990  // fixed.
5991  if (D->isFromASTFile())
5992  return D->getGlobalID();
5993 
5994  assert(!(reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(D) & 0x01) && "Invalid decl pointer");
5995  DeclID &ID = DeclIDs[D];
5996  if (ID == 0) {
5997  if (DoneWritingDeclsAndTypes) {
5998  assert(0 && "New decl seen after serializing all the decls to emit!");
5999  return 0;
6000  }
6001 
6002  // We haven't seen this declaration before. Give it a new ID and
6003  // enqueue it in the list of declarations to emit.
6004  ID = NextDeclID++;
6005  DeclTypesToEmit.push(const_cast<Decl *>(D));
6006  }
6007 
6008  return ID;
6009 }
6010 
6011 DeclID ASTWriter::getDeclID(const Decl *D) {
6012  if (!D)
6013  return 0;
6014 
6015  // If D comes from an AST file, its declaration ID is already known and
6016  // fixed.
6017  if (D->isFromASTFile())
6018  return D->getGlobalID();
6019 
6020  assert(DeclIDs.contains(D) && "Declaration not emitted!");
6021  return DeclIDs[D];
6022 }
6023 
6024 bool ASTWriter::wasDeclEmitted(const Decl *D) const {
6025  assert(D);
6026 
6027  assert(DoneWritingDeclsAndTypes &&
6028  "wasDeclEmitted should only be called after writing declarations");
6029 
6030  if (D->isFromASTFile())
6031  return true;
6032 
6033  bool Emitted = DeclIDs.contains(D);
6034  assert((Emitted || GeneratingReducedBMI) &&
6035  "The declaration can only be omitted in reduced BMI.");
6036  return Emitted;
6037 }
6038 
6039 void ASTWriter::associateDeclWithFile(const Decl *D, DeclID ID) {
6040  assert(ID);
6041  assert(D);
6042 
6043  SourceLocation Loc = D->getLocation();
6044  if (Loc.isInvalid())
6045  return;
6046 
6047  // We only keep track of the file-level declarations of each file.
6048  if (!D->getLexicalDeclContext()->isFileContext())
6049  return;
6050  // FIXME: ParmVarDecls that are part of a function type of a parameter of
6051  // a function/objc method, should not have TU as lexical context.
6052  // TemplateTemplateParmDecls that are part of an alias template, should not
6053  // have TU as lexical context.
6054  if (isa<ParmVarDecl, TemplateTemplateParmDecl>(D))
6055  return;
6056 
6057  SourceManager &SM = Context->getSourceManager();
6058  SourceLocation FileLoc = SM.getFileLoc(Loc);
6059  assert(SM.isLocalSourceLocation(FileLoc));
6060  FileID FID;
6061  unsigned Offset;
6062  std::tie(FID, Offset) = SM.getDecomposedLoc(FileLoc);
6063  if (FID.isInvalid())
6064  return;
6065  assert(SM.getSLocEntry(FID).isFile());
6066  assert(IsSLocAffecting[FID.ID]);
6067 
6068  std::unique_ptr<DeclIDInFileInfo> &Info = FileDeclIDs[FID];
6069  if (!Info)
6070  Info = std::make_unique<DeclIDInFileInfo>();
6071 
6072  std::pair<unsigned, serialization::DeclID> LocDecl(Offset, ID);
6073  LocDeclIDsTy &Decls = Info->DeclIDs;
6074  Decls.push_back(LocDecl);
6075 }
6076 
6077 unsigned ASTWriter::getAnonymousDeclarationNumber(const NamedDecl *D) {
6078  assert(needsAnonymousDeclarationNumber(D) &&
6079  "expected an anonymous declaration");
6080 
6081  // Number the anonymous declarations within this context, if we've not
6082  // already done so.
6083  auto It = AnonymousDeclarationNumbers.find(D);
6084  if (It == AnonymousDeclarationNumbers.end()) {
6085  auto *DC = D->getLexicalDeclContext();
6086  numberAnonymousDeclsWithin(DC, [&](const NamedDecl *ND, unsigned Number) {
6087  AnonymousDeclarationNumbers[ND] = Number;
6088  });
6089 
6090  It = AnonymousDeclarationNumbers.find(D);
6091  assert(It != AnonymousDeclarationNumbers.end() &&
6092  "declaration not found within its lexical context");
6093  }
6094 
6095  return It->second;
6096 }

6098 void ASTRecordWriter::AddDeclarationNameLoc(const DeclarationNameLoc &DNLoc,
6099  DeclarationName Name) {
6100  switch (Name.getNameKind()) {
6101  case DeclarationName::CXXConstructorName:
6102  case DeclarationName::CXXDestructorName:
6103  case DeclarationName::CXXConversionFunctionName:
6104  AddTypeSourceInfo(DNLoc.getNamedTypeInfo());
6105  break;
6106 
6107  case DeclarationName::CXXOperatorName:
6108  AddSourceRange(DNLoc.getCXXOperatorNameRange());
6109  break;
6110 
6111  case DeclarationName::CXXLiteralOperatorName:
6112  AddSourceLocation(DNLoc.getCXXLiteralOperatorNameLoc());
6113  break;
6114 
6115  case DeclarationName::Identifier:
6116  case DeclarationName::ObjCZeroArgSelector:
6117  case DeclarationName::ObjCOneArgSelector:
6118  case DeclarationName::ObjCMultiArgSelector:
6119  case DeclarationName::CXXUsingDirective:
6120  case DeclarationName::CXXDeductionGuideName:
6121  break;
6122  }
6123 }
6124 
6125 void ASTRecordWriter::AddDeclarationNameInfo(
6126  const DeclarationNameInfo &NameInfo) {
6127  AddDeclarationName(NameInfo.getName());
6128  AddSourceLocation(NameInfo.getLoc());
6129  AddDeclarationNameLoc(NameInfo.getInfo(), NameInfo.getName());
6130 }

6132 void ASTRecordWriter::AddQualifierInfo(const QualifierInfo &Info) {
6133  AddNestedNameSpecifierLoc(Info.QualifierLoc);
6134  Record->push_back(Info.NumTemplParamLists);
6135  for (unsigned i = 0, e = Info.NumTemplParamLists; i != e; ++i)
6136  AddTemplateParameterList(Info.TemplParamLists[i]);
6137 }
6138 
6139 void ASTRecordWriter::AddNestedNameSpecifierLoc(NestedNameSpecifierLoc NNS) {
6140  // Nested name specifiers usually aren't too long. I think that 8 would
6141  // typically accommodate the vast majority.
6142  SmallVector<NestedNameSpecifierLoc , 8> NestedNames;
6143 
6144  // Push each of the nested-name-specifiers's onto a stack for
6145  // serialization in reverse order.
6146  while (NNS) {
6147  NestedNames.push_back(NNS);
6148  NNS = NNS.getPrefix();
6149  }
6150 
6151  Record->push_back(NestedNames.size());
6152  while(!NestedNames.empty()) {
6153  NNS = NestedNames.pop_back_val();
6154  NestedNameSpecifier::SpecifierKind Kind
6155  = NNS.getNestedNameSpecifier()->getKind();
6156  Record->push_back(Kind);
6157  switch (Kind) {
6158  case NestedNameSpecifier::Identifier:
6159  AddIdentifierRef(NNS.getNestedNameSpecifier()->getAsIdentifier());
6160  AddSourceRange(NNS.getLocalSourceRange());
6161  break;
6162 
6163  case NestedNameSpecifier::Namespace:
6164  AddDeclRef(NNS.getNestedNameSpecifier()->getAsNamespace());
6165  AddSourceRange(NNS.getLocalSourceRange());
6166  break;
6167 
6168  case NestedNameSpecifier::NamespaceAlias:
6169  AddDeclRef(NNS.getNestedNameSpecifier()->getAsNamespaceAlias());
6170  AddSourceRange(NNS.getLocalSourceRange());
6171  break;
6172 
6173  case NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpec:
6174  case NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpecWithTemplate:
6175  Record->push_back(Kind == NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpecWithTemplate);
6176  AddTypeRef(NNS.getTypeLoc().getType());
6177  AddTypeLoc(NNS.getTypeLoc());
6178  AddSourceLocation(NNS.getLocalSourceRange().getEnd());
6179  break;
6180 
6181  case NestedNameSpecifier::Global:
6182  AddSourceLocation(NNS.getLocalSourceRange().getEnd());
6183  break;
6184 
6185  case NestedNameSpecifier::Super:
6186  AddDeclRef(NNS.getNestedNameSpecifier()->getAsRecordDecl());
6187  AddSourceRange(NNS.getLocalSourceRange());
6188  break;
6189  }
6190  }
6191 }
6192 
6193 void ASTRecordWriter::AddTemplateParameterList(
6194  const TemplateParameterList *TemplateParams) {
6195  assert(TemplateParams && "No TemplateParams!");
6196  AddSourceLocation(TemplateParams->getTemplateLoc());
6197  AddSourceLocation(TemplateParams->getLAngleLoc());
6198  AddSourceLocation(TemplateParams->getRAngleLoc());
6199 
6200  Record->push_back(TemplateParams->size());
6201  for (const auto &P : *TemplateParams)
6202  AddDeclRef(P);
6203  if (const Expr *RequiresClause = TemplateParams->getRequiresClause()) {
6204  Record->push_back(true);
6205  AddStmt(const_cast<Expr*>(RequiresClause));
6206  } else {
6207  Record->push_back(false);
6208  }
6209 }

6211 /// Emit a template argument list.
6212 void ASTRecordWriter::AddTemplateArgumentList(
6213  const TemplateArgumentList *TemplateArgs) {
6214  assert(TemplateArgs && "No TemplateArgs!");
6215  Record->push_back(TemplateArgs->size());
6216  for (int i = 0, e = TemplateArgs->size(); i != e; ++i)
6217  AddTemplateArgument(TemplateArgs->get(i));
6218 }

6220 void ASTRecordWriter::AddASTTemplateArgumentListInfo(
6221  const ASTTemplateArgumentListInfo *ASTTemplArgList) {
6222  assert(ASTTemplArgList && "No ASTTemplArgList!");
6223  AddSourceLocation(ASTTemplArgList->LAngleLoc);
6224  AddSourceLocation(ASTTemplArgList->RAngleLoc);
6225  Record->push_back(ASTTemplArgList->NumTemplateArgs);
6226  const TemplateArgumentLoc *TemplArgs = ASTTemplArgList->getTemplateArgs();
6227  for (int i = 0, e = ASTTemplArgList->NumTemplateArgs; i != e; ++i)
6228  AddTemplateArgumentLoc(TemplArgs[i]);

6231 void ASTRecordWriter::AddUnresolvedSet(const ASTUnresolvedSet &Set) {
6232  Record->push_back(Set.size());
6233  for (ASTUnresolvedSet::const_iterator
6234  I = Set.begin(), E = Set.end(); I != E; ++I) {
6235  AddDeclRef(I.getDecl());
6236  Record->push_back(I.getAccess());

6240 // FIXME: Move this out of the main ASTRecordWriter interface.
6241 void ASTRecordWriter::AddCXXBaseSpecifier(const CXXBaseSpecifier &Base) {
6242  Record->push_back(Base.isVirtual());
6243  Record->push_back(Base.isBaseOfClass());
6244  Record->push_back(Base.getAccessSpecifierAsWritten());
6245  Record->push_back(Base.getInheritConstructors());
6246  AddTypeSourceInfo(Base.getTypeSourceInfo());
6247  AddSourceRange(Base.getSourceRange());
6248  AddSourceLocation(Base.isPackExpansion()? Base.getEllipsisLoc()
6249  : SourceLocation());
6250 }

6252 static uint64_t EmitCXXBaseSpecifiers(ASTWriter &W,
6253  ArrayRef<CXXBaseSpecifier> Bases) {
6254  ASTWriter::RecordData Record;
6255  ASTRecordWriter Writer(W, Record);
6256  Writer.push_back(Bases.size());
6257 
6258  for (auto &Base : Bases)
6259  Writer.AddCXXBaseSpecifier(Base);
6260 
6261  return Writer.Emit(serialization::DECL_CXX_BASE_SPECIFIERS);
6262 }
6263 
6264 // FIXME: Move this out of the main ASTRecordWriter interface.
6265 void ASTRecordWriter::AddCXXBaseSpecifiers(ArrayRef<CXXBaseSpecifier> Bases) {
6266  AddOffset(EmitCXXBaseSpecifiers(*Writer, Bases));
6267 }
6268 
6269 static uint64_t
6270 EmitCXXCtorInitializers(ASTWriter &W,
6271  ArrayRef<CXXCtorInitializer *> CtorInits) {
6272  ASTWriter::RecordData Record;
6273  ASTRecordWriter Writer(W, Record);
6274  Writer.push_back(CtorInits.size());
6275 
6276  for (auto *Init : CtorInits) {
6277  if (Init->isBaseInitializer()) {
6278  Writer.push_back(CTOR_INITIALIZER_BASE);
6279  Writer.AddTypeSourceInfo(Init->getTypeSourceInfo());
6280  Writer.push_back(Init->isBaseVirtual());
6281  } else if (Init->isDelegatingInitializer()) {
6282  Writer.push_back(CTOR_INITIALIZER_DELEGATING);
6283  Writer.AddTypeSourceInfo(Init->getTypeSourceInfo());
6284  } else if (Init->isMemberInitializer()){
6285  Writer.push_back(CTOR_INITIALIZER_MEMBER);
6286  Writer.AddDeclRef(Init->getMember());
6287  } else {
6288  Writer.push_back(CTOR_INITIALIZER_INDIRECT_MEMBER);
6289  Writer.AddDeclRef(Init->getIndirectMember());
6290  }
6291 
6292  Writer.AddSourceLocation(Init->getMemberLocation());
6293  Writer.AddStmt(Init->getInit());
6294  Writer.AddSourceLocation(Init->getLParenLoc());
6295  Writer.AddSourceLocation(Init->getRParenLoc());
6296  Writer.push_back(Init->isWritten());
6297  if (Init->isWritten())
6298  Writer.push_back(Init->getSourceOrder());
6299  }
6300 
6301  return Writer.Emit(serialization::DECL_CXX_CTOR_INITIALIZERS);
6302 }
6303 
6304 // FIXME: Move this out of the main ASTRecordWriter interface.
6305 void ASTRecordWriter::AddCXXCtorInitializers(
6306  ArrayRef<CXXCtorInitializer *> CtorInits) {
6307  AddOffset(EmitCXXCtorInitializers(*Writer, CtorInits));
6308 }
6309 
6310 void ASTRecordWriter::AddCXXDefinitionData(const CXXRecordDecl *D) {
6311  auto &Data = D->data();
6312 
6313  Record->push_back(Data.IsLambda);
6314 
6315  BitsPacker DefinitionBits;
6316 
6317  bool ShouldSkipCheckingODR = shouldSkipCheckingODR(D);
6318  DefinitionBits.addBit(ShouldSkipCheckingODR);
6319 
6320 #define FIELD(Name, Width, Merge) \
6321  if (!DefinitionBits.canWriteNextNBits(Width)) { \
6322  Record->push_back(DefinitionBits); \
6323  DefinitionBits.reset(0); \
6324  } \
6325  DefinitionBits.addBits(Data.Name, Width);
6326 
6327 #include "clang/AST/CXXRecordDeclDefinitionBits.def"
6328 #undef FIELD
6329 
6330  Record->push_back(DefinitionBits);
6331 
6332  // We only perform ODR checks for decls not in GMF.
6333  if (!ShouldSkipCheckingODR)
6334  // getODRHash will compute the ODRHash if it has not been previously
6335  // computed.
6336  Record->push_back(D->getODRHash());
6337 
6338  bool ModulesDebugInfo =
6339  Writer->Context->getLangOpts().ModulesDebugInfo && !D->isDependentType();
6340  Record->push_back(ModulesDebugInfo);
6341  if (ModulesDebugInfo)
6342  Writer->ModularCodegenDecls.push_back(Writer->GetDeclRef(D));
6343 
6344  // IsLambda bit is already saved.
6345 
6346  AddUnresolvedSet(Data.Conversions.get(*Writer->Context));
6347  Record->push_back(Data.ComputedVisibleConversions);
6348  if (Data.ComputedVisibleConversions)
6349  AddUnresolvedSet(Data.VisibleConversions.get(*Writer->Context));
6350  // Data.Definition is the owning decl, no need to write it.
6351 
6352  if (!Data.IsLambda) {
6353  Record->push_back(Data.NumBases);
6354  if (Data.NumBases > 0)
6355  AddCXXBaseSpecifiers(Data.bases());
6356 
6357  // FIXME: Make VBases lazily computed when needed to avoid storing them.
6358  Record->push_back(Data.NumVBases);
6359  if (Data.NumVBases > 0)
6360  AddCXXBaseSpecifiers(Data.vbases());
6361 
6362  AddDeclRef(D->getFirstFriend());
6363  } else {
6364  auto &Lambda = D->getLambdaData();
6365 
6366  BitsPacker LambdaBits;
6367  LambdaBits.addBits(Lambda.DependencyKind, /*Width=*/2);
6368  LambdaBits.addBit(Lambda.IsGenericLambda);
6369  LambdaBits.addBits(Lambda.CaptureDefault, /*Width=*/2);
6370  LambdaBits.addBits(Lambda.NumCaptures, /*Width=*/15);
6371  LambdaBits.addBit(Lambda.HasKnownInternalLinkage);
6372  Record->push_back(LambdaBits);
6373 
6374  Record->push_back(Lambda.NumExplicitCaptures);
6375  Record->push_back(Lambda.ManglingNumber);
6376  Record->push_back(D->getDeviceLambdaManglingNumber());
6377  // The lambda context declaration and index within the context are provided
6378  // separately, so that they can be used for merging.
6379  AddTypeSourceInfo(Lambda.MethodTyInfo);
6380  for (unsigned I = 0, N = Lambda.NumCaptures; I != N; ++I) {
6381  const LambdaCapture &Capture = Lambda.Captures.front()[I];
6382  AddSourceLocation(Capture.getLocation());
6383 
6384  BitsPacker CaptureBits;
6385  CaptureBits.addBit(Capture.isImplicit());
6386  CaptureBits.addBits(Capture.getCaptureKind(), /*Width=*/3);
6387  Record->push_back(CaptureBits);
6388 
6389  switch (Capture.getCaptureKind()) {
6390  case LCK_StarThis:
6391  case LCK_This:
6392  case LCK_VLAType:
6393  break;
6394  case LCK_ByCopy:
6395  case LCK_ByRef:
6396  ValueDecl *Var =
6397  Capture.capturesVariable() ? Capture.getCapturedVar() : nullptr;
6398  AddDeclRef(Var);
6399  AddSourceLocation(Capture.isPackExpansion() ? Capture.getEllipsisLoc()
6400  : SourceLocation());
6401  break;
6402  }
6403  }
6404  }
6405 }
6406 
6407 void ASTRecordWriter::AddVarDeclInit(const VarDecl *VD) {
6408  const Expr *Init = VD->getInit();
6409  if (!Init) {
6410  push_back(0);
6411  return;
6412  }
6413 
6414  uint64_t Val = 1;
6415  if (EvaluatedStmt *ES = VD->getEvaluatedStmt()) {
6416  Val |= (ES->HasConstantInitialization ? 2 : 0);
6417  Val |= (ES->HasConstantDestruction ? 4 : 0);
6418  APValue *Evaluated = VD->getEvaluatedValue();
6419  // If the evaluated result is constant, emit it.
6420  if (Evaluated && (Evaluated->isInt() || Evaluated->isFloat()))
6421  Val |= 8;
6422  }
6423  push_back(Val);
6424  if (Val & 8) {
6425  AddAPValue(*VD->getEvaluatedValue());
6426  }
6427 
6428  writeStmtRef(Init);
6429 }
6430 
6431 void ASTWriter::ReaderInitialized(ASTReader *Reader) {
6432  assert(Reader && "Cannot remove chain");
6433  assert((!Chain || Chain == Reader) && "Cannot replace chain");
6434  assert(FirstDeclID == NextDeclID &&
6435  FirstTypeID == NextTypeID &&
6436  FirstIdentID == NextIdentID &&
6437  FirstMacroID == NextMacroID &&
6438  FirstSubmoduleID == NextSubmoduleID &&
6439  FirstSelectorID == NextSelectorID &&
6440  "Setting chain after writing has started.");
6441 
6442  Chain = Reader;
6443 
6444  // Note, this will get called multiple times, once one the reader starts up
6445  // and again each time it's done reading a PCH or module.
6446  FirstDeclID = NUM_PREDEF_DECL_IDS + Chain->getTotalNumDecls();
6447  FirstTypeID = NUM_PREDEF_TYPE_IDS + Chain->getTotalNumTypes();
6448  FirstIdentID = NUM_PREDEF_IDENT_IDS + Chain->getTotalNumIdentifiers();
6449  FirstMacroID = NUM_PREDEF_MACRO_IDS + Chain->getTotalNumMacros();
6450  FirstSubmoduleID = NUM_PREDEF_SUBMODULE_IDS + Chain->getTotalNumSubmodules();
6451  FirstSelectorID = NUM_PREDEF_SELECTOR_IDS + Chain->getTotalNumSelectors();
6452  NextDeclID = FirstDeclID;
6453  NextTypeID = FirstTypeID;
6454  NextIdentID = FirstIdentID;
6455  NextMacroID = FirstMacroID;
6456  NextSelectorID = FirstSelectorID;
6457  NextSubmoduleID = FirstSubmoduleID;
6458 }

6460 void ASTWriter::IdentifierRead(IdentID ID, IdentifierInfo *II) {
6461  // Always keep the highest ID. See \p TypeRead() for more information.
6462  IdentID &StoredID = IdentifierIDs[II];
6463  if (ID > StoredID)
6464  StoredID = ID;
6465 }
6466 
6467 void ASTWriter::MacroRead(serialization::MacroID ID, MacroInfo *MI) {
6468  // Always keep the highest ID. See \p TypeRead() for more information.
6469  MacroID &StoredID = MacroIDs[MI];
6470  if (ID > StoredID)
6471  StoredID = ID;
6472 }
6473 
6474 void ASTWriter::TypeRead(TypeIdx Idx, QualType T) {
6475  // Always take the highest-numbered type index. This copes with an interesting
6476  // case for chained AST writing where we schedule writing the type and then,
6477  // later, deserialize the type from another AST. In this case, we want to
6478  // keep the higher-numbered entry so that we can properly write it out to
6479  // the AST file.
6480  TypeIdx &StoredIdx = TypeIdxs[T];
6481  if (Idx.getIndex() >= StoredIdx.getIndex())
6482  StoredIdx = Idx;
6483 }
6484 
6485 void ASTWriter::SelectorRead(SelectorID ID, Selector S) {
6486  // Always keep the highest ID. See \p TypeRead() for more information.
6487  SelectorID &StoredID = SelectorIDs[S];
6488  if (ID > StoredID)
6489  StoredID = ID;
6490 }

6503 void ASTWriter::CompletedTagDefinition(const TagDecl *D) {
6504  if (Chain && Chain->isProcessingUpdateRecords()) return;
6505  assert(D->isCompleteDefinition());
6506  assert(!WritingAST && "Already writing the AST!");
6507  if (auto *RD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D)) {
6508  // We are interested when a PCH decl is modified.
6509  if (RD->isFromASTFile()) {
6510  // A forward reference was mutated into a definition. Rewrite it.
6511  // FIXME: This happens during template instantiation, should we
6512  // have created a new definition decl instead ?
6513  assert(isTemplateInstantiation(RD->getTemplateSpecializationKind()) &&
6514  "completed a tag from another module but not by instantiation?");
6515  DeclUpdates[RD].push_back(
6516  DeclUpdate(UPD_CXX_INSTANTIATED_CLASS_DEFINITION));
6517  }
6518  }
6519 }

6521 static bool isImportedDeclContext(ASTReader *Chain, const Decl *D) {
6522  if (D->isFromASTFile())
6523  return true;
6524 
6525  // The predefined __va_list_tag struct is imported if we imported any decls.
6526  // FIXME: This is a gross hack.
6527  return D == D->getASTContext().getVaListTagDecl();
6528 }
6529 
6530 void ASTWriter::AddedVisibleDecl(const DeclContext *DC, const Decl *D) {
6531  if (Chain && Chain->isProcessingUpdateRecords()) return;
6532  assert(DC->isLookupContext() &&
6533  "Should not add lookup results to non-lookup contexts!");
6534 
6535  // TU is handled elsewhere.
6536  if (isa<TranslationUnitDecl>(DC))
6537  return;
6538 
6539  // Namespaces are handled elsewhere, except for template instantiations of
6540  // FunctionTemplateDecls in namespaces. We are interested in cases where the
6541  // local instantiations are added to an imported context. Only happens when
6542  // adding ADL lookup candidates, for example templated friends.
6543  if (isa<NamespaceDecl>(DC) && D->getFriendObjectKind() == Decl::FOK_None &&
6544  !isa<FunctionTemplateDecl>(D))
6545  return;
6546 
6547  // We're only interested in cases where a local declaration is added to an
6548  // imported context.
6549  if (D->isFromASTFile() || !isImportedDeclContext(Chain, cast<Decl>(DC)))
6550  return;
6551 
6552  assert(DC == DC->getPrimaryContext() && "added to non-primary context");
6553  assert(!getDefinitiveDeclContext(DC) && "DeclContext not definitive!");
6554  assert(!WritingAST && "Already writing the AST!");
6555  if (UpdatedDeclContexts.insert(DC) && !cast<Decl>(DC)->isFromASTFile()) {
6556  // We're adding a visible declaration to a predefined decl context. Ensure
6557  // that we write out all of its lookup results so we don't get a nasty
6558  // surprise when we try to emit its lookup table.
6559  llvm::append_range(DeclsToEmitEvenIfUnreferenced, DC->decls());
6560  }
6561  DeclsToEmitEvenIfUnreferenced.push_back(D);
6562 }
6563 
6564 void ASTWriter::AddedCXXImplicitMember(const CXXRecordDecl *RD, const Decl *D) {
6565  if (Chain && Chain->isProcessingUpdateRecords()) return;
6566  assert(D->isImplicit());
6567 
6568  // We're only interested in cases where a local declaration is added to an
6569  // imported context.
6570  if (D->isFromASTFile() || !isImportedDeclContext(Chain, RD))
6571  return;
6572 
6573  if (!isa<CXXMethodDecl>(D))
6574  return;
6575 
6576  // A decl coming from PCH was modified.
6577  assert(RD->isCompleteDefinition());
6578  assert(!WritingAST && "Already writing the AST!");
6579  DeclUpdates[RD].push_back(DeclUpdate(UPD_CXX_ADDED_IMPLICIT_MEMBER, D));
6580 }

6582 void ASTWriter::ResolvedExceptionSpec(const FunctionDecl *FD) {
6583  if (Chain && Chain->isProcessingUpdateRecords()) return;
6584  assert(!DoneWritingDeclsAndTypes && "Already done writing updates!");
6585  if (!Chain) return;
6586  Chain->forEachImportedKeyDecl(FD, [&](const Decl *D) {
6587  // If we don't already know the exception specification for this redecl
6588  // chain, add an update record for it.
6589  if (isUnresolvedExceptionSpec(cast<FunctionDecl>(D)
6590  ->getType()
6591  ->castAs<FunctionProtoType>()
6592  ->getExceptionSpecType()))
6593  DeclUpdates[D].push_back(UPD_CXX_RESOLVED_EXCEPTION_SPEC);
6594  });
6595 }

6694 void ASTWriter::DeclarationMarkedUsed(const Decl *D) {

6700  // completion of the redeclaration chain of the entity.

6753 void ASTWriter::AddedCXXTemplateSpecialization(
6754  const ClassTemplateDecl *TD, const ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl *D) {

6756 
6757  if (!TD->getFirstDecl()->isFromASTFile())
6758  return;
6759  if (Chain && Chain->isProcessingUpdateRecords())
6760  return;
6761 
6762  DeclsToEmitEvenIfUnreferenced.push_back(D);
6763 }
6764 
6765 void ASTWriter::AddedCXXTemplateSpecialization(
6766  const VarTemplateDecl *TD, const VarTemplateSpecializationDecl *D) {
6767  assert(!WritingAST && "Already writing the AST!");
6768 
6769  if (!TD->getFirstDecl()->isFromASTFile())
6770  return;
6771  if (Chain && Chain->isProcessingUpdateRecords())
6772  return;
6773 
6774  DeclsToEmitEvenIfUnreferenced.push_back(D);
6775 }
6776 
6777 void ASTWriter::AddedCXXTemplateSpecialization(const FunctionTemplateDecl *TD,
6778  const FunctionDecl *D) {
6779  assert(!WritingAST && "Already writing the AST!");
6780 
6781  if (!TD->getFirstDecl()->isFromASTFile())
6782  return;
6783  if (Chain && Chain->isProcessingUpdateRecords())
6784  return;
6785 
6786  DeclsToEmitEvenIfUnreferenced.push_back(D);
6787 }

6795 class OMPClauseWriter : public OMPClauseVisitor<OMPClauseWriter> {
6796  ASTRecordWriter &Record;
6797 
6798 public:
6799  OMPClauseWriter(ASTRecordWriter &Record) : Record(Record) {}
6800 #define GEN_CLANG_CLAUSE_CLASS
6801 #define CLAUSE_CLASS(Enum, Str, Class) void Visit##Class(Class *S);
6802 #include "llvm/Frontend/OpenMP/OMP.inc"
6803  void writeClause(OMPClause *C);
6804  void VisitOMPClauseWithPreInit(OMPClauseWithPreInit *C);
6805  void VisitOMPClauseWithPostUpdate(OMPClauseWithPostUpdate *C);
6806 };
6807 
6808 }

6810 void ASTRecordWriter::writeOMPClause(OMPClause *C) {
6811  OMPClauseWriter(*this).writeClause(C);
6812 }
6813 
6814 void OMPClauseWriter::writeClause(OMPClause *C) {
6815  Record.push_back(unsigned(C->getClauseKind()));
6816  Visit(C);
6817  Record.AddSourceLocation(C->getBeginLoc());
6818  Record.AddSourceLocation(C->getEndLoc());
6819 }
6820

6822  Record.push_back(uint64_t(C->getCaptureRegion()));
6823  Record.AddStmt(C->getPreInitStmt());
6824 }
6825 
6826 void OMPClauseWriter::VisitOMPClauseWithPostUpdate(OMPClauseWithPostUpdate *C) {

6828  Record.AddStmt(C->getPostUpdateExpr());
6829 }

6920  Record.AddStmt(NumIter);
6921  for (unsigned I = 0, E = C->getLoopNumIterations().size(); I <E; ++I)
6922  Record.AddStmt(C->getLoopCounter(I));
6923  Record.AddSourceLocation(C->getLParenLoc());

7071 void OMPClauseWriter::VisitOMPReductionClause(OMPReductionClause *C) {
7072  Record.push_back(C->varlist_size());
7073  Record.writeEnum(C->getModifier());
7074  VisitOMPClauseWithPostUpdate(C);
7075  Record.AddSourceLocation(C->getLParenLoc());
7076  Record.AddSourceLocation(C->getModifierLoc());
7077  Record.AddSourceLocation(C->getColonLoc());
7078  Record.AddNestedNameSpecifierLoc(C->getQualifierLoc());
7079  Record.AddDeclarationNameInfo(C->getNameInfo());
7080  for (auto *VE : C->varlists())
7081  Record.AddStmt(VE);
7082  for (auto *VE : C->privates())
7083  Record.AddStmt(VE);
7084  for (auto *E : C->lhs_exprs())
7085  Record.AddStmt(E);
7086  for (auto *E : C->rhs_exprs())
7087  Record.AddStmt(E);
7088  for (auto *E : C->reduction_ops())
7089  Record.AddStmt(E);
7090  if (C->getModifier() == clang::OMPC_REDUCTION_inscan) {
7091  for (auto *E : C->copy_ops())
7092  Record.AddStmt(E);
7093  for (auto *E : C->copy_array_temps())
7094  Record.AddStmt(E);
7095  for (auto *E : C->copy_array_elems())
7096  Record.AddStmt(E);
7097  }
7098 }

7223  Record.AddSourceLocation(C->getOmpAllMemoryLoc());
7224  for (auto *VE : C->varlists())

7238 void OMPClauseWriter::VisitOMPMapClause(OMPMapClause *C) {
7239  Record.push_back(C->varlist_size());
7240  Record.push_back(C->getUniqueDeclarationsNum());
7241  Record.push_back(C->getTotalComponentListNum());
7242  Record.push_back(C->getTotalComponentsNum());
7243  Record.AddSourceLocation(C->getLParenLoc());
7244  bool HasIteratorModifier = false;
7245  for (unsigned I = 0; I < NumberOfOMPMapClauseModifiers; ++I) {
7246  Record.push_back(C->getMapTypeModifier(I));
7247  Record.AddSourceLocation(C->getMapTypeModifierLoc(I));
7248  if (C->getMapTypeModifier(I) == OMPC_MAP_MODIFIER_iterator)
7249  HasIteratorModifier = true;
7250  }
7251  Record.AddNestedNameSpecifierLoc(C->getMapperQualifierLoc());
7252  Record.AddDeclarationNameInfo(C->getMapperIdInfo());
7253  Record.push_back(C->getMapType());
7254  Record.AddSourceLocation(C->getMapLoc());
7255  Record.AddSourceLocation(C->getColonLoc());
7256  for (auto *E : C->varlists())
7257  Record.AddStmt(E);
7258  for (auto *E : C->mapperlists())
7259  Record.AddStmt(E);
7260  if (HasIteratorModifier)
7261  Record.AddStmt(C->getIteratorModifier());
7262  for (auto *D : C->all_decls())
7263  Record.AddDeclRef(D);
7264  for (auto N : C->all_num_lists())
7265  Record.push_back(N);
7266  for (auto N : C->all_lists_sizes())
7267  Record.push_back(N);
7268  for (auto &M : C->all_components()) {
7269  Record.AddStmt(M.getAssociatedExpression());
7270  Record.AddDeclRef(M.getAssociatedDeclaration());
7271  }
7272 }

7278  Record.AddStmt(C->getAllocator());
7279  for (auto *VE : C->varlists())
7280  Record.AddStmt(VE);

7339 void OMPClauseWriter::VisitOMPToClause(OMPToClause *C) {
7340  Record.push_back(C->varlist_size());
7341  Record.push_back(C->getUniqueDeclarationsNum());
7342  Record.push_back(C->getTotalComponentListNum());
7343  Record.push_back(C->getTotalComponentsNum());
7344  Record.AddSourceLocation(C->getLParenLoc());
7345  for (unsigned I = 0; I < NumberOfOMPMotionModifiers; ++I) {
7346  Record.push_back(C->getMotionModifier(I));
7347  Record.AddSourceLocation(C->getMotionModifierLoc(I));
7348  }
7349  Record.AddNestedNameSpecifierLoc(C->getMapperQualifierLoc());
7350  Record.AddDeclarationNameInfo(C->getMapperIdInfo());
7351  Record.AddSourceLocation(C->getColonLoc());
7352  for (auto *E : C->varlists())
7353  Record.AddStmt(E);
7354  for (auto *E : C->mapperlists())
7355  Record.AddStmt(E);
7356  for (auto *D : C->all_decls())
7357  Record.AddDeclRef(D);
7358  for (auto N : C->all_num_lists())
7359  Record.push_back(N);
7360  for (auto N : C->all_lists_sizes())
7361  Record.push_back(N);
7362  for (auto &M : C->all_components()) {
7363  Record.AddStmt(M.getAssociatedExpression());
7364  Record.writeBool(M.isNonContiguous());
7365  Record.AddDeclRef(M.getAssociatedDeclaration());
7366  }
7367 }

7604 void ASTRecordWriter::writeOMPTraitInfo(const OMPTraitInfo *TI) {
7605  writeUInt32(TI->Sets.size());
7606  for (const auto &Set : TI->Sets) {
7607  writeEnum(Set.Kind);
7608  writeUInt32(Set.Selectors.size());
7609  for (const auto &Selector : Set.Selectors) {
7610  writeEnum(Selector.Kind);
7611  writeBool(Selector.ScoreOrCondition);
7612  if (Selector.ScoreOrCondition)
7613  writeExprRef(Selector.ScoreOrCondition);
7614  writeUInt32(Selector.Properties.size());
7615  for (const auto &Property : Selector.Properties)
7616  writeEnum(Property.Kind);
7617  }
7618  }
7619 }
7620 
7621 void ASTRecordWriter::writeOMPChildren(OMPChildren *Data) {
7622  if (!Data)
7623  return;
7624  writeUInt32(Data->getNumClauses());
7625  writeUInt32(Data->getNumChildren());
7626  writeBool(Data->hasAssociatedStmt());
7627  for (unsigned I = 0, E = Data->getNumClauses(); I < E; ++I)
7628  writeOMPClause(Data->getClauses()[I]);
7629  if (Data->hasAssociatedStmt())
7630  AddStmt(Data->getAssociatedStmt());
7631  for (unsigned I = 0, E = Data->getNumChildren(); I < E; ++I)
7632  AddStmt(Data->getChildren()[I]);
7633 }
7634 
7635 void ASTRecordWriter::writeOpenACCClause(const OpenACCClause *C) {
7636  writeEnum(C->getClauseKind());
7637  writeSourceLocation(C->getBeginLoc());
7638  writeSourceLocation(C->getEndLoc());
7639 
7640  switch (C->getClauseKind()) {
7641  case OpenACCClauseKind::Default: {
7642  const auto *DC = cast<OpenACCDefaultClause>(C);
7643  writeSourceLocation(DC->getLParenLoc());
7644  writeEnum(DC->getDefaultClauseKind());
7645  return;
7646  }
7647  case OpenACCClauseKind::If: {
7648  const auto *IC = cast<OpenACCIfClause>(C);
7649  writeSourceLocation(IC->getLParenLoc());
7650  AddStmt(const_cast<Expr *>(IC->getConditionExpr()));
7651  return;
7652  }
7653  case OpenACCClauseKind::Self: {
7654  const auto *SC = cast<OpenACCIfClause>(C);
7655  writeSourceLocation(SC->getLParenLoc());
7656  writeBool(SC->hasConditionExpr());
7657  if (SC->hasConditionExpr())
7658  AddStmt(const_cast<Expr *>(SC->getConditionExpr()));
7659  return;
7660  }
7661  case OpenACCClauseKind::NumGangs: {
7662  const auto *NGC = cast<OpenACCNumGangsClause>(C);
7663  writeSourceLocation(NGC->getLParenLoc());
7664  writeUInt32(NGC->getIntExprs().size());
7665  for (Expr *E : NGC->getIntExprs())
7666  AddStmt(E);
7667  return;
7668  }
7669  case OpenACCClauseKind::NumWorkers: {
7670  const auto *NWC = cast<OpenACCNumWorkersClause>(C);
7671  writeSourceLocation(NWC->getLParenLoc());
7672  AddStmt(const_cast<Expr *>(NWC->getIntExpr()));
7673  return;
7674  }
7675  case OpenACCClauseKind::VectorLength: {
7676  const auto *NWC = cast<OpenACCVectorLengthClause>(C);
7677  writeSourceLocation(NWC->getLParenLoc());
7678  AddStmt(const_cast<Expr *>(NWC->getIntExpr()));
7679  return;
7680  }
7681  case OpenACCClauseKind::Finalize:
7682  case OpenACCClauseKind::IfPresent:
7683  case OpenACCClauseKind::Seq:
7684  case OpenACCClauseKind::Independent:
7685  case OpenACCClauseKind::Auto:
7686  case OpenACCClauseKind::Worker:
7687  case OpenACCClauseKind::Vector:
7688  case OpenACCClauseKind::NoHost:
7689  case OpenACCClauseKind::Copy:
7690  case OpenACCClauseKind::UseDevice:
7691  case OpenACCClauseKind::Attach:
7692  case OpenACCClauseKind::Delete:
7693  case OpenACCClauseKind::Detach:
7694  case OpenACCClauseKind::Device:
7695  case OpenACCClauseKind::DevicePtr:
7696  case OpenACCClauseKind::DeviceResident:
7697  case OpenACCClauseKind::FirstPrivate:
7698  case OpenACCClauseKind::Host:
7699  case OpenACCClauseKind::Link:
7700  case OpenACCClauseKind::NoCreate:
7701  case OpenACCClauseKind::Present:
7702  case OpenACCClauseKind::Private:
7703  case OpenACCClauseKind::CopyOut:
7704  case OpenACCClauseKind::CopyIn:
7705  case OpenACCClauseKind::Create:
7706  case OpenACCClauseKind::Reduction:
7707  case OpenACCClauseKind::Collapse:
7708  case OpenACCClauseKind::Bind:
7709  case OpenACCClauseKind::DeviceNum:
7710  case OpenACCClauseKind::DefaultAsync:
7711  case OpenACCClauseKind::DeviceType:
7712  case OpenACCClauseKind::DType:
7713  case OpenACCClauseKind::Async:
7714  case OpenACCClauseKind::Tile:
7715  case OpenACCClauseKind::Gang:
7716  case OpenACCClauseKind::Wait:
7717  case OpenACCClauseKind::Invalid:
7718  llvm_unreachable("Clause serialization not yet implemented");
7719  }
7720  llvm_unreachable("Invalid Clause Kind");
7721 }
7722 
7723 void ASTRecordWriter::writeOpenACCClauseList(
7724  ArrayRef<const OpenACCClause *> Clauses) {
7725  for (const OpenACCClause *Clause : Clauses)
7726  writeOpenACCClause(Clause);
7727 }
